title: chicken with potatoes and peppers(microwave)
directions: Microwave Directions:
In 3-quart microwave casserole, arrange chicken, skin side down, with thickest portions to the outer edge of casserole.
Cover with wax paper and microwave at High for 12 minutes, rearranging once; drain.
Remove chicken and place on paper towels; set aside.

title: grandmother motley's blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Add jam then vanilla.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add buttermilk and dry ingredients alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Bake in three greased and floured 8 or 9-inch pans (round) at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: five cup snacker mix
directions: Mix ingredients well together. Store in an airtight container.

title: "arni psito" - leg of lamb
directions: Make holes in meat with a sharp knife and insert cloves of garlic throughout the lamb.
Place in roasting pan with just enough water to barely cover bottom of pan.
Bake in 350° to 375° oven for about 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Melt butter; add lemon juice and oregano.
Pour lemon mixture over lamb and bake for about 1 1/2 hours, basting every few minutes with sauce. Remove from oven and let set a few minutes.
Cut meat from bone and place meat in juice.
Continue baking in oven until fork-tender.

title: diabetic blueberry cupcakes
directions: Cream in bowl the margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg.
In another bowl, sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices.
Stir into creamed mixture, alternating with the milk just until mixed.
Fold in berries.
Fill 12 muffin cups 1/2 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, Cheddar cheese, mayonnaise, onion and celery. Put into a greased 9 x 13 pan. Salt and pepper to taste. Top with bacon and green onions. Do not cover pan while baking. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: pork chops with sour cream
directions: Brown pork chops in 1 tablespoon oil.
Place chops in roasting pan.
Saute onion and mushrooms in same oil.
Add sour cream. Pour mixture over chops.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
May be made ahead and reheated.

title: tamale bites
directions: Combine corn bread, salt and enough of the enchilada sauce to combine with the ground beef to bind all together well.
Mix well; shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 18 to 20 minutes, or until done.
Drain on paper towels.

title: tuna pate
directions: Blend cream cheese, chili sauce, parsley, onions and hot pepper sauce.
Gradually mix in drained tuna.
Beat until mixture is blended.
Pack in a 4-cup mold or small bowl.
Chill 3 hours. Unmold on plate.
Garnish top with sliced stuffed olives.
Serve with assorted crackers (great on Ritz crackers).

title: bohemian cake
directions: Cream sugars and shortening; add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add milk alternately with flour which has been sifted with baking powder.
Add vanilla, then fold in nuts and coconut.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buckeye's
directions: Mix together oleo, peanut butter, sugar and Rice Krispies. Form balls.
Dip in chocolate chips and paraffin wax.

title: western cake bun
directions: Mix sugar, butter, and milk.
Separate eggs.
Add yolks to milk mixture.
Sift together flour, soda and powder.
Add to mixture. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in to mixture.
Fold in grated nuts.
Pour into Bundt or tube pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter each biscuit; butter tube pan.
Place chopped nuts in bottom of pan.
Mix 2/3 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon in bag.
Put biscuits in to coat with sugar and cinnamon.
Drop biscuit pieces into pan.
Do not press down.
Mix margarine, 1 cup sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon; heat to boiling.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes (enough to dissolve sugar).
Pour over biscuits and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab apple bread
directions: Mix and put in greased bread pan. Sprinkle top of mixture with 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: nancy's coconut macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Stir in egg whites and extract; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheets.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325° or until brown around edges.
Remove from baking sheets immediately.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Slice cookie dough in 1-inch slices.
Cut each slice in quarters.
Grease miniature muffin cups with melted butter.
Lay one piece of dough into each miniature muffin cup.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
While cookies are hot and puffed, gently push a peanut butter cup onto each cookie.
Cool; remove from muffin cups. Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken and wild rice salad
directions: Best if made a day ahead!

title: squash puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil and fry until brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover
and chill for 2 hours. Serve as a dip for fresh vegetables.

title: sweet pickles(from dills)
directions: Boil all except pickles and pour on dills.
Sweet syrup replaces dill syrup.

title: squash pecan casserole
directions: Mix the undiluted soup with the eggs and cheese. Place half of squash in a buttered baking dish and pour over half the mushroom mixture. Sprinkle with half the pecans. Repeat layers. Top with bread crumbs. Place in a 350° oven and bake until crumbs are golden brown. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: cinnamon rolls("make the night before")
directions: Thaw
rolls
just enough to separate.
Sprinkle nuts on bottom of
a greased Bundt pan.
Mix sugars and cinnamon.
Dip each roll in
melted butter; roll in sugar mixture.
Place in pan, side
by side.
Pour
remaining butter and sugar mixture over rolls.
Let rise overnight.
Bake for about 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes and invert.

title: apple carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, vanilla and oil.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir into liquid mixture.
Add carrots, apples and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: egg salad
directions: Boil eggs (well done).
Chop eggs.
Add salad dressing; mix well.
Add pickle relish, mustard, salt and paprika to egg mixture, mixed.
Garnish with paprika.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients alternately with milk; add vanilla.
This mixture can be rolled and cut out, dropped by teaspoon or filled with raisins. Bake at 425° until golden brown (6 to 8 minutes).
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt 7 candy bars with a stick of margarine in microwave oven. Set aside.
Cream sugar with the second stick of margarine.
Add egg, baking soda, milk and flour.
Stir well to mix.
Add candy bar mixture and pecans.
Stir well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 70 to 90 minutes at 300°.

title: sauteed vegetables
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium heat.
Add vegetables. Cook and stir until tender.
Add salad dressing mix; toss to coat well.
Stir in vinegar until well mixed.
Serve warm.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: golden glow salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add lemon juice and enough cold water to pineapple juice to make one cup.
Stir into gelatin, chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in pineapple and carrots.
Chill until firm. Serves 6.

title: no-bake alaska supreme
directions: In medium bowl, mix unflavored gelatine with 1/4 cup sugar. Add hot juice; stir until gelatine is completely dissolved.
With wire whip or rotary beater, blend in cranberry sauce and liqueur. Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.

title: gator or shark steak
directions: Cover fillets with salted water; refrigerate overnight.
Drain and mix equal parts of Dale's or Moore's marinade, water and garlic.
Soak at least 1 hour before grilling.
Drain.
Lightly salt and pepper fillets and cover with butter.
Continue brushing with butter until done while cooking.
Best meat in the world; worth trying.

title: jalapeno corn muffins
directions: Grease miniature muffin pan and place in a 400° oven for 5 minutes.
Place cornbread mix in a bowl; make a well in center. Combine eggs and remaining ingredients; add to cornbread mix, stirring until moistened.
Spoon into muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 11 minutes.

title: pecan filling (for 1 cake)
directions: Grind pecans first. Put milk and sugar in pot and mix well. When it starts to cook, add butter, vanilla and pecans. If it cooks too fast or is too thick, add your extra milk and cook on slow fire. Let cool, then frost cake.

title: pecan chess pie
directions: Mix
sugar and flour.
Add melted margarine.
Mix well; add beaten
eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Bake about 45 minutes in 350° oven or until set.

title: zucchini-pineapple bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs, salt, vanilla, zucchini and pineapple.
Mix.
Add rest of ingredients. Pour into greased tins (one large or two small loaf tins).
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: reduced fat broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal and next 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine broccoli and next 5 ingredients; stir well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.

title: cubed steak and gravy
directions: Prepare steak by spraying pan with Pam and adding oil in frying pan.
Heat.
Wash steak and roll in flour.
Put steak in hot grease and let brown on both sides.
Salt and pepper both sides.
After steak is done, steam by putting the lid on the pan and adding a little water.
Remove steak from pan.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine butter, eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour a layer of this into pie shell.
Slice bananas to cover.
Add another layer of pudding mixture and top with crushed pineapple.
Add remainder of bananas.
Add nuts and cover with Cool Whip.
Top with cherries. Refrigerate overnight for best results.

title: fresh strawberry pecan pie
directions: Crust:
Melt oleo and combine with flour and 1 cup of pecans. Form into 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool.

title: apple salad
directions: Dissolve jello and marshmallows in the hot water.
Chill until partly set.
Add pineapple, apples and nuts.
Chill until firm. Mix the last 4 ingredients for the topping.
Cook the eggs, sugar and lemon juice, then add the Dream Whip after it is cooled.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, vanilla and sugars until well blended.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add soda to pumpkin and mix well.
Chopped nuts and raisins may be added.
Grease 3 small loaf pans.
Fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: debra's mexican cheese squares
directions: Mix grated cheeses with flour and add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 35 squares.

title: persian chicken soup(obgoosh)
directions: First, rinse rice.
Cover with salt and water; put aside to soak.
Put chicken in a large pot; cover with water and about 1 inch more.
Add onion and salt to taste (approximately 2 teaspoons).
Slow boil for 1 hour, uncovered.
Drain beans and add to pot.
Add approximately 2 teaspoons of turmeric.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours, covered.
Drain rice after adding beans to pot.
Boil a large pot of water with salt.
Add rice; boil 5 to 10 minutes. Immediately drain and rinse with cold water.
Add oil with a little turmeric to bottom of pot, just enough to cover bottom. Put heat on low; heat oil until it starts to spit.
Add rice. Cook on low 1/2 hour more.
Eat with chicken soup poured over the rice on your plate.
Eat with radish and pita bread on the side. Easy and yummy!

title: brown rice with vegetables
directions: Use 2 cups brown rice and cook according to directions listed on back of box.
In a large skillet, put in 2 tablespoons of olive oil.
Over low heat, saute red pepper and green pepper for 5 minutes.
Then add onion and mushrooms for 5 to 8 minutes.
Add zucchini and finish just until tender.
When rice is cooked, mix together with sauteed vegetables.
Makes a nice side dish with any meat entree.

title: fruit syrup
directions: Simmer for 10 minutes.
That is it.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add tomatoes (cut with grater), tomato paste, water, parsley, salt, sugar, garlic powder, pepper and oregano.
Simmer, uncovered, for about 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook lasagna in large saucepan; drain.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, spread about 1 cup sauce, then alternate layers of lasagna, sauce and cheeses, ending with sauce and cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: tiramisu torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour two 9-inch round baking pans. Beat together cake mix, coffee and egg whites on low speed until moistened. Beat on high for 2 minutes. Fold in chopped candy bars. Pour batter into pans and bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until tested done. Set aside to cool. When cool, remove cake from pans and cut horizontally to make 4 layers.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown green peppers and onion in butter.
Add cooked sausage. Grease a 9 x 15-inch dish.
Press crescent rolls in bottom without tearing apart.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on crust.
Mix eggs and milk together and set aside.
Pour sausage on crust, then egg mixture.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients in a large bowl; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, until center springs back when touched lightly.
Cool, right side up, for about 25 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix together and bake 1 hour or until brown at 350°.

title: friendship tea
directions: Put in mixing bowl and mix thoroughly.
Store in jar.
When served, put 2 teaspoons in cup and pour boiling water over it.

title: pepperoni pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Using fingers, press out dough into flat rounds.
Top with tomato sauce. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 5 to 8 minutes or until lightly brown on the edges and cheese is melted.
Serve warm.

title: cheese log
directions: Grate Cracker Barrel cheese before it gets to room temperature.
Let all cheese come to room temperature.
Put all together and work up with your hands.
Squeeze until mixed well. Separate into 4 or 5 small rolls.
Roll in chopped fine pecans or dry parsley flakes.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and place in refrigerator. Serve with Club or Escort crackers.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar.
Add eggs and banana pulp.
Beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients, milk and vanilla.
Mix well and stir in nuts.
Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan (greased and floured). Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool on rack.
Good with cream cheese.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening, margarine and light brown sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.

Sift and measure flour with baking powder and salt. Add alternately the flour and evaporated milk. Add maple flavor, vanilla and nuts. Mix well. Bake in well greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: valetta's meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, eggs, soup, tomato sauce, crackers and Worcestershire in a large bowl.
Mix lightly until blended. Shape into a 12 x 5-inch loaf in a jelly roll pan.
Brush with catsup.
Bake in a hot oven at 400° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, until richly glazed.
Serve hot or cold or cut into two loaves and freeze one.

title: patti's tempting taco salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss together or layer.
Serve immediately.

title: sherry freeze
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into dish and freeze.
May be poured into cooked pie crust or in pan and cut into squares to serve.

title: chocolate delights
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add nuts, vanilla and peanut butter.
Blend well and add oatmeal.
Drop by spoon on wax paper.

title: macaroni-kielbasa casserole
directions: Grate cheese and reserve.
Dice onion.
Cut kielbasa into 1/2-inch slices.
Cook macaroni according to package directions and drain well.
Mix together the cooked macaroni, onion, tomatoes and kielbasa.
Grease a 2-quart casserole and put in a layer of cheese, layer of macaroni and kielbasa mix; repeat, ending with a layer of cheese on top.
Add milk to 1 inch below edge of dish. Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: corn crab muffins
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Mix and sift together cornmeal, salt and baking powder.
Add to beaten eggs alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in shortening and mix well.
Stir in crabmeat. Pour into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients and store in a container.
Add about 3 tablespoons in a cup of boiling water and you have a delicious cup of Russian tea.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries, sugar and water until berries start to pop, then add 1 box cherry Jell-O with 1/2 cup water.
Add celery and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Tie celery tops and pickling spice loosely in cheesecloth. Place in boiling water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add the shrimp and salt and simmer for 5 minutes.
Drain.
In 1/2 gallon glass container combine the shrimp, chopped celery, onion rings, bell pepper, oil, vinegar, salt, bay leaves, capers and juice and tabasco.
Cover and chill for 24 hours before serving, stirring occasionally.
Drain liquid before serving.
Serve with party picks or as a buffet dish.
Serves 8-10.

title: shrimp florentine
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 pan with Pam. Spread spinach over bottom of dish and layer shrimp over spinach. Saute onions with butter until onions are clear. Add flour, then gradually blend in half and half, stirring until thickened. Slowly stir in wine or water; add salt, pepper and paprika. Pour over shrimp; sprinkle with cheese. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 325°. Allow to rest several minutes before serving.

title: bean and hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in butter; do not drain.
Add salt, pepper, flour, soup, molasses and sugar; mix well.
Add beans; mix lightly.
Place in a covered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour (remove cover for the last 15 minutes).

title: egg noodle stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let set about 45 minutes before serving, so sour cream can mix throughout.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Marinate sirloin in sauce made from other ingredients for 2 hours.
Charcoal about 15 minutes on each side for medium rare. This sauce is enough for about 3 1/2 to 4 pounds of beef.

title: dessert delight
directions: Melt oleo, add flour, sugar, and nuts.
Press into the bottom of a 9 by 13 inch pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Cool. In a mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, powdered sugar, and 1/2 the container of cool whip.
Spread this on the cooled crust.

title: christmas relish
directions: Soak above ingredients overnight in 1/2 c. vinegar, 1 teaspoon salt, and 1 1/2 cups sugar.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, saute onion in butter.
Add water and bouillon cubes. Bring to a boil and gradually add noodles and salt. Cook uncovered for 3 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and garlic powder. Cook for an additional 3 minutes and stir in milk.	Add cheese and pepper and stir until cheese is melted.

title: pineapple cuts
directions: Mix together pineapple, sugar and tapioca and set aside.
Mix other ingredients as pie crust.
Roll out 1/2 of the dough; place on cookie sheet and spread with filling.
Roll out other half of the dough and cover for top crust.
Put slits in top crust.
Bake at 350° until light brown, about 30 minutes.

title: dad's quick chili
directions: Combine hamburger and onion.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Combine in large kettle pork and beans, sliced stewed tomatoes, tomato juice, Chili-O mix, hamburger and onion.
Simmer 30 minutes, then ready to eat.

title: tuna chowder supreme
directions: Drain tuna; save liquid.
Flake the tuna and set it aside. Saute celery and onion in butter in a large saucepan over medium-low heat about 6 minutes.
Add the saved tuna liquid, milk and celery soup; stir gently to blend.
Add both corns and tuna. Cook until heated through, adding salt and pepper.
Should only take 3 or 4 minutes.
Do not let boil.
Sprinkle paprika on top and serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: In casserole dish, mix soup, milk and Spam or Treet.
Add cauliflower.

title: tofu soup
directions: Add white pepper, fish sauce and garlic powder to ground pork. Mix well; let stand.
Cut tofu into small pieces or cubes.
Cut green onions into 1 inch lengths; set aside.
Bring chicken broth and water to boil in Dutch oven or large pot.
Shape pork mixture into small balls and drop into boiling broth.
Boil for 5 to 7 minutes, until pork is cooked.
Add fish sauce to taste.
Add tofu and cook briefly.
Add green onions last.
Remove from heat immediately.
Serve.
Sprinkle a little white pepper on top of soup in serving bowls.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Hard-boil and shell the eggs.
Cut in half.
Mix the yolks with the other ingredients.
Put the mixture back into the egg white.
Chill and serve.

title: baked german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and reserve 1/2 cup grease. Return grease to skillet; add celery and onions.
Cook 1 minute. Blend in flour.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Stir in sugar, salt and pepper.
Put potatoes and bacon in a greased 3-quart casserole.
Pour thickened sauce over potatoes and bacon.
Stir, cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir in radishes.
Serve.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan; stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popped corn in 2 large, shallow roasting pans.
Mix well.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool completely.
Break apart and store in tightly covered containers.

title: chicken a la can can
directions: Combine soups, water, chicken and rice in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 7 minutes.
Put in casserole dish. Place onions on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Roll quartered biscuits in this mixture.
Layer in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle each layer with pecans and raisins.
Melt together butter and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil for a minute.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool for 5 minutes, then turn out of pan.

title: pretzel salad or dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix pineapple and cornstarch.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Cream well.
Add Cool Whip, saving some for a topping.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cooled pretzels.
Pour cooled pineapple over top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.
Chill.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Early in the day, preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, with a mixer, beat pumpkin with the next 10 ingredients until well mixed. Place pie plates on oven rack; pour pumpkin mixture into crusts and bake 15 minutes.
Turn oven to 350° and bake 35 minutes or until filling is set.
Cool.

title: pistachio cookies
directions: Stir the first 5 ingredients together.
Add the nuts and coconut and mix.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: stir-fried pepper steak
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
Roll in flour and drop in hot oil.
Brown on both sides.
Drain excess oil.
Add onion, pepper, tomato paste and water.
Bring to a boil and add vegetables.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: copper pennies
directions: Scrape carrots and cut into 1/4 inch diagonal slices.
Simmer carrots, green pepper, and onion in small amount of water.
Simmer until carrots are tender.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Stir to mix.
Refrigerate 2-3 days before serving.
Store in air tight container.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade and condensed milk together in a large mixing bowl.
Fold in 1 container of Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust; chill for 1 hour.
Top with other container of Cool Whip.
Chill for 1 more hour.
Garnish with lemon slices, lemon gumdrops, gummy bears, etc.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well in bowl and put rest of ingredients in.
Sift with a large spoon (do not use a mixer).
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: dirt pie(not to be mistaken with diet pie!)
directions: Pour milk into medium sized bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Stir in 1 cup cookie crumbs and rocks.
Spoon into pie crust.
Sprinkle with remaining cookies.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.

title: tomato-corn salad
directions: Add
drained corn to diced tomatoes.
Add green onions, pepper and
enough mayonnaise to hold it together.
Chill and serve in lettuce
cups
with
a
dollop of mayonnaise on top. Serves 4.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and place in casserole. Top with cracker crumbs. Melt butter and dribble over the crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add egg, sugar, shortening and flour.
Mix well and refrigerate for at least 2 to 4 hours.
Drop by spoonful into greased muffin tins (fill to about half full). Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: no egg chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add salad oil and vinegar, vanilla and cold water.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured, at 350° for 35 minutes or until done to touch.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients; spread in bottom of dish. Chop next 4 ingredients and lay on top.
Then top with 1 package taco cheese.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and form into small balls (walnut size).
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 425° about 10 minutes, until brown.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Soften margarine and add sugars and peanut butter.
Beat until creamy.
Add egg and mix well.
Add chips and mix again.
Add flour 1 cup at a time.
After 2 cups are added, add only enough flour to make dough form into a loose, creamy nonsticky ball. Dough should not stick to finger when you touch the dough.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Place stuffing mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour butter and hot water over dressing.
Saute celery and onion in 1 tablespoon butter.
Spread chicken or turkey, celery and onion over stuffing. Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over everything.
Spread mayonnaise over everything.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight. Remove 1 hour before baking, removing Saran Wrap.
Spread 1 can cream of chicken soup over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Put 4 tablespoons Wesson oil in one iron skillet and 4 in another.
Put beef in 1 and onions in other.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours. Cook 1 box spaghetti 20 minutes.
Put beef, onions, mushrooms, salt and pepper and tomatoes into skillet and simmer 1 hour, but do not boil.
When ready to serve mix with spaghetti and cover with grated cheese.
Place in oven until cheese melts.

title: betsy's hot spiced fruit
directions: Mix all of the ingredients with liquid in a large saucepan. Bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer one hour.
Try fixing in crock-pot.

title: a favorite low-cal vegetable soup
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart nonstick saucepan, combine onion, dry broth mix (do not add water at this stage) and garlic; cook stirring occasionally until onion is translucent.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to combine; cover and cook on low heat, stirring occasionally for about 10 minutes.
Add 2 cups of water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cover and cook until vegetables are soft, about 20 minutes.
Using a slotted spoon, remove about 1/2 cup vegetables from saucepan and set aside.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Combine strawberries and sugar; bring slowly to a boil, stirring occasionally until sugar dissolves.
Cook rapidly until thick, about 40 minutes.
As mixture thickens, stir frequently to prevent sticking.
Pour boiling hot into sterilized ball jars. Adjust caps.
Yield:
4 pints.

title: cheese dip
directions: Place cheese spread cubes in a 2-quart casserole dish. Microwave at 50% power for 3 to 6 minutes or until melted, stirring once.
Beat in beer and garlic with wire whisk until smooth.
Microwave at High until heated, about 1 minute.
Garnish with pimento and parsley.

title: gwen's fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, eggs and sugar.
Add apples and pecans.
Add flour and soda; stir well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Place in cold oven; set temperature at 325°.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Melt oleo.
Add all ingredients except broth.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Add broth and pour into greased casserole.
Cover tightly, bake 1 hour at 375°.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add and blend in eggs and vanilla. Gradually add dry ingredients.
Shave or chop up the Hershey bar. Bake for 12 minutes in a 375° oven.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.
These are really wonderful cookies.
They also ship well.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: In a large bowl combine flour, sugar and salt.
In a small bowl combine buttermilk and baking soda.
Immediately add to flour mixture.
Add eggs and mix well (mixture will be lumpy).
Lightly oil a skillet or griddle, heat at medium temperature.
Cook pancakes until lightly brown.
Serve immediately or keep warm in a 200° oven.
Makes approximately 12 to 16 pancakes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, onion and salt.
Spread on top of broccoli in baking dish.
Grate cheese over mixture and top with cracker crumbs.
Dot with oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: egg casserole
directions: Grease casserole (use a pretty large one).
Layer with croutons, cheeses, cooked sausage and onions.
Mix eggs, mustard, milk, mushroom soup and mushrooms (I season with some curry; it really adds a good flavor).
Pour over top and cover overnight. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until eggs are set.
Serves quite a few people.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and let stand in cold water overnight (ice may be used in water).
Pack cucumbers raw into clean canning jars. To each jar add alum, garlic, dill, hot peppers and 1 large or 2 small grape leaves.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump undrained crushed pineapple into greased 9 x 13-inch pan; spread over bottom.
Dump cherry pie filling over pineapple. Spread it around a little bit.
Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling.
Cut margarine into patties and place on top of mixture. Sprinkle nuts over margarine; do not mix the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until lightly browned.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix together 1/4 cup mix with 1 cup boiling water.

title: strawberry ice cream(uncooked)
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, vanilla and whipping cream in bowl.
Mix thoroughly with mixer.
Pour into ice cream freezer can.
Add Eagle Brand milk and fruit.
Stir well.
Add milk to fill line and stir well.
Freeze.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: fish or meat loaf
directions: Mix together.
Place in individual baking dish.
Sprinkle top of loaf with 1 tablespoon grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Counts as lunch protein, 1 bread and 2 ounces milk.

title: congealed vegetable salad
directions: Dissolve jello and gelatin in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup liquid from peas.
Add other ingredients and mold.
Chill.

title: egg rolls
directions: Create a flour paste by mixing 2 Tbsp. flour and 1 Tbsp. cold water.
In a skillet stir fry pork until brown.
With a slotted spoon remove pork from skillet, drain it and preserve 2 Tbsp of fat.
In preserved fat stir fry cabbage, bamboo shoots, mushrooms and onions.
In a small glass bowl mix together soy sauce, cornstarch, Five Spice powder, salt and sugar.
Sprinkle over vegetable mixture and stir fry for 1 minute.
Cool the vegetable and pork and mix them well.
Place 1/4 cup of the mixture on center of each egg roll skin.
Fold one corner of egg roll skin over filling so that the two opposite corners overlap.
Moisten the fourth corner with flour paste and fold over to make a roll. In a frying pan heat about 3 inches of oil.
Fry 3 egg rolls at a time until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve with Sweet and Sour Sauce and Hot Mustard Sauce.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt oleo in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over oleo.
Mix and press into pan.
Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over crumbs. Top evenly with remaining ingredients; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned in 350° oven.

title: zesty mozzarella chicken
directions: In a shallow bowl combine egg white and milk.
In another bowl combine breadcrumbs, Parmesan cheese and seasoning.
Dip each chicken breast in egg white mixture, then crumb mixture.
Melt butter and brown chicken until juice runs clear.
Meanwhile heat tomato sauce and basil.
When chicken is done, sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Serve with tomato basil sauce.

title: egg custard
directions: In
large
mixing
bowl
beat
3 egg yolks.
Add flour, sugar and
enough cold milk to make a paste.
Place remaining milk
and butter in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from stove	and pour
over egg mixture.
Add vanilla and pour into unbaked	pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, reduce heat to 375° until done.

title: diabetic pineapple pie
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a heavy pan and cook slowly until it thickens.
Pour into your pie shell and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 425°.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain sliced beets reserving liquid.
Pack into quart jars adding optional ingredients if desired.
In a saucepan combine vinegar and beet juice.
Bring to a boil then add: sugar, cloves, salt, peppercorns, and bay leaf.
Return to boil until well blended. Pour slightly cooled mixture over beets.
Add more juice to fill jar.
Chill and serve.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: glazed apricot nectar cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sugar, apricot nectar and salad oil in a large bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool on rack 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: baked pepper shrimp
directions: For each pound of shrimp, use 1/4 pound butter and 3 to 4 teaspoons pepper and juice of one lemon.
Place shrimp one layer deep in glass baking dish.
Evenly cover with pats of butter, pepper and lemon juice.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve in baking dish, letting each person remove shrimp shells; messy but delicious!

title: cheese ball
directions: Cut 2 packages dried beef into small pieces and add other ingredients.
Shape into two balls or one large ball.
Cut the third package of dried beef into small pieces and roll cheese ball until covered with beef.
Chill.

title: chocolate delight
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat together milk, sour cream and almond extract. Add pudding mix. Beat until smooth and creamy, about 2 minutes. Divide into serving dishes. Cover and chill. Top with whipped cream. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: seven-cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Serve on lettuce.

title: "your own" casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, blend soup and milk.
Stir in meat, noodles and vegetable.
If desired, season with a bit of finely minced onion or chopped parsley or 1/8 teaspoon thyme or sage.
Top with crumbs, cornflakes or stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, pudding, oil, eggs and sour cream; beat for 6 minutes.
Pour mixture into ungreased angel food cake pan. Mix together sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Reserve a small amount for topping.
Cut the remaining sugar/cinnamon mixture through the batter.
Sprinkle the reserve mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry sour cream mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-o in boiling water. Add strawberries, bananas & nuts. Pour 1/2 mixture into mold. Chill until set. Spread sour cream over top. Spoon the remaining mixture into mold. Chill.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine oleo and sugar until creamy.
Add pretzels.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch
pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: french silk pie
directions: Prepare and bake pie shell; cool.
In mixer bowl, cream margarine; add sugar slowly, beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 3 minutes after each addition.
Spoon into pie shell. Refrigerate.
Serve garnished with whipped cream and chocolate.

title: pork and mashed potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Heat oil in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat until hot.
Cook pork in oil about 6 minutes, until brown. Stir in carrots, celery, onion, mushrooms, broth, thyme, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Shake apple juice and flour in tightly covered container.
Gradually stir into pork mixture. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir one minute. Spoon mixture into 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Spoon mashed potatoes around edges and bake uncovered 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: brisket
directions: Sprinkle brisket with celery salt, garlic salt, lemon pepper and onion salt.
Center in a heavy piece of foil.
Sprinkle with liquid smoke.
Fold sides of foil over to seal in packet. Refrigerate overnight.
Six and one-half hours before serving, open foil and season with salt, pepper and Worcestershire.
Reseal and cook in a 300° oven for 5 hours.
Uncover and pour barbecue sauce over brisket.
Cook 1 more hour, uncovered.
You can also bake overnight at 200°.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese and French onion dip and spread on a large pizza pan.
Spread taco sauce on top of cream cheese mixture.
Brown meat; drain and add taco seasoning to meat.
Do not add water.
Sprinkle meat on top of mixture.
Dice tomatoes and shred lettuce on top of meat and then add the shredded cheese.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook white onion in oil until wilted.
Add green onion, green pepper and basil.
Cook until tender.
Add sausage, sliced thin, and brown.
Put beans, water, cooked veggies and meat in large pot. Add seasoning to taste (1 to 2 teaspoons cayenne, 1 to 2 tablespoons Cajun seasoning, depending on how warm you like your food).
Add salt to taste.
Bring to boil and cook on low for 4 hours or more.
Must frequently add water to cook beans down.

title: dutch oven chili rellenos casserole
directions: Brown
beef and onion in Dutch oven; drain grease.
Add seasoning.	Place chilies over ground beef, then cheese.
Beat the remaining
ingredients;
pour
over
chilies,
meat
and cheese. Place most of the heat on lid.
Cook until the top is firm. Check in about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a large Pyrex dish, then sprinkle with almonds and cheese.
If you do not want to use cheese you can use crushed potato chips.
Cook in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Break broccoli and cauliflower into small flowerets.
Slice pepper and onion fine.
Add pimento.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour over vegetables and marinate overnight.

title: short cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and sift twice.
Cut in butter and add milk gradually.
Put on floured board.
Roll and cut for individual servings.
Bake approximately 12 minutes in a hot oven. Split and spread with butter.
Any fruit, crushed, and sweetened may be placed between layers and on top.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: apricot-peach fluff
directions: Mix all together in mixing bowl.
Chill and enjoy!
(I prefer the apricot.)
Serves 10.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Scald 1 3/4 cups milk with chocolate and corn syrup in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt in a bowl.
Add 1/4 cup milk.
Add egg yolks and blend.
Quickly add mixture to scalded milk.
Stir until thickened.
Cover and cook 5 to 7 minutes (longer on low heat).
Add butter and vanilla; cool.
Pour into a 9-inch baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream or meringue.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla wafers and milk, nuts and coconut.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes in a greased angel food or Bundt pan.

title: essenhaus butterscotch pie
directions: In large saucepan, combine the butter, sugar and cream. Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In a small bowl, combine the cornstarch and the flour.
Add to the beaten eggs and blend.
Then stir in the milk.
Gradually add the egg mixture to the hot sugar mixture and continue cooking until mixture thickens and bubbles up in the center.
Do not use a whisk for stirring until the very end of the cooking time, for you don't want a lot of bubbles to form.
Add the salt and vanilla and allow mixture to stand 20 minutes without stirring.
Pour into the pie shells and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Top with sweetened whipped cream.
Yields 2 pies, approximately 16 servings.

title: sausage strata
directions: Layer bread, sausage, cheese, eggs and soup in a large oblong casserole.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: 3 week slaw
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, celery seed, salt and sugar.
Bring to a boil in a large bowl.
Combine all other ingredients.
Pour boiling mixture over cabbage.
Keeps 3 weeks.

title: italian tossed salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small pieces.
Slice onion into rings.
Toss first 4 ingredients together.
Pour Italian dressing onto salad and toss again.
Top with Parmesan cheese and croutons.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix potatoes and water in medium bowl.
Let stand until water is absorbed.
Mix in shortening, flour, baking powder and salt. Stir in milk as necessary to form a dough that may be patted to fit the filling.

title: lime pear jello salad
directions: Drain pears; add enough water to juice to make 2 cups.
Bring to boil and add jello and cream cheese.
Chill until partially set and whip.
Add whipped cream and pears.
Mix well and set.

title: gooey pecan pie bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together the flour, granulated sugar and salt.
Using a pastry blender, cut in 3/4 cup butter until the mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Press the mixture evenly into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 18 minutes or until lightly browned; set aside.

title: peanut heaven
directions: Crust:
Blend together flour, peanuts and butter; press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool.
Cream peanut butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Beat both puddings with milk and spread on top.
Cover with layer of Cool Whip and shred Hershey candy bar on top.
Sprinkle chopped peanuts on top, if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix water, butter and broccoli in skillet, boil for 3 minutes, remove from heat and add rice, Cheez Whiz and cream of celery soup.

title: pastry
directions: Sift flour and salt together. Mix in shortening, and add water a little at a time. Blend all together, roll out and use as desired.

title: extra good pie crust
directions: In large bowl, sift flour, sugar and salt.
Add shortening. Beat egg in a 1-cup measuring cup and finish filling with cold water.
You can use blender or knife, but works better to use your hands.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and set aside.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Add flour mixture.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°. Use tube pan.

title: very good cookies(heritage recipe)
directions: In bowl on medium speed mix the first 6 ingredients.
At low speed add flour, baking powder, soda, and salt.
Shape in 1 inch balls.
Roll in sugar and place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12-15 minutes.

title: mexican black-eyed peas
directions: Sort, wash and soak peas overnight.
Brown sausage.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Drain.
Drain peas well; stir in sausage and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add more water if necessary.

title: cream puffs
directions: Put water, butter and salt in saucepan and bring to a boil. Pour the flour into the ingredients and remove from fire and stir until dough does not stick on the sides of the pan, then add the eggs, one at a time, beat each time (by hand do not use the mixer). Drop on greased cookie sheet by a tablespoon heaped for each puff. Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes (but do not open oven door).

title: curry onion dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.

title: red hot cider
directions: Combine ingredients in large coffee pot.
Heat to serve. Stir often until red hots dissolve.

title: jello cheese cake
directions: Cream the butter and brown sugar.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix. Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Cool.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello in 2 cups of hot water; let jell.
Add drained, crushed pineapple.
Jell completely.

title: apple or cherry cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream sugar, oleo and eggs; blend well.
Alternately add sour cream and vanilla with combined flour, baking powder, soda and salt to the egg mixture; blend well.
Pour 1/2 the batter on the bottom of the pan.
Spread pie filling on top and then add the rest of the batter.
Mix together 1/2 stick oleo, 1/2 cup sugar, chopped nuts, 2 tablespoons flour and cinnamon like pie crust; refrigerate 10 minutes; then sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: hot seafood salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Pile lightly in casserole or individual baking dishes.
Sprinkle with cheese and chips.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° about 20 minutes or until mixture is heated and cheese is melted.

title: skillet pie
directions: Blend flour, eggs, sugar and margarine.
Add milk and vanilla and mix.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into a cold buttered iron skillet.
Bake in medium oven at 300°
for 30 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in pie comes out clean.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine zucchini, onions and salt; mix well.
Let set overnight.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain again.
Combine drained vegetables, vinegar, sugar, spices, cornstarch and pepper; mix well.
Bring to boiling; lower heat and simmer (uncovered) for 30 minutes or until desired consistency.
Stir occasionally.
Seal in jars.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 pints.

title: ranch taco chicken salad
directions: Cook and stir chicken in 1/4 cup of the salsa in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat 8 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.

title: delicious zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in salted water until tender. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Roll out on floured board, cut into strips.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes enough for large party.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and eggs; blend in sugar.
Add vanilla; blend well.
After mixing, pour into the pie crust.
Bake for 40 minutes or until the center is set at 350°.
It may depend on your stove. Myself, I like 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tuna quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Thaw pie crust as package directs. Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake on cookie sheet 5 minutes. Remove from oven.
Distribute tuna over bottom of pastry shell. Sprinkle cheese and onion over tuna.
Beat together eggs, milk, lemon juice and seasonings.
Pour over tuna mixture.
Bake on cookie sheet 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and bake an additional 12 to 15 minutes or until top is golden.
Serves 6.

title: frankfurters with rarebit
directions: Slice into franks 1/4-inch pieces.
Melt butter in saucepan. Add flour, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Add milk gradually, stirring until thickened.
Add tomatoes, stirring, then cheese. Stir until sauce is thickened and cheese melted.
Add salt and pepper and fold in franks.
Heat and pour over toasted buns (or rolls).

title: pauline's apple butter
directions: Cook applesauce and 1 cup sugar for 20 minutes on medium heat. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low to medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Pour into scalded jars and seal. Early transparents and Lodis make the best apple butter.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Wash cukes.
Soak whole cukes for 1 week in 1 pint of salt per gallon of water (approximately 2 gallons), enough to cover the cukes.
After 7 days, wash and cut in 1/4 lengthwise.
Soak overnight in alum and enough water to cover cukes.
Next, rinse and pour boiling water over them and let stand until cool.
Drain. Bring to a boil sugar and vinegar and 1 tablespoon spice per quart of vinegar.
Pour over cukes.
Let stand overnight.
Drain and heat vinegar and pour over again.
On third day, drain and heat.
Add cukes and heat.
Put in jars and seal.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Put alternate layers of beets, eggs and onions into a wide mouth jar; to beet juice, add vinegar, salt, sugar and pickling spice.
Boil 5 minutes and pour over eggs.
Add enough water to completely cover eggs.
Let stand a couple of days.
Will keep several weeks in refrigerator.

title: baked lasagne
directions: In a large skillet brown ground beef in oil.
Add garlic, onion, tomato paste, water and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: easy spanish meatballs
directions: Mix rice with ground chuck.
Add egg, salt and pepper.
Shape into small round balls.
Cook 40 minutes at 350°.
While baking, combine ketchup, mustard and brown sugar in a saucepan, then heat 20 minutes, stirring well.
When meatballs are done, cover with sauce and serve hot.

title: shrimp crab casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: Fill blender container to the top with vegetables.
Add cold water just to cover vegetables.
Cover container.
Follow blender instructions; run long enough to chop vegetables, about 3 to 4 seconds.
Pour mixture into strainer; drain thoroughly.
Repeat with remaining veggies.

title: onion squares corn bread
directions: Saute onion slices in a nonstick fry pan until soft and slightly browned.
Add yogurt, dill weed and salt.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder, oil, skim milk and egg white.
Mix well.
Add corn and Tabasco sauce.
Pour batter into a lightly vegetable sprayed 9-inch square pan.
Spread onion mixture over batter.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over onions. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 450°.
Cut into squares.
Makes 9 servings.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Put half the first 4 ingredients in a bowl.
Blend well and add evaporated milk, dates and pecans.
Mix together and spread in the bottom of a 10-inch pan.
Spread cranberries on top of oat mixture.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together and sprinkle evenly over the cranberries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Serve hot or cold.

title: fried fruit pies
directions: Soak dried fruit until soft.
Add some sugar and cinnamon to taste; cook on low until tender.
Let cool.
Roll out a biscuit into a round.
Put a heaping tablespoonful of filling on one half of pastry and fold over, crimping around open edges with a fork. (If you moisten inside of edges before crimping, it will hold together better.)
Fry in a skillet on medium with about 1 inch of oil until brown.
Drain on a paper towel.

title: layered tostado casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a skillet, brown beef and drain. Stir in beans, tomato sauce, taco seasoning and 1/2 cup water. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
In a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish, layer half of the taco shells, half of the meat mixture and half of the cheese.
Repeat the layers.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: s.e.g.r.a.'s sad cake
directions: Sift flour.
Measure and resift with baking powder and salt. Add eggs to brown sugar, one at a time, beating in well.
Add flour mixture gradually; mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla and nuts. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Let cool.
Cake will fall as it cools.
Cut in squares.
Top with whipped cream.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar, eggs and flavoring.
Blend in flour, baking powder and salt.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Cut into shapes.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Sprinkle with colored sugar or decorating candies.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes until very lightly browned.
May frost after baked if you did not add sugar.

title: orange-sauced chicken
directions: In medium skillet, cook chicken and onion in hot margarine over medium-high heat for 8 minutes, turning chicken to brown evenly.
In small bowl, stir together orange juice, sherry, brown sugar, parsley, orange peel, savory and mace.
Pour over chicken in skillet.

title: billy's favorite banana pudding
directions: Combine milk and water.
Add pudding mix and beat well.
Chill 5 minutes. Fold in whipped cream or topping. Spoon approximately 1/3 of this mixture into a 2 1/2-quart glass bowl.
Layer vanilla wafers, then bananas and pudding until ending with pudding mix. If you have extra Cool Whip or whipped cream, put this on top. Chill before serving.

title: spicy sugared nuts
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Mix egg white and nuts, stirring until all are coated and sticky.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together; sprinkle over the nuts, stirring until evenly coated.
Spread on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: no bake chocolate drop cookies
directions: Place sugar, milk and cocoa in large saucepan.
Bring ingredients to a slow boil.
Remove pan from heat and add remaining ingredients.
When cool, shape mixture into balls and place on waxed paper.
Cool in refrigerator for a few hours.

title: alabama chocolate pie
directions: Use a 3-quart saucepan.
Combine flour, cocoa, sugar, milk and eggs; mix well.
Cook until mixture is thick; remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Stir until butter melts. Return to stove.
Stir constantly for 2 minutes more.
Pour into cooled, baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: colonel sanders'-style kentucky fried chicken
directions: Wipe chicken dry.
Make a paste of the dressing mix, salt, butter, flour and lemon juice.
Brush to coat chicken evenly. Stack and refrigerate several hours.

title: homemade veg-beef soup
directions: Bring water to boil in large boiler.
Add beef bouillon and browned ground beef.
Bring to a light boil and add all the ingredients except for the macaroni.
Cook soup until all vegetables are done.
Add macaroni and cook approximately 10 minutes.
Enough soup to serve 8 hungry people.

title: spinach salad
directions: Remove stem from spinach; wash leaves thoroughly and pat dry. Tear into bite-size pieces.
Place spinach in a large bowl and set aside.

title: squash au gratin
directions: Cook squash in boiling water until just tender.
Drain very well.
Put in buttered casserole.
Saute onions in butter.
Stir in sour cream and cheese; cook just until cheese melts.
(Do not boil.)
Stir in oregano, salt and pepper.
Pour over squash. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and then paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stovetop meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pat out into heavy iron skillet. Place cover on pan. Cook on burner at simmer for 15 minutes. Turn over and cook 15 minutes on other side.

title: rapidrise french bread(makes two fat loaves)
directions: Reserve 3 cups white flour.
In large bowl, mix remaining flours, sugar, salt and yeast.
Stir hot water into flour mixture to form firm dough.
Mix in reserved flour as needed.
Knead until smooth and elastic, 8 to 10 minutes.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out to 10 x 15-inch rectangle.
Roll up, pinch edges and taper ends.
Place in French bread pan or on corn-mealed baking sheet.
Let rise to double, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: frosted braunschweiger roll
directions: Skin braunsweiger; mash with fork.
Beat in catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Place on waxed paper; shape into 9-inch long roll.
Refrigerate until firm.
Remove paper and place on tray.
Frost entire surface with cream cheese; thin cheese with small amount of milk, if necessary.
Sprinkle top with parsley and paprika.
Serve with cocktail crackers.

title: chili
directions: Mix together and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Smash shrimp with fork; mix with other ingredients and chill. This is great with crackers or chips.

title: dr. bowen's oatmeal cookies(adapted from the diabetic gourmet)
directions: On wax paper stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
In a medium saucepan or metal bowl over low heat melt the margarine. Off heat stir in the oats, sugar and vanilla.
In a small bowl beat the egg whites only until frothy; stir into the oats mixture. Stir in the flour mixture in 3 additions alternately with the milk, just until blended.
Stir in the raisins and nuts.
Drop by level tablespoonfuls a few inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven until lightly browned on undersides, 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: In a small mixing bowl, stir together softened cream cheese and peppermint extract.
Gradually add powdered sugar, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Knead the last of the powdered sugar with your hands.
Add food coloring.
Knead until food coloring is evenly distributed.

title: peppered meat marinade
directions: Dry the pork and paint it with mustard.
Coat it with brown sugar.
Saute the Mirepoix vegetables.
Brown the pork in oil. Sprinkle the baking pan (Dutch oven*) with the Mirepoix, then place the pork on top of it.
Pour heated bourbon into the pan and flambe it (carefully).
Add stock, then cover and cook at 350° for 30 minutes per pound.
An internal temperature of 145° to 155° should be reached.
Use a thermometer.
Remove from oven and place roast on platter to rest about 15 minutes prior to carving.
While resting, cover and keep it warm.
Strain liquid from pan and degrease it.
Reduce it slightly in saucepan, then whisk in the cornstarch to sauce consistency.
Season it to taste and add cognac and lemon juice to taste.
Carve roast; pour the sauce over it and pass remaining sauce.

title: golden chicken bake
directions: Arrange chicken in single layer (skin-side down) in shallow baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch).
Dribble butter or oleo over chicken.
Bake in a 400° oven 20 minutes.
Turn chicken; bake 20 minutes more.
Stir soup; pour over chicken. Sprinkle parsley on top.
Bake 20 minutes more.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Tear chicken into bite size pieces.
Place in bottom of ungreased casserole dish.
Pour vegetables over chicken.
Mix milk and soup; pour over vegetables.

title: jumbo oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream
together
the
butter,
peanut butter and sugars until smooth
and
creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; blend well. Sift
together
the flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir into
creamed mixture.
Blend in oats and raisins. Drop
by tablespoonfuls
onto
greased baking sheets, about 2 inches apart.
Bake
at
for 15 minutes, or until done. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine first four ingredients in Dutch oven or 1 large boiler.
Bring to boil; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 30 minutes. Stir in water and milk.
Heat thoroughly.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil macaroni until tender; chop onion and green pepper and saute in butter.
Pour boiling water over tuna to remove excess oil.
Break in pieces; place in a large casserole.
Add mushroom soup and sauteed onion and green pepper.
Drain macaroni and add. Stir in milk and seasoning.
Mix well.
Bake 50 minutes in a moderate 375° oven.

title: cake with blueberries-cherry
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, margarine or butter and eggs by hand until soft.
Divide in half.
Put one-half in refrigerator.
Spread dough into ungreased large pan and then pour pie filling over dough.
(Note:
Any pie filling flavor can be used.)
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar over filling. Take the rest of the dough and break over top of filling.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Lower oven temperature to 350° and continue to bake for 45 minutes (1 hour all together).

title: chicken pizzola
directions: Place cut up chicken, skin side up, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Slightly drain tomatoes and mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Turn and sprinkle 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Bake another 1 hour.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Blend butter, sugar and vanilla in bowl.
Add beaten eggs. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to egg; mix and blend well.
Spread in greased 8-inch pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: lemon pepper primavera
directions: Stir-fry vegetables in margarine until crisp-tender.
Stir Velveeta light cubes, milk and lemon peel in saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Pour Velveeta light mixture over pasta and vegetables.
Season with pepper as desired.
Makes 6 servings. Prep time:
10 minutes.
Cooking time: 15 minutes.

title: old-fashioned apple pie
directions: Blend sugar, salt and spices, lemon rind and butter.
Toss apples in mixture.
Arrange in pie crust.

title: ice cube punch
directions: Soak 1 envelope plain gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Dissolve 1 cup hot water and then add 2 cups sugar.
Have ready the pineapple juice, lemon juice and orange juice.
Add 3 cups cold water.
Pour into gelatin mixture.
Put into ice cube trays and freeze.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together.
Form balls the size of walnuts and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: ranch style salad
directions: Fix lettuce as for salad. Add tomatoes, cheese, onion and beans. Toss.
Pour dressing over salad and toss again.

title: banana cream dessert
directions: Cut margarine
into
flour
until
crumbly.
Add
nuts. Press in a 9
x
13-inch	pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool. Slice bananas over crust and arrange.
Mix cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Stir Cool Whip and pour over bananas. Follow pudding directions on box and pour over cheese mixture. Let set in refrigerator.
Spread
Cool
Whip	on and sprinkle with nuts.

title: partridge fillet
directions: Cut finer sized pieces of the partridge breast.
Melt butter and add the lemon juice.
Dip the partridge pieces in the butter mixture and spread out on a plate and let set for a few minutes. Roll the pieces in the bread crumbs.
Dip the pieces in the egg and roll in crumbs again.
Fry in fat until done, about 5 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Place sugar, cocoa, milk, and butter in medium saucepan. Bring to a boil over med-high heat.
When center starts to bubble, time 2 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, peanut butter, and vanilla.
Quickly mix together.
Pour into a buttered 9 X 13-inch pan.
Cool before cutting into squares.

title: garlic parmesan pasta
directions: In large skillet, melt butter.
Add basil, lemon juice, garlic powder and seasoned salt.
Blend well.
Add fettuccine, broccoli, walnuts and Parmesan cheese.
Toss to coat.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine together over low heat.
Add sugar and stir.
Add flour and mix.
Add beaten eggs and mix.
Add vanilla and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a greased and floured pan.
Cool and cut.

title: hamburger cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and onion together; add soup and water.
Stir.
Add rice and simmer for 5 minutes. Arrange cabbage in bottom of 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Add carrots and cheese on top.
Pour meat mixture over all.
Do not stir.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: ranch salad
directions: Marinate Ranch beans in French dressing, preferably overnight.
Prepare salad with lettuce and chopped tomatoes in a large bowl.
Pour beans over salad in an even layer.
Spread shredded cheese over beans in an even layer.
Right before serving layer crushed Fritos over salad.
Serve and enjoy!

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown the meat with taco seasoning.
Drain grease and spread in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Layer refried beans, picante sauce and cheese soup.
Bake at 350° in oven until cheese melts down into meat.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make cream sauce of butter, flour and milk.
Add sauce to spinach and cheese, and beaten egg yolks; mix. Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into mixture. Pour in buttered casserole.
Set in hot water.
Bake 30 minutes. Let stand a few minutes after removing from oven.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients together.
Add oatmeal and flour. Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes in 9-inch cake pans.

title: white bean soup
directions: Rinse and drain 2 of the cans of beans and put into a large soup pot. In a blender, pure the other 3 cans of beans with their liquid and add it to the soup pot. Then add the chicken broth, celery and onion soup mix and stir well. Cook on low heat 20 to 30 minutes. The longer this cooks, the thicker it gets. Add the liquid smoke just to flavor the cooked soup. Can use crock-pot on low for 2 to 3 hours. Serves 6.

title: marbled double chocolate cheesecake squares
directions: In small bowl, beat butter, 1/2 cup sugar and salt until smooth.
Stir together flour and cocoa.
Gradually add to butter mixture, beating until soft dough is formed.
Press dough onto bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan lined with foil.
`Beat cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
In separate bowl, mix 1 cup batter with topping, stirring until well blended.
Pour 1 cup topping flavored batter over dough.
Stir melted chocolate into remaining flavored batter; set aside.
Gently pour vanilla batter, 1/4 cup at a time, over flavored batter.

title: fried apples
directions: Wash and core apples.
Melt bacon drippings or desired fat in a heavy skillet and slice apple rings into melted fat.
Sprinkle sugar over apples and cover.
When thoroughly heated, lower flame and smother until tender.
It is usually advisable to turn the apples once or twice during the smothering.
Especially good with pork or ham as a side dish.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, white syrup and water.
Cook until thread.
Add peanuts and butter.
Cook until light brown, stirring continuously.
Don't scorch.
Add vanilla and soda.
Pour in a buttered pan.
Cool.
Break in pieces.

title: chocolate peanut cluster
directions: In double boiler, melt chocolate morsels.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk.
Remove from heat and stir in nuts and cereal.
Spoon teaspoons on wax paper.
Chill for 2 hours or until firm.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Beat cream cheese, sour cream and mayo until smooth.
Spread on 12-inch serving platter.
Cover with seafood sauce.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese, onion and tomatoes.
Cover and chill. Serve with crackers.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine, milk and pecans.
Press 1/2 of this mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes. While this bakes, melt caramels with a small amount of water or milk to make easier to spread.
Pour caramel mixture over baked portion of brownie mixture.
Pour chocolate chips over caramels. Sprinkle other 1/2 of brownie mixture over this and bake for 20 minutes.
Cut into squares and place on platter.

title: venison pot roast
directions: Immediately after deer is dressed, place meat in vinegar and salt water and soak overnight to remove strong taste or odors. Meat may then be frozen, if desired.
Salt, pepper and flour the roast.
Heat fat in a heavy skillet or roaster.
Brown roast on all sides in hot fat.
Add onions while browning.
Add water; cover tightly and cook slowly on top of range until tender. Add potatoes and carrots about 20 minutes before roast is done, if desired.
Yields 12 servings.

title: tangy green beans
directions: Wrap 7 or 8 beans in a half piece of bacon.
Secure with a toothpick.
Repeat with remaining beans.
Place in pan and broil until bacon is done.
Pour hot Vinaigrette Sauce over beans and serve.
This dish can be prepared the night before and broiled the next day.
Serves 8.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove mushroom stems. Chop stems and cook with onions in butter for a few minutes. Stir in ham, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and crumbs. Put stuffing in crowns and place in oven on foil lined cookie sheet until warm.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese and peanut butter until soft and fluffy. Add sugar; beat well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and top with chopped peanuts or shaved chocolate.
Chill 3 hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Sift together flour, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add dry ingredients to first mixture and beat until smooth.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in loaf pan that has been greased.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turkey rice soup
directions: Boil turkey legs in salt water until tender.
Remove the meat and add water to make 3 to 4 cups broth.
Bring to simmer with carrots, celery, onion and parsley.
Simmer 20 minutes. Add water, if needed, to make at least 1 quart liquid.
Add 1 cup Minute rice and meat from turkey legs.

title: squash casserole
directions: Stir all together squash, chicken soup, onion or onion flakes and egg.
Mix together margarine and dressing mix.
Put dressing into squash mixture and keep enough out to cover top.
Bake in a 2-quart dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and melted butter.
Add cornstarch and mix thoroughly.
Add egg yolks, flavoring and salt.
Add milk gradually.
Set on heat in double boiler.
Stir constantly until thick.
Remove from heat and add 1/3 cup of coconut.
Put in baked pie shell.
Use egg whites for meringue.
Sprinkle coconut on meringue and bake at 350° until brown.
Makes one 9-inch or two small pies.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: *Mash but do not add anything before measuring.
Drain 1
1/4 cups liquid.

title: chicken in sherry sauce(serves 4)
directions: Put flour, pepper, garlic salt, parsley flakes and tarragon on chicken breasts.
Saute breasts for a few minutes in oil to brown only.
Place in casserole dish with scallions, sherry and butter. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.
Baste twice during baking.

title: mock caesar salad
directions: Combine garlic and water in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until soft; drain.
Place garlic in a salad bowl; add salt.
Mash into a paste, using the back of a spoon.
Stir in vinegar and mustard with a wire whisk.
Add olive oil in a slow, steady stream, beating with a whisk until blended.
Add lettuce and gently toss. Sprinkle with cheese, pine nuts and pepper.

title: smooth and easy chocolate fudge
directions: Melt together in microwave the butter and chips until smooth. Remove and add the milk and nuts.
Pour into sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill until solid.

title: spicy pineapple zucchini bread
directions: With mixer beat eggs to blend.
Add cooking oil, sugar, and vanilla.
Beat until thick and foamy.
With spoon stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Combine remaining ingredients, then gently stir into mixture until blended.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice to add to jello.
Mix jello with boiling water and dissolve well.
Add reserved juice with water to make 2 cups liquid, and mix with jello.
Chill or set aside until liquid begins to thicken.
Add softened cream cheese broken into small pieces to jello and mix with electric mixer on low speed until thoroughly mixed.
Fold in drained pineapple and nuts.
Pour into chilled glass dish and refrigerate until congealed well.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix together.
This can also be used as a dessert with a graham cracker crust.

title: company meat balls
directions: Soak bread in milk. Mix all the ingredients. Shape into balls and fry or bake until brown. Place in baking dish and cover with 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 3/4 can water. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: lemon pie
directions: First, grate lemon rind, not the white part.
Add this to 1 cup water.
When it starts to boil, add cornstarch.
Stir until it thickens.
Put the egg yolks in a small bowl with a little of the hot mixture and stir quickly, then add to the rest of mixture. Keep stirring; add juice and butter.
Pour into baked pie shell and let cool.
Beat egg whites with 6 tablespoons sugar and use as topping.

title: butterscotch fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix together all ingredients except butter.
Melt butter.
Mix and pour into greased pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
While still warm, cut.

title: hog head cheese
directions: Have hog head thoroughly clean; cover with water in a large pot.
Bring to a boil; cook until meat will fall off bone.
Remove from the water; let cool until can be handled with hands.
Pick all the meat off the bones; discard bones.
Grind the meat with coarse blade, with a little of the fat.
Add black and red peppers, sage, salt and vinegar to taste.
Add green onions and chopped dried red pepper may be used for color.
Work well with hands, adding just a little of the liquid the head was boiled in.
Pour into a large crock bowl; cover with a plate and weigh it down with a smoothing iron.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Wash zucchini and slice. Saute zucchini and onion in butter; drain. Set aside. Brown about 1 pound of hamburger; drain off grease. Place zucchini and onion in baking dish. Then hamburger over that. Pour sauce on top of this. Sprinkle cheese over top. Bake at 350° until cheese melts, about 20 minutes.

title: strawberries candy
directions: Mix well.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Shape into strawberries. Roll in red colored sugar.
Dip ends in green colored sugar.

title: graham crax jello dessert
directions: Line bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan with graham crackers.

title: upside-down hershey peach cake(this is delicious with fresh peaches, pears or pineapple.)
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together in a bowl.
In #8 iron skillet, melt next 3 ingredients.
In skillet, arrange peach slices in sunburst, maraschino cherries and pecans.
In a bowl, blend the next 2 ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time, and then vanilla.
Beat alternately with sifted flour mixture and the buttermilk.
Put batter over peach mixture and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna salad
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Melt milk and cheese in crock-pot, stirring occasionally.
When melted, put in hamburger meat and picante sauce.
Serve with chips.
This recipe will serve 4 people.

title: soft pumpkin chip cookies
directions: Blend together pumpkin, egg, salad oil and sugar.
Sift and add to pumpkin mixture the baking powder, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Dissolve soda in milk and add to mixture.
Stir in chips, nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 370° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: In a small saucepan heat plum jelly and chilli sauce until jelly is melted.
Stir constantly.

title: easy zucchini bake
directions: Grease a
9-inch pie pan.
Heat oven to 400°.
Sprinkle vegetables	in
pan; top with cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth; pour over the vegetables.
Bake until knife inserted in	center	comes
out
clean,
at	400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: ghosts in the graveyard
directions: CRUSH chocolate sandwich cookies in large sealable plastic bag with rolling pin or food processor.
POUR milk into large bowl. Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes or until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Gently stir in 1/2 each of the whipped topping and crushed cookies.
Spoon into 13 X 9 inch dish; sprinkle with remaining crushed cookies.
REFRIGERATE 1 hour or until ready to serve.
DECORATE remaining cookies with assorted icings to resemble tombstones; stand up in top of dessert.
Add candies.
Drop remaining whipped topping by spoonfuls onto dessert to resemble ghosts.
Store leftover dessert in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal rocks
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients, adding only enough to make a stiff dough.
Drop onto greased tin, 1 inch apart.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool. Makes 3 layers.

title: wanda's best baked beans ever
directions: Drain beans some and combine all ingredients together in a large casserole or baking dish, topping with the bacon strips. Bake 1 hour at 350°, covered.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix and put in casserole.
Bake at 325° for about 50 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook each pudding separately using 2 cups fruit juice for each pudding (total of 4 cups; may add orange juice if you don't have enough juice to total 4 cups).
Cool pudding.
Add fruit.
If you use bananas, add just before serving.
Let stand several hours or overnight.

title: jambalaya mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in an airtight container in cool place.
Yields 1 1/4 cups dry mix.

title: shrimp italian
directions: Saute onion, celery and garlic in butter or olive oil in a large skillet until vegetables are tender. Add spaghetti sauce; rinse jar with 1/2 c. water and add to sauce mixture. Stir in worcestershire sauce and shrimp. Cover and cook over medium heat 6 to 8 minutes. Cook fettuccine according to package directions. Drain and place on a serving dish; spoon shrimp sauce over fettuccine. Serve immediately.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook, drain and mash potatoes.
