Melt butter; add sugar and cinnamon.
Add slightly beaten eggs to milk.
Mix all ingredients well and bake in a greased casserole dish at 400° for 30 minutes. Top with marshmallows and put back in oven until melted.
Serve.

title: chicken salad sandwich spread
directions: Let cheese soften at room temperature.
Add mayonnaise and blend with fork or rotary beater until mixture is smooth and fluffy.
Beat in lemon juice.
Add celery and chicken; toss lightly.
Chill before spreading.
Yields 3 cups.

title: corn bread
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Heat pan or greased iron until hot.
Fill irons for sticks 1/2 full.
Bake at 450° for about 10 minutes, or until done.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Pick shells from crab meat.
Place all ingredients in large bowl and toss lightly but thoroughly; do not break crab lumps. Form into 10 patties.
You can make them smaller.
Fry in deep fat at 360° until golden brown, about 8 minutes.
I also like to broil them.

title: iced tea
directions: Heat everything together
until
just
before it boils; remove from heat.
Pour into
jars
and put on lids and rings. Turn jars upside down so they will be sure to seal.
This is a concentrate so when you're ready to use it, add enough ice and water to make almost
a
gallon
of
iced
tea,
depending how strong you like it.
You can easily double the recipe.

title: reese's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg together. Add vanilla, peanut butter and flour. Mix together well. Roll into small balls. Cook in mini muffin pans at 350° for 10 minutes. When done, place a miniature Reese's peanut butter cup in the center. Let cool before you remove from pan. Will make about 3 dozen.

title: choc-oat-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat together margarine and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add combine flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: Melt butter.
Add pepper, onion and garlic; cook, but don't brown.
Blend in flour, curry, salt and sugar.
Add broth and milk; cook to thicken.
Add cut up chicken and 1 cup coconut. Heat all together and serve over steamed rice.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed.
Pour into dish and chill to set. Drain pineapple juice into cup.
Fill with water to make 1 cup liquid.
Beat egg.
Add sugar, flour and the 1 cup of juice mixture.
Cook in double boiler to form custard.
Cool.

title: thick beef vegetable stew
directions: Combine flour, pepper and salt on a large piece of wax paper. Dredge beef cubes well on all sides with flour mixture.
Reserve flour for thicker gravy.
Brown meat in oil in large Dutch oven, working in batches if necessary.
Remove meat.
Saute onions, green peppers, celery and garlic in pan drippings for 10 minutes. Add carrots, potatoes, turnip, rutabaga, beef broth, red-pepper seasoning, marjoram and savory.
Bring to a boil; add meat. Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender, adding broth to mixture if it becomes too dry.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix yeast in water (warm).
Melt butter and cream with sugar and eggs with mixer.
Add flour.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 350° for 15 minutes.
May be stored in refrigerator several days before using.

title: vegetable lentil soup
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving:
Dice carrots, celery and onion.
Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch pieces; mince garlic.
In a 5-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat, in hot olive or salad oil, cook carrots, celery and onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add garlic and cook, stirring, just until garlic begins to brown.

title: mrs. cullen's squash souffle
directions: Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: winning barbecue ribs
directions: You will need a smoker cooker and a plant mister.

title: no crust peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in glass baking dish; set aside. Sift baking powder, flour and sugar in a bowl. Add milk and mix well. Pour this in baking dish with butter, then add peaches. The batter will rise to cover peaches. Bake at 300° until golden brown.

title: noodles fettucini
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package and drain.

title: chilaquiles(tortilla chips with cheese and salsa)
directions: In a skillet with 3/4-inch hot oil, fry the tortilla pieces in batches until golden. This will happen fast, so have tongs ready. Drain on paper towels.
Spread the pieces in a shallow baking pan or pie tin.
Top each with cheese and salsa. Put them under the broiler until cheese is melted.
Makes a great snack.
Excellent with a bowl of good soup.
As an appetizer, top the crisp tortillas with only the cheese and dip them in the salsa.

title: bean dip
directions: Layer in the following manner:
Spread a can of bean dip over the bottom of a glass pie plate.
Add a pint of sour cream.
Add green onions, tomatoes and olives in layers.
Top with shredded cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add mixed vegetables and undiluted soup.
Put grated cheese on top.
Top with crumbled Tater Tots. Heat in oven until Tater Tots are done.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Soak peas overnight and rinse.
Cover with water and cook 30 minutes.
Drain; cover with water and cook 30 minutes more or until tender as you like it.
Drain well.
Mix with remaining ingredients and chill overnight.
Serves 4.

title: martha's marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve vinegar. Let cool. Drain vegetables and combine. Stir in the vegetable mixture; cover and place in refrigerator 12 hours prior to serving or overnight. Stir occasionally.

title: spice cake with apples dessert
directions: Mix with pastry blender.
Cut margarine into cake mix until crumbly and about the consistency of corn meal.
Grease square baking dish and pour in apples from the can.
Top with cake mix and margarine mixture.
(Nuts can be sprinkled on top.)
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with Cool Whip or ice cream. Easy.
Serves 4 (can be readily doubled).

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix above ingredients together and put in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown. Cut in squares.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and cornstarch.
Put in casserole.
Top with crackers, cheese and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Use with meal or as dessert.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and spoon into greased muffin tins, 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° approximately 20 minutes. Ice with cream cheese frosting.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Melt margarine and blend into cake mix in bowl.
Pat mixture into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut up peaches and spread over the cake mixture.
Mix 1 pint sour cream and 1 beaten egg. Mix sour cream and beaten egg; pour over peaches.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Refrigerate after cool.

title: southern lemon pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add flour, beaten eggs, juice and grated lemon rind.
Pour mixture into unbaked pastry shell and cook in preheated 325° oven for about 45 minutes or until filling is set.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Cream together oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 3 cake pans and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chinese barbecued pork
directions: Combine ingredients in mixing bowl.
Slice pork butt in strips, about 1 1/2-inches wide.
Marinate pork for at least 3 hours in sauce, turning frequently.
Drain pork and place on rack and bake in hot oven at 400° for 60 minutes, basting and turning every 15 minutes to brown evenly.
Slice into 1/4-inch thickness and serve with hot mustard and soy sauce.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle with apple pie spice.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: lemon bundt cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes in Bundt pan. Cool. Put on plate.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Heat until sugar dissolves. Marinate chicken for 24 hours.

title: graham cracker sandwiches
directions: Lay graham crackers on cookie sheet.
Blend melted margarine, sugar, egg and milk and bring to boil.
Add coconut, chopped pecans and graham cracker crumbs.
Mix well.
Spread over crackers and place another cracker on top to make sandwiches.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: After mixing well, pour into greased and floured loaf pans, Bundt pans or coffee cans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: banana pudding
directions: Line bananas and wafers in bowl.
Mix pudding in milk, add sour cream.
Do not let it get real thick.
Pour over wafers and bananas.
Cover with whipped topping.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix all ingredients in a small bowl with an electric mixer. You can successfully cut to half the sugar with good results.

title: diabetic no roll pie crust
directions: Mix cake mix and water together until batter is smooth, about 3 minutes.
Lightly spray bottom and sides of 2 (9-inch) round pie pans with nonfat vegetable oil.
Using a spatula, spread batter to coat bottom and sides of pans.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: tostada dip and chips(food processor recipe)
directions: Place the grating disc in food processor.
Grate both cheeses. Set aside.
Place slicing disc in food processor.
Slice green onions (use light pressure so very thin).
Set aside.
Place metal blade in food processor.
Place beans, taco mix and green chiles in work bowl.
Process until thoroughly mixed.
Scrape sides of the bowl.
Using cutting board and knife, cut the tomatoes and slice the avocados.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Shape into loaf.
Place in a loaf casserole dish or baking pan.
Top with topping.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes. Drain off fat.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: fruit flautas
directions: Spread each tortilla with 2 tablespoons peanut butter.
Spread 1 tablespoon preserves across one end of each tortilla.
Roll up. Heat oil (1-inch deep) in a 10-inch skillet to 350°.
Fry 2 to 3 roll-ups at a time, seam side down, until golden brown.
Turn once, about 1 1/2 minutes.
Drain; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve warm with ice cream.
Makes approximately 10 servings.

title: refrigerator fruit pie
directions: Mix flour, pecans, brown sugar and margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 400° (glass pan 375°). Cool completely and then refrigerate to get cold.
Soften cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix.
Prepare Dream Whip according to directions on package.
Blend cream mixture with Dream Whip and pour over crust.
Chill.
Lightly spoon pie filling over pie.
Chill at least 12 hours.

title: garlic grits
directions: Cook grits soupy and cook for about 20 minutes.
Combine other ingredients.
(Add enough milk to make mixture soft.)
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 people. (Very good with fish.)

title: beef-rice creole
directions: Cook and stir ground beef in skillet until light brown; drain. Sprinkle beef with flour and salt.
Stir in green pepper, onion, parsley, pepper, pepper sauce, garlic and thyme.
Cook and stir over low heat until onion is tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir water and tomatoes (with liquid) into beef mixture.
Break up tomatoes with fork.

title: mud pie
directions: Mix pudding with milk according to package directions.
Add vanilla and cream cheese and blend well.
Fold in Cool Whip. Place 1/3 of cookie crumbs in pan.
Top with half of pudding. Sprinkle another third of crumbs, then add layer of pudding.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: turkey piccata
directions: Combine bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Dredge turkey breast slices with crumb mixture.
Heat oil and butter in a skillet large enough to hold turkey slices in 1 layer.
Add garlic.
Add turkey. Cook about 3 minutes or until brown and cooked.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Set aside.
Measure and combine remaining 6 ingredients. Stir until it boils and then add sugar and cornstarch.
Use 4 egg whites for meringue.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar for each egg white and a pinch of cream of tartar.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a 10-inch skillet, saute zucchini and onion in margarine until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In a large bowl, blend eggs and cheese. Stir in vegetable mixture.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter; slowly beat in sugar and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat briskly.
Blend entire mixture.
Pour into shell. Bake 10 minutes at 450°; reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes.

title: reduced fat meat loaf
directions: Combine egg substitute and milk; stir in oatmeal, onion, parsley, salt, sage and pepper.
Add ground beef.
Mix well.
Pat into 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Spoon off excess fat.
Combine catsup, brown sugar and dry mustard.
Spread over meat loaf.
Return to oven for 10 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Thaw dough and let rise.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Punch dough down.
On lightly floured surface, roll out dough to 12 x 15 inches.
Melt margarine over low heat.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon.
Stir well and add nuts.
Spread mixture over dough.
Start with 15-inch side and roll up.
Pinch edge to seal. Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Place in pan.
Excess brown sugar mixture may be poured on top of each roll.
Let rise in warm place approximately 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bakes 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding crabmeat last. Put in baking dish and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: paprika chicken
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Mix next four ingredients.
Place chicken in an ovenproof dish.
Pour mixture over.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until chicken is browned.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: white icing
directions: Place water, syrup, sugar, cream of tartar and salt in a saucepan.
Stir over heat until the sugar is completely dissolved. Put egg white in bowl.
Turn speed control to highest number and beat until frothy, about 1/2 minute.
Pour the hot syrup gradually into the bowl in a fine stream, 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and continue whipping 5 1/2 or 6 minutes or until icing loses its shiny appearance and will stand in stiff peaks, approximately 8 to 9 minutes mixing time.
Makes frosting for tops and sides of two 8-inch layers.
This makes a soft icing.

title: country coleslaw
directions: Shred the cabbage.
Sprinkle generously with salt; cover with water.
Let stand several hours.
Drain water; add next 5 ingredients.
Mix well; let stand several more hours.
Drain again; refrigerate until ready to serve.
Just before serving, add carrots and mayonnaise.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: top ramen crunch cabbage salad
directions: The night before, mix together vinegar, salad oil, sugar and flavoring packets from Top Ramen.
Mix well and refrigerate. Shake anytime you open the door.
Shred together in large bowl cabbages and carrot.
Add onions.
Place in refrigerator to cool (a big time saver tip is to use one 16-ounce package cole slaw mix in place of cabbage and carrot).
In a small bowl place almonds, sunflower seeds and Top Ramen noodles (broken up).
When ready to serve, toss all together.

title: easy holiday congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Add cranberry sauce and mix well.
Cool a little more.
Add nuts and sour cream.
Blend, but not completely, so that sour cream is streaked.

title: stuffed cabbage leaves
directions: Parboil cabbage leaves.
Brown ground beef and chopped onions in 2 tablespoons of the butter.
Add salt and pepper, half the tomato paste and cinnamon.
Add water and rice; simmer until rice is partially done.
Stuff cabbage leaves as follows:
Remove thick stem portions.
Cut large leaves in half.
Place 2 tablespoons of filling on underside of leaf.
Starting at base, fold over and fold in sides, rolling tightly toward point.
Cover bottom of a greased casserole with cabbage leaves.
Place rolls in layers; cover with inverted plate.
Add remaining tomato paste diluted with enough boiling water to cover rim of plate.
Dot with remaining butter. Cover and simmer for 2 hours or until done.
Serve with lemon slices.
Serves 6.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Mix Raisin Bran, sugar, flour, soda, spice and salt in a very large bowl.
Add eggs, shortening, vanilla and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Store in a covered container in refrigerator and use as desired.

title: chocolate cherry upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine cold water and cornstarch.
Stir in pie filling; blend well.
Spread evenly on bottom of ungreased 9-inch square baking pan.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Beat with spoon or wire whisk until batter is smooth and well blended.
Pour evenly over cherries.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; invert onto serving plate.
Serve warm.

title: 3-cheese zucchini parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine first 5 ingredients in food processor.
Set aside 2/3 cup of mixture for topping.
Dip zucchini in two egg whites; coat with mixture and place on baking sheets sprayed with olive oil.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: uncooked chocolate fudge
directions: Measure sugar, eggs and vanilla into a large bowl.
Melt chocolate and shortening in top of double boiler.
Add to other ingredients.
Beat at high speed for 4 minutes.
Stop beating and add nuts.
Beat at same speed for 1 minute.
Drop by spoon on cookie sheet.

title: sweet and sour sausage balls
directions: Shape sausage into balls; cook until done and drain well on paper towel.
Pour off grease; return to skillet.
Add remaining ingredients except pineapple.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Just before serving, stick each ball with pineapple on toothpick.

title: hot dog sandwiches
directions: Mix together hot dogs, eggs, cheese, olives and onion.
Add mayonnaise and chili sauce.
Spread the mixture amply on 18 hot dog buns.
Wrap each in foil and freeze.
When ready to use, bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flour.
Add corn, salt and milk.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Put ingredients in large pan and add enough flour to make a rather thick batter.
Be sure it isn't too hot for the yeast.
Beat well with electric mixer.
It makes a finer texture.
Let rise for about an hour away from drafts or until light.
Stiffen with enough white flour to make a soft dough.
Let rise for an hour.

title: souper good roast
directions: Season beef roast to taste with garlic salt and pepper.
Place roast on a sheet of aluminum foil large enough to completely wrap it.
On top of roast, sprinkle soup mix.
On top of this, spread evenly the mushroom soup.
Wrap and fold the foil to seal around the roast.
Place in a pan and bake in slow oven, about 250°, for 8 to 10 hours.
Potatoes and carrots may be added around the roast before it is wrapped and sealed.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Mix all ingredients together except powdered sugar.
Do not use mixer.
Roll into little balls and then flatten out.
Bake for 10 minutes on 350°.
Let cool to harden.
Shake in bowl of powdered sugar.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Follow directions on soup can.
Add Cheez Whiz and half and half.
Heat, stirring constantly, until Cheez Whiz is melted.
Add frozen broccoli; cook over low heat for approximately 10 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: overnight bloody marys
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Cover and chill overnight.
Stir in vodka just before serving.
Serve over crushed ice. Yields 15 1/2 cups.

title: marinated mushrooms and vegetables
directions: In saucepan, combine the vinegar, oil, onion, garlic, 1 teaspoon salt, sugar, basil, oregano and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Bring to boiling.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Mix Oreos and margarine together.
Reserve 1/4 cup for topping.
Press remaining Oreo mixture into a 9-inch pie plate.

title: best bran muffins
directions: Combine bran and milk.
Let stand several minutes.
Add egg and oil; beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir until combined. Pour into 12 muffin pan cups (greased or with cupcake papers). Bake at 400°
for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: moist and creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed, making 2 layers.
Cook as directed on box.
While cake is cooling, boil milk, sugar and 1/2 cup coconut. Place one layer on plate, punch holes with a utility fork all over cake.
Spoon milk mixture over top.
While this cools, stir in remainder of coconut into Cool Whip.
Frost cooled layer, put on second layer and repeat.
After cake is covered and iced, place in airtight container and store in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: zucchini custard(microwave)
directions: Place zucchini in round casserole.
Cover and cook on High for 3 minutes.
Combine beaten eggs with cheese.
Blend well.
Pour over zucchini. Cover and cook 8 minutes on Medium.
Place onion rings on top.
Heat, uncovered, 1 minute on High.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with crust. Add chicken, soup, vegetables and liquid.
Cover with pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Pour into 3 cake pans.
Bake at 350° until cake leaves sides of pan.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients; spread into pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: *Veal can be substituted for chicken patties.

title: butter pecan picnic bars
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, allspice and salt.
Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in molasses until well blended.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour mixture and applesauce alternately to creamed mixture, beating until just blended after each addition.
Stir in nuts and butterscotch chips. Pour in greased and lightly floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until firm to touch; cool on rack. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: easy goulash
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until done!

title: crescent roll vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on a greased jelly roll pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Spread cream cheese mixture on top.
Top with finely chopped vegetables.
Use any or all:
broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, chopped olives, red bell pepper and radish.
Lasts 2 or 3 days in refrigerator.
Good as an appetizer or finger sandwich.

title: old fashioned holiday turkey
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Clean and wash the turkey.
Place in roasting pan.
Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle the Sunday Finest seasonings on the turkey, inside and out.
Use the whole bottle (3.3 ounces).
Can be found at all supermarkets.
Add water to bottom of pan.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° about 6 hours.

title: tortilla dessert cups
directions: In a small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon. Coat one side of each tortilla with nonstick cooking spray; sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar. Turn tortillas over; repeat on the other side. Cut each tortilla into 4 wedges.

title: waldorf astoria(red velvet cake)
directions: Sift flour, salt and cocoa.
Cream together shortening. Add sugar gradually and cream
until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour alternately, with sour cream. Beat until smooth.
Add flavoring and food coloring.
Dissolve baking soda in vinegar and
fold
into
mixture.
Bake
in two 9-inch greased pans or one 13
x
9-inch
pan.
Bake
30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream cookies
directions: Mix flour and oleo.
Add ice cream.
Divide into 8 parts. Chill.
Roll out in powdered sugar to about 1/4 inch thick.
Cut into 12 squares.
Spread a teaspoon of filling on each (apricot, nut, thick jams).
Press 2 opposite corners together.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: strawberry chiffon squares
directions: In a small pan, melt butter and stir in cookie crumbs.
Pat firmly in bottom of 12 x 7-inch pan.
Chill.
In large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk and undrained strawberries.
Fold in marshmallows and whipped cream.
Pour into pan.
Chill 2 hours or until set.
Garnish with extra whipped cream or strawberries.
Makes 18 bars.

title: old fashion egg salad
directions: Blend together mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion, salt and pepper.
Reserve 4 center egg slices for garnish.
Chop remaining eggs.
Stir chopped eggs and celery into mayonnaise mixture. Cover and refrigerate to blend flavors.
For each serving, spoon about 1/2 cup of egg salad into a lettuce-lined dish.
Garnish with reserved egg slice and celery leaves.

title: ten minute microwave fudge
directions: In microwavable bowl, mix sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla.
Blend in nuts.
Place stick of butter on top of mixture. Microwave on high for 2 minutes.
Remove and beat until smooth. Pour into 8 x 8 x 3 pan lined with wax paper.
Refrigerate until hard.

title: all night coffee cake
directions: Spray Pam in Bundt pan. Sprinkle the pecans in bottom of pan. Put the frozen dinner rolls on top of the pecans.
Sprinkle the dry pudding over the rolls.
Pour the melted butter over the pudding and top with the brown sugar.
Put wax paper and tea towel over it to rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes and you have a hot delicious coffee cake for breakfast or brunch.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Beat together with electric mixer cream cheese, sugar and vanilla or almond exract until smooth, then fold in Cool Whip. Spoon mixture into crust and chill for 3 hours.
Top with canned fruit, if desired.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes; cover with water.
Add salt, pepper, onions, carrots and celery.
Boil until tender.
Add milk, bring to low boil and thicken with cornstarch mixture.
Stir constantly while it thickens.

title: cucumber spread
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: rice-a-roni salad
directions: Mix ingredients with cooked rice.
Chill.
If more moisture is needed in salad, you can use chicken bouillon dissolved in hot water.
Use only enough to supplement dressing.

title: baked shrimp
directions: Arrange shrimp in shallow baking dish.
Put other ingredients over shrimp.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Stir and continue cooking for another 15 minutes.
Great with oven roasted potatoes, salad and hot garlic bread.

title: pineapple glaze for baked ham
directions: Mix all ingredients and spoon over ham the last 30 minutes of baking time.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: master mix muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg and milk or water and mix until just moistened.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute broccoli and onion together with margarine.
Add soup, milk, cheese, and pepper.
Cook on medium low until broccoli is tender and cheese is melted, approximately 30 to 45 minutes.
Stir often.
Makes approximately 6 quarts.

title: chocolate-covered cherry cake
directions: Place rack in center of the oven and preheat to 350°.
Lightly mist a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with vegetable oil spray.
Set pan aside.

title: no peek stew
directions: Lightly
salt and pepper meat and vegetables.
Place in casserole
in layers.
Combine 1 cup tomato juice, salt, sugar and tapioca.
Mix
well
and
pour
over meat and vegetables. Bake, covered, for 5 hours at 250°.
No fair peeking!

title: mexican corn bread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients; add the dry ingredients and stir only until moistened. Pour into greased 9-inch square pan or 10-inch skillet.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients with spoon.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until play dough becomes solid.
Turn onto floured surface and knead.
Store in airtight container.

title: jamica cake
directions: Oil and flour a pan (tube or oblong).
Mix all ingredients very well.
Bake until golden brown.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Can be served without icing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Saute poppy seed (optional), onion, mustard and Worcestershire sauce in melted margarine.
Spread a teaspoon of the mixture on each bun, then put chipped ham and grated cheese on top.
Wrap in foil, heat 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix and set a few hours in refrigerator.

title: paprika chicken
directions: Heat shortening until hot in a Dutch oven.
Add onion and saute until glossy and stir in paprika.
Cook chicken over high heat, stirring pieces with a fork, until it turns a reddish-golden color.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper.
Pour in bouillon cube, dissolved in 1 cup hot water.
Cover and cook slowly 25 minutes or until tender.

title: dilled yogurt dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Good for salad dressing, veggie, cracker or chip dip.

title: sweet n sour chicken
directions: Place chicken parts in casserole dish.
Mix dressing, preserves and soup mix and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix dry ingredients into Cool Whip.
Add sherry to taste. Great for entertaining.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries and orange on coarse grind setting.
Add sugar substitute and mix.
Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water.
Set jello until thick.
Mix in ground cranberry-orange mixture.
Mold in 6-cup bowl, loaf pan or jello mold until set.
Serves 8.

title: angels on horse backs
directions: On 1/2 a slice of bacon place oyster and slice of water chestnuts. Roll up and secure with toothpicks. Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Heat soup and milk in a saucepan until hot. Remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour mixture into an 11 x 7-inch pan and cover with foil. Bake 45 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut pepper in half, remove seeds and pulp.
If using small peppers, cut off and scoop out centers. Wash.
Wash rice and mix all ingredients except tomato sauce.
Fill peppers loosely with the meat mixture.
Place in Dutch oven, pour tomato sauce on top enough to cover peppers.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat over medium heat.

title: honeydew-walnut salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, toss together the honeydew, walnuts, parsley, celery and red pepper.
Whisk together the remaining ingredients and pour over the salad.
Toss to coat.
Serve at once or chill and serve.

title: mom's baked chili
directions: Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes in covered Dutch oven or similar pan.

title: crab and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, 2 cups Cheddar cheese, crab and onion in baking dish.
Beat biscuit mix, eggs, milk, salt and pepper and pour over crab mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in 400° oven.
Top with remaining 1 cup cheese.
Return to oven until cheese is melted and mixture is fairly firm to touch (about 10 minutes).
Makes good luncheon meal.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil to hard crack stage the raw peanuts, sugar, white syrup, water and salt.
Quickly add soda, stirring only until dissolved. Be careful not to disturb air bubbles.
Pour onto slightly greased pan, about 11 x 16-inch.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Check.
I sometimes need more time.
Glaze when hot.

title: yo mezzatti
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add soup, sauce, celery, green pepper and onion.
Simmer at least 1 hour.
Cook noodles; drain.
In casserole, put layer of noodles, layer of meat sauce and layer of cheese slices.
Repeat (end with cheese on top).
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
This can be made ahead and frozen.

title: sparkling punch
directions: Make ice ring out of juice, if desired.

title: creamy orange dessert
directions: Mix gelatin and water in microwave bowl.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add marshmallows.
Microwave 1 1/2 to 2 minutes more.
Stir mixture slowly until marshmallows are melted and mixture is smooth.
Add ice cream.
Stir with wire whisk until melted.
Stir in oranges.
Pour into 6-cup ring mold.
Refrigerate for 45 minutes before serving.

title: easy clam chowder
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
For a richer tasting soup, use the half and half.
For not so rich, use 2% milk.
For the health conscious, use skim milk.

title: barbecues
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until done.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients except celery.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Put on buns and top with about 1 teaspoon of chopped celery.

title: mom's custard
directions: Mix ingredients.
Butter custard cups (6).
Optional: Raisins and pieces of bread may be put in cups.
Pour mixture in cups and top with a dusting of nutmeg.
Put cups in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with a small amount of water in bottom of pan.
Bake 1 hour at 375° or until a knife comes out of custard clean.

title: pumpkin pudding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl, about 2 minutes on medium speed.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over top (yellow or white).
Press down with back of spoon.
Melt 1 stick oleo.
Dribble over top of dry cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crab mold
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Place in mold. Refrigerate.
Unmold onto dish.
Serve with crackers as an appetizer.

title: mama's sweet potato pie
directions: Mash sweet potatoes while hot, add next five ingredients and blend well.
Add milk.
Pour into two 9-inch pie shells and bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: fried rice with beef and green peppers
directions: Combine beef, 1 tablespoon soy sauce, cornstarch and sugar and let stand 10 minutes.
Saute onions in 2 tablespoons oil for 3 minutes.
Add green pepper; saute 1 minute.
Add meat and marinade, chicken broth and remaining soy sauce.
Saute 1 minute.
Transfer meat to large bowl.
Heat remaining 4 tablespoons oil in skillet. Add rice and stir-fry 3 minutes.
Return meat to skillet; add green onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Serve immediately.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Blend well and pour in greased casserole.

title: cheese pecan wafers
directions: In food processor, process together cheese and butter until smooth and creamy. Add flour, pecans, salt and cayenne. Process until thoroughly mixed.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add egg, flour and other ingredients.
Mix together well and chill in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Roll out dough into 3/16-inch thickness on a lightly floured, cloth covered board.
Cut into shapes.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: shrimp, tomato, okra and sausage
directions: Fry okra until no longer slimy.
Saute celery, onion and bell pepper together until tender.
Add tomatoes, along with one can of water.
Let boil for 15 minutes.
Add sausage and okra.
Let cook 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook 5 more minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: diet chili
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, heat oil.
Add onions and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until softened, about 5 minutes.
Add salsa, beans and tomato juice; stir to combine. Reduce heat to low and let simmer until flavors blend, 20 to 25 minutes.
Add steak and pepper and stir to combine.
Cook until steak is heated through, about 10 minutes.
Store 3/4 cup servings of chili in resealable freezer bags for up to 1 month.
Each 3/4 cup serving provides 1/2 fat, 2 proteins and 1 1/2 vegetables.

title: chili sauce
directions: Blanch tomatoes; peel.
Add thoroughly chopped onions, celery and peppers.
Add 1 cup sugar, salt, vinegar and allspice.
Cook in a large kettle until tender on top of stove.
Fill sterilized Mason jars 1/4 inch from lip.
Process in water bath.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Stir in eggs and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly. Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Ice muffins while still hot.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Put hen
in large Dutch oven with enough water to make 1 gallon of broth.
Cook until well done.
Remove chicken and set broth aside.
Debone chicken.
Add all ingredients except biscuits back into the broth.
Take each biscuit and pinch off small pieces until all 10 biscuits are used.
Simmer on medium heat about 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken, save 1 quart of broth.
Pour chicken soup in 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Take chicken off bones and lay on top of soup.
Sprinkle stuffing on top.
Pour 1 quart broth over stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peach sauce
directions: Combine peaches and water in large saucepan; cook over medium heat 5 minutes.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 minutes or until tender.
Cool.
Combine peaches and remaining ingredients in container of electric blender.
Process until smooth; chill. Serve over ice cream.
Yields 3 cups.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Put 1 tablespoon cooking oil in skillet; brown ground meat, onion, salt and pepper.
While meat and onion are browning, mix rest of ingredients in bowl; then when meat and onion are browned, mix all ingredients.
Heat thoroughly and serve on toasted bun. Makes about 15 hamburgers.
Ideal for childrens' or adults' party. Can also be served family style on rice or noodles.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta until tender and drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill for 1 hour.

title: choconut caramel bars
directions: Melt chips and shortening in top of double boiler.
Pour half into a 9-inch pan. Refrigerate about 15 minutes.
Melt caramels, butter and water.
Mix in nuts.
Pour over hardened chocolate and chill about 10 minutes.
Pour remaining chocolate over caramel mixture and return to refrigerator until hard (about 30 minutes).

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and blend in milk.
Add flour, soda and cinnamon, beating until smooth.
Fold in fruit, nuts and coconut (which has been tossed in flour).
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: trawler's crab dip
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: homemade barbecue sauce(not spicy hot)
directions: Mix all ingredients in pot and bring to a boil.
Let simmer 15 minutes.
Use immediately on meat or store in refrigerator for later use.

title: pear relish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 minutes. Seal in hot, sterilized jars.

title: crescent cream cheese squares
directions: Spread half the roll dough in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, cream cheese and egg yolk in bowl.
Spread over dough.
Top with remaining dough. Brush with egg white.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar. Bake for 15 minutes.
Cool in pan. Chill until serving time.
Cut into squares. Makes 15 squares.

title: roasted chicken with sausage and potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Arrange chicken, sausage and potatoes in roasting pan.
Combine oil and seasonings in small cup.
Pour over chicken, sausage and potatoes and toss gently to coat.
Cover. Bake at 425° for 1 hour.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Uncover and bake until browned, 30 to 40 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: brownies deluxe
directions: Mix oil,
sugar
and
vanilla together with a spoon (no mixer). Add
eggs.	Beat
well with a spoon. Combine flour and cocoa together
in	a
small bowl and then add to egg mixture. Stir until well blended.
Pour into greased 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberry divinity
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a heavy 3-quart saucepan. Cook over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Cook over medium heat until forms hard ball in water (258°).
Remove from heat.
Beat egg whites (3) in large bowl at high speed with electric mixer until foamy.
Add gelatin and beat until stiff peaks form.
Pour hot syrup mixture in a thin stream over egg whites, beating constantly at high speed.
When mixture holds shape add pecans and drop on wax paper.

title: fluffy mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes. Cover with water and boil in saucepan until tender. Drain water from potatoes but save water. Mash potatoes. Add remaining ingredients and beat until fluffy.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Brown beef in shortening, add sliced onion, salt, pepper and water.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Sprinkle strawberry jello over.
Stir and chill.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Pound chicken breasts until thin (about 1/4-inch).
Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika in a bag.
Add chicken; shake to coat well.
Shake off excess.
Heat butter and olive oil in large skillet until bubbling.
Saute chicken breasts 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Do not overcook.
Drain on paper towel.
Keep warm. Drain off all but 2 tablespoons butter and oil.
Stir in Madeira or water in dripping, scraping bottom of skillet to loosen any browned bits.
Add lemon juice and heat briefly.
Return chicken to skillet with lemon slices and heat until sauce thickens.
Add capers; sprinkle with minced parsley.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook meat in a large frying pan over medium heat; drain. Return meat to pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Spoon Sloppy Joes over toasted hamburger buns.

title: hot mulled punch
directions: Pour fruit juices into 30 or 36-cup coffee maker.
Put all other ingredients into basket.
Plug in and perk.
When complete, remove basket which still contains cinnamon sticks.
Makes 40 punch cups.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until almost tender.
While it is cooking, grate cheese.
Drain macaroni.
Add 3/4 of cheese to macaroni. Butter 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add remaining butter to macaroni and stir until butter is melted.
Pour in pan.
Add milk to cover.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cheese is browned.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except crackers and margarine.
Crush crackers and sprinkle on vegetables. Drizzle margarine over top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° approximately 55 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to cream mixture.
Add sour cream (blend well).
Make a mixture of cinnamon and sugar (to make 1 cup) and chopped nuts.
Spoon coffee cake mixture, alternating with cinnamon and nut mixture into a well-greased pan (swirl the batter).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: marinated mushrooms, shrimp and onions
directions: Put all ingredients together.
Let stand, refrigerated, at least 24 hours before serving.

title: english butter cookie
directions: Mix above ingredients in a large bowl.
Roll into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make tiny dent in middle and fill with jelly.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: irish potato rolls
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, Crisco, potatoes and salt, then milk.
Put yeast in next, then flour and work together.
Let rise until double in size.

title: one thousand isle dressing
directions: Mix well, chill and serve on salads.

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Cook squash in boiling salted water, until just tender; drain. In pan, melt 4 tablespoons butter.
Add carrot and onion and saute until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups stuffing cubes, soup and sour cream.
Gently stir in zucchini. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole which has been buttered.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and remaining cubes and mix.
Sprinkle on casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: gnocchi
directions: Empty Ricotta cheese from container into a bowl.
Fill Ricotta container with flour and combine with cheese, egg and oil.
Knead well.
Divide into 4 equal parts.
Roll out into "snakes" and cut into 1-inch strips.
Place in boiling water for approximately 2 to 3 minutes.
Or you may place cut dough on cookie sheet that has been sprayed with Pam and sprinkle with cornmeal and freeze. Remove from freezer and put in plastic bags.
When ready to serve, remove from freezer and boil.

title: no-bake cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping; blend well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, for 4 hours.
Garnish with fresh strawberries, if desired.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar, flour and spices.
Stir in prunes and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in tube pan or 45 minutes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: grilled hot wings
directions: Put wings in plastic bag; coat with Tabasco sauce.
Shake well.
Sprinkle blackened redfish seasoning into bag and shake again.
Cook on grill until done.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll out cookie dough in greased pizza pan.
Press in chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Combine Cool Whip and cream cheese adding sugar and vanilla to taste.
Spread over cooled cookie crust.
Garnish with fruit and glaze if desired.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in lightly greased baking dish.
Add water. Combine sugar and margarine.
Add flour, cinnamon and salt mixture.
Blend together and sprinkle on top of apples.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
This amount makes about 6 servings.

title: amaretto dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together in blender or food processor. Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: pilgrim pumpkin pie
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients well with mixer.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Spread bread cubes on bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Spread sauerkraut evenly over bread, then layer beef over that. Pour dressing over all. Cover with aluminum foil sprayed with Pam. Bake 20 minutes. Remove cover. Add cheese and bake 10 minutes. If you like Reuben sandwiches, you will love this.

title: easy chinese chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients, pour over chicken wings.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn wings occasionally.

title: pineapple-bran muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in eggs.
Stir in honey, pineapple and bran.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add to bran mixture alternately with milk.
Mix lightly; spoon batter into oiled muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
18 small muffins.

title: green pepper dip
directions: Cook egg yolks, sugar and vinegar until thick.
Add peppers and onion.
Remove pan from stove and add cream cheese.
Stir until smooth; chill.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients until slightly thick.
Pour into baking dish.
In a bowl, put 1 cup flour, 1 cup sugar, 1 egg and 1 tablespoon baking powder.
Mix until crumb-like pie dough. Sprinkle on top of the peaches.
Melt 1 stick butter.
Pour over crumbled mixture.
Bake at 350° to 400° about 30 minutes or until brown.
Top with ice cream or whipped cream (optional).

title: overnight french toast
directions: In medium bowl, whisk all ingredients together.
Place bread (fresh, sliced French) in a rimmed baking sheet and slowly pour batter over.
Turn bread until all are covered.
Press piece of waxed paper directly over bread to cover.
Refrigerate overnight. In the morning, cook on moderate heat in skillet or griddle with butter until golden brown.
Eat and enjoy!

title: barbecues
directions: Fry and drain hamburger and onion.
Add ketchup, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, tomato paste and 1 can water. Simmer on low.

title: potatoes and eggs
directions: Boil potatoes and slice into rounds.
Grease deep baking dish. Layer potatoes, then eggs, also sliced into rounds.
Dot with butter and smooth on a layer of sour cream.
(A small amount of milk added to the sour cream will make it easier to spread.) Continue to layer.
Top off with bacon, uncooked and cut in half. Bake 3/4 hour or longer, if needed, at 350°.
Can be prepared ahead of time and baked just before serving.

title: turkey, chicken and tuna casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, stir again.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Half recipe for 2 or 4 people.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage; drain. Butter bread. Add and cut bread into cubes. Place cubes in bottom of buttered 9 x 13 casserole dish. Beat eggs. Add milk, mustard, pepper and sausage. Stir to blend. Pour over bread cubes. Sprinkle grated cheese on top. Let sit in refrigerator 12 hours or overnight. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Let set 5 to 10 minutes before serving. Serves 6 to 10.

title: chicken and vegetable spaghetti
directions: In large skillet, melt butter; saute garlic 1 minute.
Add broccoli and carrots; stir-fry 5 minutes.
Stir in chicken, pea pods, onions, water, sherry, bouillon and tarragon.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes or until veggies are crisp-tender.
In small bowl, combine cornstarch and water; blend well.
Add to skillet; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cook spaghetti to desired doneness.
Drain; rinse with hot water.
Serve veggies-chicken over spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shoe peg corn-green bean casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Mix remaining ingredients together (except Ritz crackers) with onions.
Sprinkle Ritz cracker crumbs over top of casserole.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: onion-baked pork chops
directions: In small bowl, combine soup mix and bread crumbs. Dip chops in egg, then bread crumb mixture until evenly coated. In lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking or roasting pan, arrange chops. Bake at 400°, uncovered, for 20 minutes or until done. Turn once. Makes 4 servings.
tags: Recipe Secrets golden onion soup mix

title: holiday strawberry bread
directions: Make hole in center of dry ingredients and pour in liquid mixture. Stir until just blended.
Pour into 1 large or 2 medium loaf pans or use 1 pound coffee cans.
I make this at Christmas and give along with pumpkin bread as gifts.
Freezes well.

title: snedeker salad dressing(wv family recipe)
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, egg and 1/2 cup water.
Add vinegar and 3/4 cup water.
Cook together and stir until thickened.
Then add prepared mustard.
Refrigerate. Use in cabbage salad, potato salad, etc.
Can be mixed half and half with Miracle Whip as a salad dressing or use it alone.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spoon pineapple over and then sprinkle cake mix over.
Drop slices of margarine over cake mix and then scatter nuts and/or coconut over top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done and lightly brown.

title: potato peel soup
directions: Generously peel the potatoes. Put the peelings in a pot along with remaining ingredients. Simmer mixture for 1 1/2 hours. Put through a blender and add 1 cup milk and 1 cup grated cheese. Heat until cheese is melted. Serve.

title: sunday corn bread
directions: Mix well. Bake in 9-inch pan or skillet about 40 minutes or until golden brown. Bake at 350 degrees.

title: swiss steak
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

title: lemon bars
directions: Line entire bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers. Mix lemon juice with milk until thick.
Spread milk/juice mixture over crackers.
Top mixture with layer of graham crackers.
Chill 2 to 3 hours, until crackers soften; cut into bars.
Very rich.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Roll mixture into 6 equal balls and set each ball into a paper souffle cup.
Set cups on freezer-sage plate; cover with moisture and vapor-resistant wrapping and freeze until hardened.
Makes 2 servings, 3 balls each.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix mushroom soup, chicken soup, tuna and milk together.
Cook macaroni until tender.
Pour into tuna mixture (with water) and bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: giant soap bubbles
directions: Mix Joy or Dawn detergent with water.
Measure carefully, it makes a big difference.
Stir.
Add glycerine.
It tends to make more durable bubbles.
Bend coat hanger into a loop.
Pour bubble juice into skillet.
Now dip your coat hanger loop into bubble solution, then wave it in the air.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Drain peas and corn.
Mix corn and peas with cream of mushroom and celery.
Mix Jiffy mix as for cornbread.
Place drained beef in pan, then pour mixture of peas, corn, cream of mushroom and cream of celery on top.
Pour over cornbread mix and place in oven to brown.

title: linguini
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil and add the clams with juice, salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add parsley.
Serve over lighter angel hair pasta or small size pasta.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole bowl.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with crackers or bread.

title: calico salad
directions: Combine kraut, onion, green pepper and pimentos.
Mix vinegar, sugar, salad oil, salt, celery seed and garlic salt.
Stir into kraut mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: quick-easy lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and leave in cool water.
Brown meat and drain. Stir in with meat, cottage cheese, mushrooms and spaghetti sauce. Layer in pan; top with sliced cheese.
Bake at 375° until bubbles, about 1 hour.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Blend milk and instant pudding and let sit for 5 minutes.
Add Cool Whip and Reese's pieces.
Pour into chocolate crust pie shell and freeze.
Bring out 20 minutes before serving.

title: alligator sauce piquante
directions: Make roux using 1/2 cup oil and 1 cup flour.
When roux is golden brown, add onions and simmer for 5 minutes. Add tomato sauce and simmer for 1 hour. Do not add water.
In another pot, brown seasoned gator meat.
After tomato sauce and onions have simmered for 1 hour, add gator meat, bell peppers, green onions, cream of mushroom soup, V-8 juice, bay leaf, garlic, oregano, Lea & Perrins and 3 quarts of water.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 2 hours.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: apple muffins
directions: In large bowl, thoroughly combine flour, apples, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Stir in oil, nuts and vanilla.
Batter will be stiff.
Grease and flour muffin tins.
Fill half full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: italian meatball kabobs(4 servings)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Shape into 1 1/2 to 2-inch balls.
On four skewers, arrange meatballs, onions, peppers and zucchini alternately.
Grill over medium coals or broil 4 to 5 inches from heat source, 5 to 8 minutes per side for medium doneness (160°) or until well done (170°).

title: mackie's cracked sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 2 cookie sheets.
Cream butter and sugar together until light.
Beat in yolks and vanilla. Sift together the measured, sifted flour, baking soda and cream of tartar, then fold into the butter-sugar mixture.
Form dough into walnut sized balls.
Place 2 inches apart on the cookie sheets.
Do not flatten.
Bake for about 11 minutes until tops are cracked and just turning color.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: soy macaroni cheese loaf
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water until tender.
Cook parsley and onion in oil until soft.
Place a layer of drained macaroni in baking dish and add a layer of onion and soy or cottage cheese.

title: chicken balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll in coconut.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli until tender then drain.
Line casserole dish with broccoli. Layer chicken cubes on top of broccoli.
Mix mayonnaise, cream of chicken sour and curry powder with wire whisk.
Pour mixture on top of chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and croutons.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: crazy crunch
directions: Cook sugar, margarine and Karo to hard crack stage.
Add vanilla.
Pour over popped corn, stirring to coat well.
Pour onto foil in a thin layer.
Break into pieces when cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: peachy pecan ham
directions: Brush ham with 1/2 cup preserves.
Add remaining 1/2 cup preserves, brown sugar, peach nectar, cornstarch and mustard. Cook until thick and add nuts.
Pour over ham.
Garnish with peach slices.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine 1 egg, shortening and dry cake mix until crumbly; reserve 1 cup.
Pat remaining mixture lightly in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown. Beat remaining 2 eggs, sugar, baking powder, salt, lemon peel and lemon juice with beater until light and foamy.
Pour over hot crust.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.
Cool.
Cut into bars (2 x 1 1/2-inches).
Makes 32 bars.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Add garlic when almost completely browned. Drain hamburger and then add green beans and mushroom soup. Put hamburger mixture in a 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle cheese over hamburger mixture. Place Tater Tots on top of mixture. Sprinkle cheese on top of Tater Tots. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet ham slice
directions: Mix brown sugar and pineapple juice.
Cut ham slice into 4 to 6 pieces.
Put ham pieces into large skillet.
Pour pineapple juice and brown sugar over ham.
Cook over medium to medium-high heat until thoroughly heated, about 5 to 7 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all together until well blended (3 minutes).
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Add topping while still warm.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all without meat and let stand 5 minutes, then mix in hamburger.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes.

title: hot salsa
directions: Peel and quarter tomatoes.
Add sugar, salt, vinegar, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, garlic and basil.
Bring mixture to a boil and simmer about 2 hours until slightly thickened.
Add onions, bell peppers and hot peppers to mixture and return to boil.
Taste and add more hot peppers if desired.
Pour into hot jars and seal.
Makes 8 to 10 pints.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream butter, sugar and salt until fluffy.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Roll into balls, about 1 teaspoon of dough for each cookie. Bake at 250° for 1 hour. Do not overbake.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt peanut butter and chocolate chips. Fold in corn flakes and coconut.
Drop by heaping spoonfuls onto waxed paper. Refrigerate until set.

title: skillet corn bread
directions: Mix and sift together the corn meal, flour, sugar and salt. Heat oven to 425° and put medium size 9 or 10-inch iron skillet on hot burner with 1 1/2 tablespoons of shortening.
When this gets hot, add 1 cup milk, 1 egg (well beaten) and 1 tablespoon shortening to corn meal mixture and pour into hot frying pan or skillet.
Immediately put into hot oven and bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Put sherbet in punch bowl.
Pour chilled 7-Up over.
Stir. Ready to serve.

title: dutch henry
directions: Bring to a boil and serve on a pancakes/waffles or french toast. Very good and rich.

title: home made noodles
directions: Combine egg, water, and salt.
Gradually work in the flour until consistency to roll.
Roll out on floured surface.
Roll very thin.
Cut into narrow strips and put into boiling broth. Cook about 10 minutes.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Brown meat, chopped onions and chopped garlic in margarine and olive oil, lightly brown.
Add other ingredients, except mushrooms, and simmer for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Add mushrooms (with liquid) and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Mix cukes, onions and salt.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Boil sugar with vinegar until sugar is dissolved and cool it.
Drain cukes and onions mixture.
Mix syrup and pickles together.
Put in containers and freeze at least 3 to 5 days and serve whenever you want.

title: venison roast
directions: Place in pan and marinate for 12 hours.
Cook, covered, for 4 to 4 1/2 hours at 325°.
Turn at 3 hours. Remove from oven.
Leave covered and spoon juice over meat several times.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine pineapple, cornstarch, sugar and salt. Cook until thick and clear, stirring constantly.
Add butter and lemon juice, if desired.
Pour into pie shell. Add top crust.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in ball.
Place in 4 1/2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain.
Yummy!!!

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix ingredients together into a batter.
Drop by spoon into hot grease.
Fry until tender or roll into small balls.
Drop in hot grease and fry until brown.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream cheese, butter and oleo. Add sugar slowly and cream. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Fold in flour. Add flavorings. Pour into 10-inch tube or Bundt pan. Place in cold oven. Turn temperature to 300°. Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Butter a 9 x 5 x 4 baking dish.
Crumble 12 crackers in bottom of dish.
Cover with 1/4 cup milk.
Add 1/2 can of corn and another layer of 12 crackers.
Add rest of can of corn.
Continue layers of crackers, milk and corn.
Top with 6 tablespoons butter over last of crackers.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and egg until crumbly.
Sprinkle over the apples.
Melt the butter and pour over the mixture.
Sprinkle cinnamon over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Soak chicken in salt water overnight, drain.
Put rice in 9 x 11 1/2-inch baking dish.
Lay cut up chicken on top of rice. Sprinkle salt and pepper on chicken.
Add water.
Lay aluminum foil over top.
Bake 1 hour at 375° or until chicken is done.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook, debone and layer chicken in bite size pieces in 2-quart greased casserole dish.
By directions, prepare rice and set aside.

title: megan's apple crisp
directions: Grease 9 x 9 baking pan. Place apples slices in pan. Mix together the rest of the ingredients and sprinkle on top of the apples. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and 1/2 cup pecans.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely and place in refrigerator to chill well.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix and let set 2 to 3 hours.

title: sausage soup
directions: In a large, covered soup pot, combine all ingredients and simmer for 2 hours. You can add other kinds of beans, such as pinto, navy, Great Northern or butter beans.

title: chicken-rice soup
directions: Add rice to chicken broth.
Bring to boiling and simmer covered until rice is tender, about 20 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: rocky road cake
directions: The package of cake mix should include separate envelopes: cake mix, macaroon mixture and glaze mix.
Combine cake mix, 1 1/4 cups water, butter and eggs in a large mixing bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed of an electric mixer.
Stir in marshmallows, pecans and 1/2 cup chocolate morsels.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan or tube pan.
Combine macaroon mix, 1/3 cup water and remaining chocolate morsels; mix well.
Spoon over chocolate batter without touching sides of pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 25 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
Combine glaze mix and 1 tablespoon plus 1 teaspoon water; mix until smooth.
Spoon over cake.

title: preacher's delight
directions: Bake cake and let cool.
Punch holes in cake and pour milk over cake.
Place drained pineapple over the cake.
Add whipped topping and sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: oatmeal-raisin muffins
directions: These small, moist, bite-size muffins are best served slightly warmed, so if you make them ahead, reheat them on a baking sheet in a hot oven for a few minutes before serving and then toss again in cinnamon sugar. At Thanksgiving time, you might want to buy a few extra bags of cranberries and store them in the freezer so you can make cranberry muffins all year long. These should be made in small cupcake pans, those with a top diameter of 1 3/4-inches.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Cut up your favorite fruits (apples, oranges, tangerines, dates, raisins, coconut, any other).
According to the amount of fruit, mix with 1/2 or 1 cup whipped cream and vanilla flavoring.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt 1 1/2 squares of chocolate and 1/4 cup butter.
Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Beat eggs lightly and add to flour mixture.
Add chocolate to flour-egg mixture and milk and vanilla. Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with ground pecans before baking.

title: chili mac
directions: Brown beef. Add onion and cook until slightly browned.
Stir in tomatoes, beans and water.
Bring to a boil. Add uncooked macaroni and seasonings. Stir well.
Lower heat to simmer.
Cover and cook until macaroni is done.
Stir occasionally during cooking.

title: all american apple pie
directions: Slice apples; sprinkle with mixture of sugar, flour, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Fill pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring sugar, corn syrup and water to boil.
Cook to 238°.
Add peanuts and salt to mixture and cook to 300°.
Remove from heat. Quickly stir margarine, baking soda and vanilla into hot mixture, blending well.
Turn hot mixture onto well-greased cookie sheet. Cool completely.
Break into pieces.
Store in airtight container or eat.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken.
Debone and shred in pieces.
Cook spaghetti
in remaining broth.
Saute onion and pepper in oleo.
Mix spaghetti with cubed cheese, then remaining ingredients.
Cook in buttered casserole dish at 350° until bubbly.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: nut cookies
directions: Mix well and drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 10 minutes.

title: ham 'n swiss rolls
directions: Blend butter, mustards, poppy seed and Worcestershire sauce. Split dinner rolls crosswise; spread butter mixture on each half. Spread mayo on 1/2 of each roll and layer ham and cheese slices. Put on top of sandwiches.
Put on cookie sheet.
Cover with foil and heat rolls for 20 to 25 minutes in a 400° oven.
Serve while hot.

title: fluffy cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and fold in small container of cool whip. Chill several hours.

title: snicker cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour half the batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Melt caramels and margarine over low heat.
Pour over baked cake. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Spoon the rest of the cake batter over caramel layer.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes. Increase temperature to 350° and bake 10 minutes.

title: 8-minute cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth, add sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla. Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon onto crust.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut chicken in 1 1/2-inch cubes and rinse.
Combine ingredients in cup.
Dip chicken pieces in flour mixture and fry or bake until golden brown.

title: turkey curry
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, cook celery and onions in a large skillet with butter or margarine until onions are limp. Stir in flour, salt, bouillon and curry powder until well blended. Slowly stir in milk and cook over medium heat, stirring until thickened.
Add olives and turkey and heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cold vegetable salad
directions: Drain first 3 ingredients in colander.
Cook last 3 ingredients and set aside until cool.
Combine all ingredients and put in refrigerator.
Better the next day!

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Make brownies in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool slightly.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients together and form into a ball.
Roll in nuts.

title: anytime smoothie
directions: In a blender, put berries or peaches (fresh is preferred, but frozen with no juices is okay), then break 1 banana on top.
Next, add yogurt, honey (or sugar), cinnamon and/or nutmeg.
Add protein powder, if desired, at this time.
Add enough ice to fill just under top of blender.
Put enough orange juice in to fill to near top.
Put lid securely over blender and blend at low and then high speed.
Pour into tall glass or frosted mug.
Makes 24 ounces.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well in small bowl.
Serve with vegetables such as carrots, celery, green pepper, cauliflower and broccoli spears. Great for parties or meals.

title: drop tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs and add oil and sugar.
Add flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop with a spoon on sprayed cookie sheet and bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: salmon surprise
directions: Break up salmon with fork; add the rest of ingredients.
Stir well.
Put in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Heat the milk in a saucepan until it is hot, but not boiling. Mix the water, corn meal and salt together in a small bowl; then add it to the heated milk.
Continue heating the mixture over low heat until it has thickened.
Stir frequently to prevent lumps from forming.
Add the beaten eggs and the butter to the thickened corn mixture and mix well.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine the apples and sugar and let set 1/2 hour.
Add the flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, soda, egg, oil and nuts.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° in well oiled 8 x 8-inch pan.
Needs no topping.

title: slaw
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
In a saucepan, heat to boiling the remaining ingredients until the sugar is dissolved; pour over cabbage mixture while hot.
Mix well.
Let cool, then refrigerate.

title: country pasta with mozzarella
directions: Cook rigatoni.
Cook bacon until browned.
Add broccoli and garlic, cook approximately 4 to 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients except parsley.
Continue to cook over medium heat until cheese melts.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together well.
Beat egg yolks.
Add milk and pumpkin.
Cream together well.
Add (beaten) egg whites. Add dry ingredients mixture.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 40 minutes, or until thick.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook ground beef until browned in skillet. Remove meat and add onions and green pepper to skillet. Cook until tender.
Drain fat. Stir in tomatoes, rice, salt, chili powder and black pepper. Add hamburger and mix well. Pour into casserole dish and cover. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cocoa and milk.
Boil for 3 to 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and oats. Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together except water chestnuts and bread.
Mince water chestnuts and add to mixture.
Refrigerate overnight for best results.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 45 minutes at 325° to 350°, uncovered.
This is a good one dish meal with cornbread or hard rolls.
It's also an excellent potluck dish!

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Reserve 1/4 of chips to crumble on top.
Bake 20 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Put pumpkin, Milnot, sugar, cinnamon and eggs in bowl and mix well.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch baking pan and sprinkle dry cake mix over top of the batter.
Drizzle melted butter over cake mix and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and serve. Top with whipped cream.

title: nutty popcorn
directions: Combine popped corn, almonds and pecans in a large bowl, then set aside.
Melt butter in a saucepan, add brown sugar.
Cook about 30 seconds, stirring constantly.
Pour sugar mixture over popcorn mixture.
Stir until evenly coated.
Spread mixture in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yield: 14 cups.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Wash the potatoes. Cut into pieces (peel, if desired).
Cut up the onions (as many as you like).
Pour oleo over the potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle with Lawry's salt.
Microwave on High 15 to 20 minutes or until done. Stir halfway through.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, sugar and oleo.
Press mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar thoroughly; fold in Cool Whip.
Spread mixture onto cooled crust; let set 1/2 hour.
Dissolve jello in hot water, add strawberries and stir until well blended.
Pour over cheese layer. Chill until set.

title: ann marie's nacho dip
directions: Mix over low heat until melted. Serve with nacho chips.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken pieces.
Mix other ingredients together, except olive oil.
Dip each chicken piece in olive oil, then in the bread crumb mixture.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 1 hour, turning once.
Serve with a salad.

title: most requested liver
directions: Coat wide heavy skillet with oil.
Dust liver with flour. Cook over medium heat until lightly browned on both sides.
Add oil as needed.
Remove from pan.
Add onion and pepper to pan. Cook until onion is soft.
Remove.
Put liver back in pan.
Put vegetables on top.
Sprinkle with soup; pour tomatoes over all. Season to taste.
Cook over low heat approximately 25 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: bloody mary shrimp casserole
directions: Soften green pepper, celery and onion in microwave. Combine ingredients and season with salt, pepper, paprika and Cajun seasoning. Place in casserole and top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Layer carrots, onion and bell pepper slices in Pyrex dish.
Combine soup, sugar and vinegar in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over vegetables, cover and refrigerate.
Serve cold.
Keeps one month.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies(chris warren's favorite)
directions: Cream butter; add sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Place on cookie sheet with ice cream scoop, about 6 to a sheet.
Bake 13 minutes at 350°.
Do not brown.
Underbake and let finish baking on cookie sheet.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Excellent over spinach salad.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and frost cake when cooled.

title: raspberry gelatin salad
directions: Heat applesauce to boiling.
Add raspberry jello and frozen raspberries.

title: friendship cake
directions: Cream greeting and smiles thoroughly.
Add hugs separately. Slowly stir in love.
Sift sympathy and hospitality and fold in carefully.
Bake in warm heart.
Serve often.

title: rhubarb delight
directions: Put rhubarb in lightly greased 8x8 pan.
Add sugar and mix. Pour jello powder on top then cake mix, then water, then butter.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour, milk and baking powder into a batter.
Place butter, cut up, in bottom of baking dish.
Pour in batter.
Add your favorite fruit on top of batter.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
(Make sure to check if fruit is sweetened.)

title: sweet rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let set at least 5 minutes. Mix all ingredients together in given order until well mixed.
Let dough rest 10 minutes, then knead until soft and pliable.
Place in warm moist place until doubled in bulk.
Punch down and form into rolls or desired shapes.
Again let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: candy
directions: Melt candy in double broiler; add noodles and peanuts.
Pour out in cookie sheet real thin.
Put in refrigerator until hard; break into small pieces.

title: cheese treats
directions: Spray 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex dish with nonstick spray.
Layer in order listed.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Let cool; then slice into bite-size squares.
May put fancy toothpick in each square, if desired, before serving.

title: coconut rice
directions: Blend the coconut with its own milk and drain the liquid into a pan.
Boil coconut milk to get the coconut oil.
Reserve oil.
Add the milk to the coconut and drain again.
Put this milk in the pan with the coconut oil.
Add rice, brown sugar, salt and raisins. Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat to very low.
Simmer for about 20 minutes or until the liquid has been absorbed.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion, then add the tomato paste, Veg-All, Worcestershire sauce, salt and garlic powder.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Place in an 11 x 13-inch pan; cover with mashed potatoes.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, or until cheese is melted.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° in greased casserole dish, covered with foil.

title: lumberjack macaroni
directions: Spread hot pasta out on a large platter. Sprinkle with next 4 ingredients.
Pour over all, hot melted butter.
Mix with 2 forks until sauce is creamy.
Serves 6.

title: vidalia cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients except onions (batter will be thin). Stir in onions, mixing well.
Pour into well-greased iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until light brown.
Let cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Beat butter, powdered sugar, egg yolks and vanilla until thick.
Fold in whipped cream.
Break one-half of the cake into little pieces in a loaf pan.
Pour one-half of the custard over the cake.
Pour half of the smashed candy bar over the custard. Repeat with cake, custard and candy bars.
Refrigerate overnight and serve the next day.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Heat all ingredients until very hot. Serve with chips or cornbread.

title: stove top corn bread(recipe developed march 19, 1988)
directions: Sift meal and flour; mix dry ingredients.
Beat egg until fluffy.
