Stir in egg and milk; spray skillet with Pam.
Preheat skillet.
Pour mixture into skillet; turn heat down to very low and cover.
Cook until top of cornbread is firm; turn cornbread over and brown top.
Corn bread will cook in 15 or 20 minutes.
Makes 8 slices.

title: seven-up or sprite cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients with an electric mixer for exactly 10 minutes.
Pour the mixture into a greased and floured angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool completely and remove cake from pan.

title: nutty o's
directions: Heat
oven
Brush
1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll
pan
with
butter.
Heat brown sugar, corn syrup, oleo
and salt in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved, about 5 minutes.	Remove from
heat; stir in cereal and nuts until well coated.	Spread mixture	in pan and bake 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Loosen mixture
with metal spatula and let stand until firm, about 1 hour.
Store in covered container.	Makes about 8 cups.

title: okra with tomatoes-bulgaria(bamya s domaty)
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Dice onions, tomatoes and garlic and steam in oil with 2 tsp. of water.
Add paprika and mix.
Add wine and 1/4 cup water and simmer for 30 minutes.
Wash okra and trim off stems, add to onion mixture.
Add salt and place in baking dish.
Bake 20-30 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley and red pepper. Serves 6.

title: watergate salad
directions: Set Cool Whip out on cabinet to defrost.
Drain all 3 cans fruit and place in large mixing bowl.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over fruit and toss lightly.
Stir in sour cream.
Add Cool Whip and stir gently until well blended.
Chill for 6 to 8 hours. Serves 6 to 10 people.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and then at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: hors d'oeuvre pie
directions: On large baking sheet, unfold crust according to package instructions and put into an 11-inch circle.
Pierce through with fork and bake at 425° for 8 minutes, or until very lightly browned.
Cool and place on serving platter.

title: barney's favorite pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Lower oven to 350° and continue cooking approximately 1 hour (until golden brown on top and solid enough not to jiggle when shook).

title: baked shells with turkey or hamburger
directions: Cook large shells according to package directions.
While cooking mix turkey or hamburger, egg, onion, salt and pepper, oatmeal or crackers together.
After shells are cooked, cool with cold water.
In oblong 9 x 12-inch baking dish, fill each shell with turkey or hamburger mixture.
Then pour spaghetti sauce over all shells.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes at 350°.
When done, sprinkle cheese over top until melted, about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: liver sausage dip
directions: Mix together well.
Serve with crackers or excellent with pretzels.

title: zucchini custard
directions: Mix all of the preceding.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May garnish with sliced olives and pimentos.

title: taco pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese and salsa together, then mix other ingredients.
Spread on tortillas and roll. Refrigerate overnight.
Slice and serve.

title: rice-a-roni
directions: Cook vermicelli in butter until brown.
Cook rice according to package directions. Mix together. Then mix bouillon and water. Pour into dish of rice mixture.
Cook until liquid is absorbed or rice is tender.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and 6 cups of milk in a large non stick saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Cook until the mixture is thickened.

title: amazing lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add chopped onion and green pepper.
Stir until onion and pepper are tender. Add spaghetti sauce.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, spread 1 1/2 cups sauce mixture.
Arrange a layer of uncooked lasagne noodles.
Top with pepperoni slices, cottage or Ricotta cheese and sauce, then sprinkle some Mozzarella and start another layer of noodles, pepperoni, cottage cheese or Ricotta, sauce and Mozzarella.
End with sauce and Mozzarella.
(Do not be concerned with empty space at ends of pan, lasagne will expand during baking.)
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: hungarian twists
directions: Mix well; dough will be sticky.

title: hot buffalo wings
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut tips off wings and save for soup stock or discard.
Cut wings at joints.
Arrange in single layer on broiling pan or rack and sprinkle with garlic powder.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in 400° oven, turning once.

title: lemon chiffon salad
directions: Beat eggs. Add pineapple, water and sugar.
Heat until hot but not boiling.
Remove from heat and add the Jell-O.
Refrigerate until mixture thickens, 1 to 2 hours.
Add nuts and Cool Whip. Place in a large mold. Refrigerate until hard.

title: cranberry citrus quencher
directions: In 2 qt. pitcher combine concentrate, water and cranberry juice; mix well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
To serve stir in soda.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and press in bottom of a 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour this over cooled crust.
Pour 1 package of thawed strawberries (you may use fresh, if possible) over the cream cheese mixture. Cover the strawberries with a jar of strawberry glaze. Chill and serve.

title: strawberry and avocado salad(serves 4)
directions: Break lettuce into salad bowl.
Peel, pit and slice avocado. Clean and cut strawberries in half.
Toss together with dressing.

title: game bird stuffing
directions: Mix cornbread and whole wheat bread, add celery, onion and parsley.
Dampen well with stock from boiled neck and gizzards in seasoned water.
Mix dressing thoroughly and fry in small amount of salad oil until celery and onions look wilted.
Add eggs, mushrooms with juice and pecans.
Season well with salt and pepper.
In another skillet, fry the rice in a small amount of oil until golden brown.
Add enough stock to cover rice and let cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Then add rice to first mixture, mix well.
Stuff bird or bake separately.

title: deluxe cheesecake
directions: Cookie Crust Mixture:
Mix 1 cup flour, 1/4 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon lemon rind, 1/4 teaspoon vanilla with pastry blender.
Cut in butter and 1 egg yolk.
Shape into ball; wrap in wax paper. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Start heating oven to 400°.
Roll about one-third of dough between floured pieces of wax paper into a 9 1/2-inch circle.
Place on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan; trim to fit.
Bake at 400°, 10 minutes or until golden; cool.
Grease side of spring-form pan; fit over filled base.
Roll rest of dough into 15 x 4-inch rectangle; cut in half lengthwise; use to line side of pan, patching if necessary.

title: christmas cake
directions: Combine nuts, cherries and coconut; add flour and mix.
Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Add sugar gradually and continue to cream; add eggs one at a time, blending well after each.
Add salt and flour mixture; blend.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan, line bottom with wax paper and cover top with foil. Place a pan of hot water in the bottom of oven.
Bake in oven at 250° to 275° for 2 1/2 hours, removing foil for the last hour of baking.
Cake is done when top feels slick and sinks slightly from sides of pan.

title: swedish coffee cake
directions: Sift first four ingredients together.
Break 1 egg in a cup and then fill it with milk.
Then add to sifted ingredients.
Add 3 teaspoons melted butter and beat thoroughly.
Spread in pan and drizzle a little melted butter over top.
Then put brown sugar and cinnamon on top and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all together and let set overnight.

title: old settlers beans
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Combine lemon juice, oil, onion, garlic, pepper, sugar, lemon peel and salt in a small bowl; reserve 2 tablespoons marinade. Combine remaining marinade and chicken in a large, resealable, plastic food bag. Seal bag and coat chicken. Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight. Remove chicken from bag. Arrange chicken on microwaveable plate; cover with wax paper. Microwave on High for 5 minutes. Turn and rearrange chicken. Cover and microwave on High 5 minutes. Transfer chicken to grill. Grill for 15 to 20 minutes, turning several times and basting often with reserved marinade.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: In one bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients.
In a second bowl, combine the remaining ingredients.
Mix first bowl of ingredients completely.
Fold into second bowl until blended. Spoon into two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans that have been greased and dusted with flour.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Turn onto rack to cool.

title: homemade pizza dough
directions: Combine sugar, salt, yeast and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Heat milk, butter and water very warm (120°).
Beat into dry ingredients. Add 1/2 cup flour; mix with spoon.
Knead a few minutes.
Add flour as needed.
Let rise in bowl 30 minutes.
Cover with towel. Turn out on lightly cornmealed surface.
Makes 2 pizzas.

title: peas and eggs
directions: Place oil in a large frying pan and saute onion, green pepper, tomato and spices.
Add peas and simmer.
When mixture is heated through, evenly break eggs onto peas and fry sunny side up.
Ready to eat when eggs are done.
Nicely topped with grated cheese, if desired.

title: french pastry
directions: Mix together and press into bottom of 13-inch pan.

title: fired up crabs
directions: Bring 8 quarts water to boil.
Add all ingredients above except crabs and 1/4 cup of Old Bay.
Bring back to boil.
Add live crabs to pot.
Boil 30 minutes.
Turn off heat and soak crabs in pot for 30 minutes.
Remove from pot and sprinkle with remaining Old Bay.

title: oveline's miracle pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and blend thoroughly.
Pour into a 10-inch pie pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
A crust will form on the bottom, pie filling in the center and a coconut topping on top.

title: million dollar salad
directions: Mix together and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Use 3 tablespoons of mix for each cup of boiling water.

title: no bake key lime pie
directions: Beat condensed milk and cream cheese with mixer.
Add Key lime juice a little at a time until well mixed.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, sugar and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over salad and stir.
Or use Good Seasons Italian dressing mix over salad.

title: chocolate yogurt melts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, yogurt, egg and margarine.
Beat until blended.
Stir in chocolate bits.
Drop dough on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 7 dozen.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Place peeled eggs in clean quart jar.
Mix all other ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over eggs.
Put lid on the jar.
Cool at room temperature. When cool, store in the refrigerator for at least 2 weeks before serving.

title: lemon rum sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch, add to boiling water.
Stir constantly and bring to boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add lemon extract or rum and butter.
Stir until butter is melted.
Cool and pour over bread pudding.

title: microwave egg custard pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly add hot milk.
Place in 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Do not cover.
Place on microwave turntable (or turn every 2 minutes).
Cook 6 1/2 to 7 minutes.
Center will become firm during standing time.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms.
Butter and cube 3 slices white bread.
Put bread in bottom of casserole dish.
Combine sauteed mushrooms with sauteed onion, celery and green pepper.
Add mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Spread this mixture over bread.
Butter and cube 3 more slices of bread and put over mixture.
Slightly beat the eggs and milk; pour over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Spread soup over top.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Sprinkle with grated cheese; bake 10 minutes more.

title: pork loin roast
directions: Place roast in a shallow roasting pan and bake in a slow oven at 325° until surfaces are well browned.
Combine defrosted juice, sugar, water and mustard.
Baste meat with this mixture.
Allow 3 hours for roasting.
Garnish with parsley and orange slices.

title: easy lemonade mix
directions: Stir all ingredients together until sugar dissolves.
Pour into screw-top jar.
Cover and store in refrigerator.

title: zucchini frittata
directions: Saute onion in margarine until transparent.
Add zucchini and potatoes.
Cook until zucchini is soft.
Mix cheese into eggs, gently pour into pan.
Cook slowly, about 10 minutes or until bottom is slightly brown.
Place plate over pan and flip frittata onto plate.
Slide back into pan and cook until brown.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and parsley.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate covered pretzels
directions: Line cookie sheets with waxed paper.
Break chocolate in pieces into a small narrow saucepan.
Stir constantly over very low heat until melted.
Holding pretzels with tweezers or small tongs, dip one at a time into white chocolate.
Place pretzels on lined cookie sheets.
Refrigerate 30 minutes or until completely set.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese in bowl; mix well.
Pour half of batter in 9-inch baking pan or iron skillet which has been heated on top of stove with enough oil to keep batter from sticking.
Sprinkle cheese on top and pour remaining batter over cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Corn bread should have golden color as cheese floats to top.
This corn bread is very moist.

title: susie wong chow chow
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook for 20 minutes and place in jars and seal.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix well, about 10 minutes.
Pour into small greased skillet and bake at 400° until brown.

title: manhattan potatoes
directions: Mix
potatoes, green pepper, pimentos, onions, salt and pepper and place
in
a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix milk and soup together
and pour over potato mixture.
Top with cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chicken wings, party pickin'
directions: Cut tips off wings (save tips for soup).
Halve remaining chicken wings at joint.
In a small bowl, combine soup mix, bread crumbs and caraway.

In another small bowl, beat egg with beer. Dip chicken in beer mixture, then soup mixture, coating well. Place in a large shallow pan and drizzle with melted butter. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes or until tender.
Makes 30 appetizers.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown
garlic
and
ground
beef in butter.
Add onion; cook for a few minutes.	Add remaining ingredients;
cook for 15 to 20 minutes on low heat.
Serves 4.

title: granny's homemade hominy
directions: Dissolve lye in water.
(Check strength of lye mixture by dipping large chicken feather in it.
If it cleans the feather from the stem, it is strong enough.
If it doesn't, add more lye. Retest.)

title: pudding in a cloud
directions: Prepare pudding mix with milk as directed on package.
Divide Cool Whip into 8 dessert glasses, 1/3 cup in each.
With spatula or back of spoon, make a depression in center, spreading Cool Whip up sides of glasses.
Spoon pudding into glasses.
Chill; serve.

title: snow pudding & custard sauce
directions: Scald milk in top of double boiler.
Beat egg yolks slightly. Add sugar and salt.
Stir into egg mixture several spoons of scalded milk.
Keep water in bottom of double boiler below boiling during rest of cooking time.
Add egg mixture to scalded milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until the custard thickens only enough to coat a metal spoon.
Cool.
Add vanilla.
Store in covered dish in refrigerator until serving.
Pour over individual servings and garnish.

title: veal medallions with walnuts
directions: Melt butter in heavy large skillet over medium heat.
Pat veal dry and cook about 4 minutes per side for medium rare.
Transfer to heated platter and tent with foil.
Add cream and cognac to pan. Boil, stirring up any browned bits until thickened to sauce like consistency, about 3 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Return veal to pan and add walnuts.
Simmer for 1 minute.

title: copper pennies(marinated carrots)
directions: Combine soup, pepper, salt, oil and vinegar until well blended.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold as a relish.
Enjoy!

title: tabouleh (tabouli)
directions: In a mixing bowl, pour boiling water over the bulgur wheat. Let sit for 1/2 hour.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over wheat and toss.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Serve over a bed of lettuce.
The salad is best if it is refrigerated several hours before serving.
About 10 servings, 175 calories per serving.

title: butter pecan pie with cream cheese pastry
directions: Blend cream cheese,
cup oleo, 1/4 teaspoon butter flavor and flour
thoroughly.
Chill
dough,
then
press into 9-inch pie pan.
Trim	and
flute
dough.
Slightly beat eggs, blend in sugar, salt,
corn syrup and oleo, vanilla and butter flavoring. Arrange pecan
halves
on
bottom
of crust.
Pour filling over them.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350° until center of pie is almost set.
Do not overbake for filling will set as it cools.
Cool 1 hour before cutting.

title: chicken and vegetables
directions: In a large pot, place all ingredients.
Cook at high heat until it begins to boil; then cover and cook at medium-low heat until chicken is done and the vegetables are just slightly tender but not too tender, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: our chili
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chili will cook in 30 to 45 minutes; however, chili is best when simmered for as long as possible!

title: curried chicken
directions: Take skin off chicken and clean it thoroughly.
Soak in soy sauce.
Season with seasoned salt, onion/garlic powder, black pepper, thyme leaf and lots of curry powder.
Brown chicken in oil. Put in large pan with small amount of water, diced peppers, onion, tomatoes and additional curry powder.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Will feed a crowd.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake in uncovered baking dish at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: raspberry and poppyseed dressing
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a blender and mix well.
Keeps in the refrigerator for at least 1 week.
Serves about 8. ENJOY!!!

title: culpeper tomato relish
directions: Peel tomatoes and cut coarsely.
Add chopped onions and peppers.
Add salt and mix.
Let drain in cheesecloth or colander for 3 hours.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Put into jar or crock.
Stir every day for 3 days.
Stir well before using.
This relish will keep for one year, when refrigerated.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat and transfer to large saucepan (Dutch oven).
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: baklava
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Place one sheet of phyllo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brush with butter.
Repeat 5 more times. Sprinkle with 1 cup walnut mixture.
Cover with 1 sheet of phyllo; brush with butter.
Repeat process 2 more times (6 sheets phyllo, 1 cup walnut mixture).
After last layer of phyllo, with sharp knife, cut halfway through layers in triangle pattern to make 24 (or 48 smaller).
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 25 minutes. Heat honey in microwave until hot but not boiling.
Spoon over baklava.
Cool on wire rack at least 1 hour before removing from pan.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish with Pam.
Preheat oven at 350°. Layer the following:
pineapple, then sugar mixed with flour and cheese.
Make the topping with Ritz crackers and melted margarine. Bake for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: easy deep dish peach pie
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and add milk and mix.
Melt butter in deep dish and pour in batter.
Put in enough peaches to cover top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cherry chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour oil in a 9 x 13-inch pan and spread oil until even in bottom of pan.
Place remaining ingredients in a bowl and stir with a fork or spoon, 2 to 3 minutes until blended. Spread evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: spicy prune muffins
directions: Combine prunes, flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, cinnamon and wheat germ in bowl.
Beat egg in separate bowl.
Add sour cream, marmalade and melted butter or canola oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients, mixing just to blend.
Spoon into oiled muffin tins.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes 12.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Melt butter and sugar. Add curry powder.
(If you like a thick sauce, add 1 1/2 tablespoons cornstarch.)
Drain fruit and place in a large flat casserole.
Decorate with green and red cherries, if desired.
Add melted curry sauce. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook noodles, uncovered, in boiling water 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain.
Combine soup, milk, water and Cheddar cheese in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cook and stir until all melted. Cool cheese.
Stir in cooked noodles, turkey, pimentos, peas and carrots.
Spoon mix into a greased 11 3/4 x 17 1/2-inch baking dish.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and parsley. Sprinkle over the top.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 30 minutes or until hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick breakfast ring
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix brown sugar with 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Spread in the bottom of Bundt pan or ring mold. Arrange pecans and cherries (cut side up) on brown sugar.
Dip each biscuit into remaining melted butter and roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix and cook in unbaked pie shell for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: honey butter
directions: Mix all ingredients with beater until creamy.
Keep refrigerated.
Before serving, let stand at room temperature for about 20 minutes to soften.
Can add 1/2 tsp. of cinnamon to make Cinnamon Honey Butter.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Clean and wash grapes; put in a kettle.
Cover with water. Let simmer, but do not boil.
Cook until fruit is soft, then strain through a jelly bag.
Add 1/2 cup sugar for each quart of juice.
Boil hard for 5 minutes.
Can and seal.
Very good if you have your own grapes.
This recipe is made often for Communion for our church.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix into dough.
Roll dough into small balls, then roll in sugar (with a little cinnamon).
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: apple lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and lemon rind; set aside.
Combine eggs, lemon juice, butter and applesauce; add dry ingredients and beat with an electric mixer until mixture is blended.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell; bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake an additional 15 minutes or until set.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: dirt
directions: Grind up cookies.
Mix instant pudding and milk.
Cream together cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Then add pudding mixture, then Cool Whip.
Layer Oreos and cream, starting with Oreos and ending with Oreos.

title: standing rib roast with horseradish sauce
directions: Have butcher remove the bone and tie it to the meat.
Put in roasting pan, fat side up, and season well with salt and pepper. Roast in a 325° oven for 20 minutes per pound.
Meat thermometer should read 150°.
Let stand, tented with aluminum foil, while gravy is being prepared.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix apples, sugar, cinnamon and lemon juice in a 6 x 10-inch Pyrex dish.
Put cake mix in mixing bowl.
Cut butter in thin slices and blend into cake mix with pastry blender.
Add pecans; mix well and sprinkle over apple mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix the flour, butter, brown sugar and pecans together. Spread them in a pizza pan to form the crust.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°; cool.
Mix the cream cheese and powdered sugar; fold in the whipped topping.
Spread over the cooled crust.
Mix gelatin, sugar, salt and 1/2 cup water/strawberry juice.
Dissolve the cornstarch in the other 1/2 cup of water/strawberry juice; stir into gelatin mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Add strawberries; cool.
Spread on top of the cream cheese layer.
Chill well.

title: green rice
directions: Mix all in a crock-pot on high until heated through.
Super easy and very good.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix well and
press
into mold and chill.
Turn upside-down on plate and spread with cream cheese.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Stir well.
Place over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves; then cook to soft ball stage, about 232°.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts, stirring until well coated.
Spread nuts on waxed paper.
Separate with a fork and cool.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Melt the butter and the marshmallows.
Put the Rice Krispies cereal. Mix everything together in bowl.
Put in square pan.
Let it cool off.
Cut into squares.
Then eat them.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir dry ingredients in large bowl, cut in shortening with pastry blender.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture.
Stir until thoroughly moistened. Turn onto floured board and knead 1 to 2 minutes.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness and cut with cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Unused dough can be kept refrigerated for 2 weeks.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar
and
butter.
Add	eggs and bananas.
Sift flour, soda
and salt together.
Stir in slowly.
Add vanilla. Bake in greased and floured pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook
rice.
Slightly
cook
celery,
onions
and green pepper;
drain.
Melt
margarine and mix all of this together. Put cooked
broccoli in greased casserole dish; add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: french fried cauliflower
directions: Wash and break cauliflower into small florets.
Sprinkle with salt.
Combine milk, egg and biscuit mix and stir well.
Dip florets into batter and deep fry until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain.

title: quick instant pudding
directions: Mix good all ingredients.
Boil, stirring constantly.
Then add chips of any flavor.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let set 1 hour before serving.

title: orange glaze
directions: Mix in a small bowl and microwave on High for 1 minute.
Use as a glaze on chicken.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut beef across grain into strips 1/8-inch thick.
Combine soy sauce, garlic, ginger and beef.
Toss and set aside while preparing vegetables.
Heat oil in large frying pan.
Add beef and toss over high heat until browned.
Turn heat up and toss vegetables.
Toss vegetables until tender-crisp. Mix cornstarch with water.
Add to pan.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat well.
Can be served over rice.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges for approximately 3 hours. Combine cottage cheese and jello.
Mix all ingredients together. Crushed peanuts can be used for decoration or mixed through the salad.

title: chicken breast divan
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Sprinkle salt and paprika over chicken, brown.
Remove.
Place broccoli in greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Top with chicken.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice, spread over chicken.
Bake in moderate (350°) oven 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Place under broiler 2 to 3 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spinach lasagna bechamel
directions: Rinse, stem and chop the spinach.
Heat milk until hot, not boiling.
In second pan on medium heat, melt butter.
Do not let it brown.
Whisk in flour.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes, stirring constantly. Gradually add hot milk, continue whisking until sauce thickens and season with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Saute garlic and onion in hot oil.
When onion is translucent, stir in spinach and 1/2 cup parsley.
If spinach is dry, add a little water.
When spinach has wilted, remove from heat.
Set aside.
Mix remaining 1/4 cup parsley, Ricotta cheese, eggs and 2/3 cup Parmesan cheese.
At this point, cook lasagna noodles according to package until al dente. Drain.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni and salt until tender; drain.
Grease baking dish with part of butter.
Spoon a layer of macaroni, then a layer of sliced cheese, until dish is full, ending with cheese. Dot butter over all.
Then pour on milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle corn flakes on the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: dream pie
directions: Mix 1 cup milk, vanilla and Dream Whip.
When it mixes to peaks, add instant pudding and 1 3/4 cups cold milk.
When mixed well, pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate.

title: roasted vegetables
directions: Cut vegetables into uniform pieces.
Mix onion soup, oil and basil.
Pour over vegetables and mix together. Spray casserole or roasting pan with Pam.
Put vegetables in pan and bake at 450° for 30 to 45 minutes until vegetables are done.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, chocolate and eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, salt, flour, baking powder and buttermilk.
Stir in nuts and coconut. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes for layers, 75 minutes for tube pan. Grease and flour pan.

title: chili
directions: Saute onion and peppers until soft.
Crumble hamburger and brown.
Add spices, salt and pepper.
Then add tomatoes; bring to boil.
Add beans.
Bring to a boil again and cut off.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter bread and cut each slice into fourths.
Lay bread on bottom of casserole dish.
Brown sausage and crumble on bread. Put shredded cheese on sausage. Beat eggs and add milk.
Pour over cheese. Bake covered with foil for 15 minutes at 350°. Take off foil and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Chill.
Roll into balls.
Melt chocolate.
Dip balls 3/4 of the way in chocolate.
Sit on wax paper to harden chocolate.

title: bridge club classic
directions: Butter 4 slices of bread and turn, buttered side down, in oblong pan.
Place slice of turkey, ham and Swiss cheese on bread. Cover with another piece of bread, buttered side down.
Beat eggs and add milk, grated onion, salt and pepper.
Pour over sandwiches and soak overnight (or at least 6 hours) in refrigerator.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.

Add sugar, then cream cheese. Add vanilla. Pour in spring-form pan that has been coated with butter and graham cracker crushed bits. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Let cool. Preheat at 475°, then place a mix of 16 ounces of cream cheese, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 teaspoon sugar on top. Cook 5 minutes. Cool 2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix all ingredients well and pour in dish. Chill.

title: the original chex party mix
directions: Heat oven to 250°. Melt butter in large roasting pan in oven. Stir in seasonings. Gradually stir in remaining ingredients until evenly coated. Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Spread on paper towels to cool. Store in airtight container. Makes 12 cups of snack mix.

title: barbecups
directions: Brown beef in skillet, stirring to crumble; drain.
Add barbecue sauce and onion; stir well.
Set aside.

title: homemade crescent rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water (110° to 115°) in large bowl. Add 1 cup flour, evaporated milk, salt, egg, sugar and melted butter.
Beat until smooth.
In separate bowl, cut chilled butter into remaining flour until butter particles are the size of peas. Pour yeast batter over the top.
Fold in until all flour is moist. Cover bowl with plastic wrap.
Chill 4 hours.
Can be refrigerated several days.
Handle dough as little as possible.
Divide in half, keeping rest cool.
Knead 6 to 7 times and roll 1/4 of dough into 1/4-inch thick circle on floured board.
Cut circle into pie shaped wedges.
Roll each loosely toward point.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cover lightly and let rise until double (don't speed rising by placing in warm spot).
When doubled, brush with egg and water mixture.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: gazpacho salad
directions: In the bottom of salad bowl combine dressing, salt, garlic salt and pepper. Mix mushrooms and onions into the dressing. Layer cucumbers in the bowl, sprinkle with parsley.
Remove seeds from the green pepper, cut into thin strips and arrange over cucumbers. Peel the tomatoes and cut into thin wedges.
Arrange carefully on top of salad.
Sprinkle cheese over tomatoes.
Without mixing salad, cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Just before serving, gently mix everything together. Garnish with egg slices on top.

title: north carolina yam muffins
directions: Combine yams, sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour and blend until just moistened.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Spoon batter into greased muffin tins.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Batter may be refrigerated and used as needed.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large aluminum pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 35 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Serve with lots of cold beverage and French bread.

title: rice and chicken bake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tomato relish
directions: Peel tomatoes and cut in pieces.
Drain well.
Add all ingredients together.
Boil 30 minutes.
Fill hot jars and seal.

title: chicken wings in oyster sauce
directions: Place chicken wings in	a
wok	or large frying pan and add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil over moderate heat and simmer, covered, until
the
wings are tender, about 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove lid and boil hard to evaporate all but 1/2 cup of sauce.

title: buns
directions: Mix as follows. Let rise for about 1 hour at room temperature. Work down and make out into small buns. Place on greased cookie sheet. Press buns flat and let rise to desired size. Bake 15 minutes at 425°. Makes 30 buns.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat the remaining 3 ingredients for 3 minutes.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in icebox and let cool.
Divide into half.
Put food coloring in half and roll together.
Let stay in icebox.
Bake as needed.
Do not overcook.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix first nine ingredients in the top of a double boiler and cook over hot water until thick.
Cool slightly and add vanilla flavoring.
Pour cooked mixture into baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream before serving.

title: fruited loaf cake
directions: Drain pineapple chunks & cherries over night in colander. Then, before using fruit, set it on and cover it with paper towels to remove excess moisture. Cream butter & sugar well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add vanilla. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, beating until combined. Fold in drained fruit & walnuts. Turn into 2-3 greased loaf pans & bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour & 15 minutes or until done (do not overbake). Cool in pans. To store in freezer, wrap tightly in foil.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Line 12 muffin cups with paper baking cups.
Combine dry ingredients; add milk, egg, honey and oil.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill prepared muffin cups almost full.
Bake for 15 to 17 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 1 dozen.
One muffin contains 120 calories.

title: a good dressing for potato or macaroni salad
directions: Note:
Can be doubled for a large crowd.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla and sift flour and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's. Decorate the top of cookies with remaining M&M's.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: five spice chicken
directions: Place chicken in a shallow glass dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Occasionally spoon marinade over chicken.
Remove chicken from marinade but preserve marinade.
Place chicken in an ungreased glass baking dish.
Brush marinade on chicken.
Cook uncovered at 350°F for 1 hour, occasionally brushing with marinade.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all together and make good and moist with mayonnaise.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms. Take off stems and scoop out the caps.
Save the caps.
Chop and mix the rest of the mushroom parts with the other ingredients.
Fill caps to heaping.
Put in a cake pan in a single layer.
Add enough water to cover the bottom of the pan. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
The last 10 minutes, bake uncovered.
Put mushrooms and juice in a crock-pot to keep warm for serving.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Grease 8 x 11-inch pan.
Open chilies and lay flat.
Layer 1/3 chilies and 1/3 Monterey Jack and 1/3 Cheddar.
Repeat layers twice, ending with one of the cheeses.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll dough into small balls. Mash with fork and sprinkle with paprika. Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chess cake(good!)
directions: Heat butter and brown sugar on low heat.
Remove from heat. Add other ingredients.
Mix well and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured well.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until done at 300°.
Cut into squares and roll in powdered sugar while still hot.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Place chocolate bark in double boiler; melt.
When melted, add peanuts.
Place on foil by teaspoonfuls.
Let cool.
Place in sealed can.
Will keep really well for at least 2 months.

title: "stompin" good stew
directions: Brown crumbled meat with onion and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients except cornstarch and 1/4 cup water.
Bring to boil, then simmer 20 to 30 minutes until barley is tender.
Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup water; stir into hot stew.
Cook, stirring, until clear and thickened.
Serves 6.

title: big mama's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together margarine and Crisco. Add eggs; beat until fluffy.
Add sugar and beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture and mix well. Add vanilla and mix.

title: baked corn with sour cream
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook and crumble bacon.
Cook onion in butter; blend in flour and salt.
Add sour cream gradually, stirring to keep smooth.
Bring to a boil.
Add corn.
Cook until heated thoroughly.
Fold in half of bacon.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Garnish with parsley and remaining bacon.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In oven, melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Mix flour and sugar; add milk.
Using wire whip, blend until smooth.
Pour mixture into pan over margarine.
Next, pour peaches and juice over batter.
Do not mix.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes, until bubbly.
Top with vanilla ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: homemade custard ice cream
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat sugar and egg yolks together.
Scald milk. Slowly add scalded milk to sugar and egg yolk mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture coats spoon.
Cool slightly.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add egg white and vanilla to slightly cooled custard.
Place in refrigerator until ready to freeze.
Add whipping cream just before freezing.
Proceed with freezing according to freezer manufacturer's directions.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: lemon torte
directions: This dessert has 4 layers. For the first layer, combine oleo, flour and chopped nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook hamburger and chopped onions.
Pour out fat.
Add stewed tomatoes and can of tomato soup.
Add string beans.
Boil potatoes and whip with milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Pour mashed potatoes on top of hamburger, tomatoes, soup and beans.
Add grated cheese and heat in 300° oven until cheese is melted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: german sweet chocolate icing
directions: Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 2 minutes.
Add coconut and pecans.
Beat until thick.

title: strawberry gelatin
directions: Add water to jello.
Let it dissolve well.
Add pineapple, strawberries and bananas.
Mix well.
Pour 1/2 mixture into a bowl.
Let sit in refrigerator.
When set, smooth sour cream over set gelatin.
Pour remainder of gelatin on sour cream.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: green pea salad
directions: Layer in casserole dish in order given.
Spread enough mayonnaise to cover onion.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Place in refrigerator.
Chill before serving. Can be made the night before.

title: homemade irish cream
directions: Blend at high speed for 1 minute.
Refrigerate.
Makes a little over 1 quart.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Heat sugar and butter until bubbly.
Cool and then mix eggs and extracts.
Add flour and Rice Chex.
Mix well and put in well-greased pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: mother's old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: In large bowl blend oleo, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Combine flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Add to creamed mixture; mix to blend.
Stir in oats and pecans.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet lined with wax paper. Flatten with floured fork to 2 inches in diameter.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet; remove to cooling rack.
Sift confectioners sugar over top.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add oil, pumpkin and eggs; beat. Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done when you insert knife.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: spinach madeleine *
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package.
Drain and reserve liquid.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until blended and smooth, but not brown.
Add onion and cook until soft but not brown.
Add liquid slowly, stirring constantly to avoid lumps.
Cook until smooth and thick. Add seasonings and cheese which has been cut into small pieces, stirring until melted.
Combine with spinach. This may be served immediately or put into a casserole and topped with buttered bread crumbs.
The flavor is improved if the latter is done and kept in refrigerator overnight.
This may also be frozen.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pour over 2 gallons popped corn.
Cook in oven at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 5 minutes.
Pour on wax paper and separate.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together.
Make at least 12 hours before serving.

title: never fail pound cake
directions: *I use 1 each vanilla and lemon.

title: soft play dough
directions: Boil water away from the children.
Bring it to the table. (Remember safety.)
Add the food coloring to the water if you want a colored dough.

title: hot tamales
directions: Form meat mixture into small rolls.
Use coffee filters.
Wet each filter.
Lay out flat.
Drop 1/2 tsp corn meal on wet filter. Add a small roll of meat mixture on corn meal mix.
Add another 1/2 tsp corn meal mix over meat.
Roll tamales.
Lay a heavy pot on its side and start placing tamales in.
Stack tightly, filling entire pot.

title: diabetics candy
directions: Blend peanut butter, milk, sweetener and vanilla.
Add raisins and crushed graham cracker.
Form into balls.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Combine milk and pudding mix in a medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture coats the back of a spoon (about 15 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until smooth.
Store in an airtight container in refrigerator.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Heat cranberry juice and strain.
Save juice; set cranberries aside.
Dissolve jello in hot juice and water; add salt and lemon juice.
Chill until thick; beat in mayonnaise until light and fluffy.
Fold in cranberries, fruit and nuts; pour in mold.
Chill until set.
Yield:
12 servings.
Carbohydrate 25 g, protein 1 g, fat 3 g, calories 131.
One serving = 2 1/2 fruit exchanges, 1/2 fat exchange.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pan or casserole (8 x 14-inches) and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, cheese, onion and mayonnaise in large casserole dish.
Melt margarine and combine with crumbled crackers.
Sprinkle over top of vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is brown and bubbling.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour loaf pan. Bake 55 minutes at 350°.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: country fried steak
directions: Sprinkle steaks with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Dredge steak into flour and fry in hot oil.
Set aside.
Pour out excessive oil, add flour to remaining oil and stir until golden. Add equal amount of milk and water to make a thin gravy.
Season to taste.
Put meat in an ovenproof casserole.
Pour gravy over it, cover and bake at low temperature for 2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: crab quiche
directions: Beat eggs, cream and milk together.
Add salt and pepper and set aside.
Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter until onion is clear.
Spread onion over crust.
Layer crab meat on onion, then sprinkle with cheese.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chess cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg and melted margarine and mix well. Will be stiff.
Spread into lightly greased pan (12 x 9 x 2-inch). Press into bottom of pan.

title: hot spicy tea
directions: Mix well and store in tight covered jar.
To serve: 2 teaspoons dissolved in a cup of boiling water.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: blintze souffle
directions: Melt butter or margarine in 2-quart casserole.
Place blintzes in a single layer. Blend other ingredients and pour over blintzes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with sour cream.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, lemon and oleo well.
Cream oleo and add all ingredients.
Bake in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add vinegar and lemon flavoring.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake 35 minutes at 325°.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins.
Peel, slice thinly or dice.
Fry bacon slowly.
Drain on paper towels.
Crumble and set aside. Saute onions in bacon drippings until golden brown.
Blend in flour and all seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in water and vinegar. Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Fold in potatoes and crumbled bacon carefully.
Remove from heat.
Cover; let stand until ready to serve.
Serves 2.

title: macaroni-sausage casserole
directions: Boil noodles according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: wheat bread
directions: Combine warm water, yeast and 2 c. wheat flour in mixing bowl. Allow to sponge for 15 minutes.
Add honey, oil, salt, 2 tbsp. gluten flour and 4 to 5 c. wheat flour.
Add more flour until dough cleans off edge of bowl.
Dough should be smooth and elastic.

title: tater-topped casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook onion, celery and ground beef until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain.
Add salt and pepper; stir.
Spoon into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch deep baking dish. Spread soup over meat mixture.
Top with frozen potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or
until bubbly.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven and bake until cheese melts, about 5 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray.
Layer bread and sausage, then cheese.
Mix milk, eggs, salt and pepper; pour over bread, sausage and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until brown.

title: chili dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan, then spread chili over top of cream cheese.
Finally, sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top.
Heat in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: acorn cookies
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together and set aside.
Melt margarine.
Stir brown sugar into margarine, then add vanilla and pecans.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Take a teaspoonful of dough and roll into a ball.
Flatten one side on ungreased baking sheet and pinch top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until lightly brown.
Let cool.
Melt caramels with 1/4 cup water.
Dip cooled cookies into melted caramels then into crushed pecans.

title: oreo cheesecake
directions: You will also need a 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: potato bread
directions: Grease 2 large baking sheets and one large bowl with Pam.
Set aside.
In another large bowl, mix together yeast, honey, salt and 1 1/2 cups combined flour.
In a saucepan, combine mashed potatoes, milk, margarine and water.
Heat over medium heat until very warm, stirring frequently.
With mixture at low speed, beat liquid ingredients into dry ingredients.
Add egg whites.
Increase speed to medium and beat 2 minutes longer.
Stir in 3 more cups flour. Turn dough onto well-floured board.
Knead in as much of remaining flour as necessary to make a soft, but not sticky dough.
Knead dough for about 10 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Shape into ball and place in covered bowl for 1 1/2 hours.
Knead out air bubbles and shape into loaves or rolls.
Allow to rise 1 hour. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serving size:
2 slices, 3 grams fat per serving.

title: stir-fry meal in one
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth.
Drain broth.
In a large skillet, cook bacon and onions until transparent.
Add chicken and continue cooking about 5 minutes.
Stir in mushrooms, peas and pimentos. Add seasonings.
Add rice, stirring until well mixed. Heat thoroughly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: caramel rolls
directions: In Bundt pan, put pecan halves.
Arrange dinner rolls on top of pecans.
Put dry pudding on the rolls.
Put brown sugar next. Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Melt butter and pour next.
Put wax paper over top of Bundt pan.
Next morning, but in 350° oven for 20 minutes until brown.

title: summer pasta salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, cheese and milk; mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serves 4.

title: southwest smoothie
directions: *Fruit should be one kind listed and be chopped.

title: ham n' cheese tarts
directions: Blend cream cheese, milk, orange peel and mustard.
Fold in dip and ham.
Halve biscuits.
Mold each half in small muffin pan. Spoon 1 tablespoon of filling in each.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 20.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and Kool-Aid in warm water.
Add all other ingredients, except ginger ale.
Put on containers and freeze. Take out 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Mash with potato masher. Pour ginger ale over; stir and serve.
Serves approximately 50.

title: buttermilk salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar with a tight-fitting lid. Shake until smooth. Chill for 30 minutes. Yields 1 1/4 cup.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, allspice, cloves, baking soda and cinnamon and set aside.
Then, in another bowl, mix oleo and eggs.
Add sugar and tomato soup.
Mix well; add water. Alternate with adding dry ingredients.
If desired, add chopped nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in regular cake pan.
When cool, ice with a cream cheese frosting.
Very good!

title: ruth's banana nut muffins
directions: Mix and bake at 350 or 400°.

title: cream cheese fudge
directions: Melt cheese in a double boiler over low heat (do not let cheese cook).
Add the powdered sugar, a little at a time.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Place in buttered pan and chill.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Pour dressing over and mix well.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Thaw potatoes for 30 minutes.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix rest of the ingredients together. Spread over the potatoes. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; pour into deep baking dish and mix in corn, tomato soup and chili powder.
Mix corn bread according to instructions on box; spread over top of hamburger mixture.
Bake at 325° until bread is brown on top, approximately 40 to 45 minutes.

title: parmesan salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Run under cold water and drain thoroughly.
Toss all ingredients together and beautify with a few sprays of parsley and a radish flower.

title: rachel's banana nut bar
directions: Mix together, then add 2 beaten egg whites.
Bake in a 7 x 9-inch greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
To serve, slice thin and spread with cream cheese.

title: orange blossoms
directions: Mix 1 box yellow cake mix, lemon instant pudding, 4 eggs, 3/4 cup cooking oil and 3/4 cup water.
Fill mini muffin pans (1 teaspoon each).
Bake at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Separate biscuits into 20 pieces.
Roll biscuits around apples. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Melt butter and sugars in water and boil for 1 minute.
Pour over apples and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: west point chili
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add beef and brown.
Pour off fat.
Add salt, chili powder, beef broth and catsup.
Blend cornstarch and water.
Add to meat mixture and cook until thick.
Add undrained kidney beans.
Simmer 10 minutes. Serve over hot rice.
Top with shredded lettuce and cheese. Serves 2 to 3.
For 4 people, double all ingredients.
For 6 people, triple all quantities except garlic and oil.
Use 2 cloves garlic and 4 tablespoons of oil.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli into bite size pieces.
Toss other vegetables with broccoli.
Sprinkle with dressing mix and bacon.
Toss with mayonnaise.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar; set aside.
Combine cocoa, margarine, oil and water in a saucepan; heat to boiling.
Pour over flour/sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk and eggs.
Bake at 325° in a sheet pan until done.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large Dutch oven, stirring well.
Add chicken.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Add Italian seasoning, salt and pepper to sauce.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Serve over fettucine or egg noodles.
Yields 6 servings (397 calories per serving).

title: czech mushroom soup
directions: Boil diced potatoes in 1 quart water, 1 teaspoon caraway seed and 1 teaspoon salt for 15 minutes, covered.
Stir 4 tablespoons flour into sour cream, then stir into potatoes.
(If it curdles, don't worry; it will smooth out.)
Slice mushrooms thick and add. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Turn off heat; sprinkle in dill.
In a small bowl, beat 2 eggs with small amount of soup.
Pour egg mixture into pot and serve.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: christmas rainbow
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in 2 well-greased and floured 9-inch layer pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans 15 minutes.
Poke with fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Do not remove from pans.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in hot pan.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie crusts.
Place pie in freezer to chill until set.
Remove a few minutes before serving.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Grease and floured Bundt cake pan.
Mix all ingredients. Bake at 300° for about 50 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter; spoon into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour margarine over top and bake at 400° for about 25 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: garlic cabbage
directions: Heat olive oil and minced garlic in deep skillet. Cook for 1 minute; do not burn. Add chopped cabbage and toss to get oil distributed. Stir often, 5 minutes. Add 2 cups hot water with red pepper. Cover skillet and simmer for 10 minutes over medium heat.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Store in airtight container until ready to use.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain and put in baking dish.
Melt margarine and add herb stuffing mix.
Add to broccoli.
Mix mixture and soup; pour over rest of ingredients. Cover and bake 350° for 30 minutes.
Take cover off and bake until brown.

title: funnel cakes
directions: In mixing bowl, combine eggs and milk.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add egg mixture.
Beat smooth with rotary beater. (Test mixture to see if it flows easily through funnel.
If too thick, add small amount of milk; if too thin, add small amount of flour.)

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well and squeeze to remove excess moisture.
Combine spinach and remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes. Yield:
11 dozen.
May be frozen before or after baking for later use.
Thaw slightly and reheat.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Soften cream cheese; add the tomatoes, green chillies and scallions.
Spread over tortillas with rubber spatula; roll up like a jelly roll.
Refrigerate covered for at least two hours. Slice in 1/4 to 1/2 inch pieces.
Serve, using toothpicks to dip into the picante sauce.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Place ham hock and beans in large pot. Cover with water, add onions, celery, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Salt lightly as ham hock is very salty.
Bring to a boil, cook slowly at least 3 hours or until meat leaves bone and beans are tender.
Serve over cooked rice.
Makes 10 to 12 servings. Left over beans freeze well.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add taco seasoning and onion. Spread beans on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Add meat mixture; layer remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Mix crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and margarine. Press firmly and evenly in bottom of ungreased baking pan (9 x 9 x 2-inches).
Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Beat in 1/2 cup sugar, the cream cheese and vanilla until smooth.
Pour over crumb mixture.
Bake 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top and cool.

title: parve refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften yeast in the warm water and set aside; let cool to lukewarm.
In a medium-sized bowl, combine ginger ale, sugar, margarine and salt.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour to this mixture and beat well.
Beat in yeast and egg.
Gradually add remaining flour, beating well.
Place dough in a large greased bowl.
Turn dough once to grease surface.
Cover and chill overnight.
Grease a 6 muffin pan.
Form rolls by placing three 1-inch balls in each muffin cup and brush the top with melted margarine.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Yield:
6 rolls.

title: hanover beef brisket
directions: Combine consomme, soy sauce, lemon juice and garlic.
Pour over meat and marinate 12 to 24 hours.
Place roast and liquid in a 300° oven.
Roast should be covered with aluminum foil or lid. Roast for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven and top with sliced onions.
Place vegetables around the roast in the juices.
Return to the oven and roast an additional 1 to 1 1/2 hours until vegetables are tender.

title: company macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni per directions and drain.
Lightly saute pimento and onion in 3 tablespoons margarine.
Mix all ingredients and place in buttered casserole.
Cover with a bit more cheese (Parmesan or other).
Bake 25 minutes at 300°.

title: sugar-free pear butter
directions: In a kettle, combine water and 1/4 cup lemon juice.
Peel, core and quarter the pears, placing them in lemon juice mixture to retard browning until all have been peeled.
Drain liquid in kettle.
Add grape juice and remaining juice; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium; cook until pears are soft, 20 minutes; stir occasionally.
Cool Press through sieve or food processor.
Return puree to kettle.
Add spices; cook; stir until thick, 20 to 35 minutes.
Remove from heat, add sweetener.
Pour into hot jars leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Process in a boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: easy tuna casserole
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 35 minutes.

title: green beans supreme
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter.
Saute onion, then add flour, and salt and pepper, mixing well.
Add sour cream and heat.
Blend with cooked green beans and pour into shallow 1-quart size baking dish.
Top with shredded cheese and bake 15 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: hommos bi tahina (chickpea paste)(lebanese; international)
directions: Soak chickpeas in cold water overnight.
Drain, cover with fresh water and boil for about 1 1/2 hours.
Crush garlic with 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Put the tahini, lemon juice and garlic into the liquidiser goblet; add chickpeas and blend to a creamy paste.
Turn out, add more lemon juice and salt to taste.
(It should be slightly sharp.)
If you wish, add olive oil to give a softer texture.
If you have no liquidiser, rub peas through a sieve, then beat in the garlic.
Add the tahini gradually, then lemon juice and seasoning.
Turn into bowl and garnish.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt and mustard. Into greased baking dish layer bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Delicious!
I use it a lot for Christmas morning.

title: no roll sugar cookie
directions: Mix sugars, margarine and oil together.
Add eggs and vanilla. Combine dry ingredients and mix into creamed mixture.
Roll dough into small balls.
Press them with a sugar coated press.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix ingredients until dissolved.
Freeze in container (milk jugs).
Take out until slushy.
Add 1 bottle ginger ale to each gallon.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Drop by spoonful onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Lightly butter a 9-inch square glass baking dish or 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cream butter and sugar with mixer. Beat in eggs. By hand, stir in pineapple, milk and vanilla. Fold in bread. Bake 1 hour. Serve hot or at room temperature. Serves 8.

title: cream cheese filled cupcakes
directions: Beat cheese and sugar on medium.
Beat in egg and dash of salt. Stir in chocolate bits.
Prepare cake mix according to directions. Line muffin pans with paper cups.
Fill 2/3 full with cake batter, then drop 1 rounded teaspoonful of cream cheese mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 32 cupcakes.

title: basic doughnut
directions: Cream shortening and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well. Mix other dry ingredients (except last 1/2 cup sugar) in separate bowl.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients.
Beat well; add last 1/2 cup sugar.
With a tablespoon, fill doughnut.
Makes about 18 doughnuts.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Place sugar, Karo syrup
and
dry roasted nuts in electric fry pan.
Set at 360°.
Set timer; stir constantly for 9 to
10 minutes.
Stir in quickly 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Pour on ungreased cookie sheet.
Spread with back of spoon.
Cool. Break into pieces.

title: beef brisket
directions: Place brisket on large piece of foil.
Spread A.1. sauce on both sides of meat.
Sprinkle with the dried onion soup mix and the can of mushrooms, drained.
Completely enclose the meat in the foil and cook at 325° for 3 hours.

title: toffee
directions: In an 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan, sprinkle 1/2 of pecans on bottom. Break Hershey bars into sections; arrange on nuts.
Set aside. In a heavy saucepan, combine the butter, Karo syrup, water and sugar.
Cook over medium-low heat to 300°.
(It turns from pale yellow to light brown.)
Pour over chocolate and nut layer. Spread gently to cover.
Arrange rest of chocolate bars on top; allow to soften for a minute or so and spread.
May sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped pecans on top.
Let stand at room temperature.
Break into pieces.

title: lemon filling
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt, lemon juice and rind.
Cook over low heat or boiling water, stirring, until thickened.
Cook 10 minutes more; stir often.
Stir hot mixture slowly into eggs.
Return to pan.
Add fat; cook 2 minutes, stirring.
Cool.

title: sweet-n-sour kielbasa
directions: Slice kielbasa into bite size pieces.
In a crock-pot, combine all ingredients and cook on high for 2 to 3 hours or on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine 1 cup whipped topping; mix with pudding mix, pumpkin and milk.
Add spices.
Mix slowly with blender for about a minute. Pour into pie shell.
Chill until set, about 2 hours.

title: kyle's monkey bread
directions: Note:
There will be sugar left from the cinnamon-sugar that the biscuits are rolled in.
Use this for granulated called for plus enough to make the 1/2 cup called for.

title: crock-pot italian beef
directions: Place in crock-pot and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or 5 to 6 hours on high.
Serve on sub buns.
Freezes well.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from cleaned mushrooms and chop stems finely in food processor.
Do not puree.
Scrape out the inside of mushroom caps with the tip of a potato peeler or spoon and add to chopped stems.

title: rotel dip
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger meat and drain well.
Put into crock-pot.
Add soup (undiluted), tomatoes and cheese, cut up into small chunks.
Mix all together good and turn on high until cheese melts good and then turn on low until ready to serve.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: microwave broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli 4 minutes; set aside.
Cook onion, celery and margarine in a covered dish for 2 minutes.
Now, put broccoli and all other ingredients, except cheese, in dish.
Cook 3 minutes. Now, add garlic cheese.
Cook all for 3 to 4 minutes or until bubbly.

title: french fudge
directions: In top of double boiler, melt chocolate chips over hot water. Remove from heat.
Add condensed milk, vanilla, salt and nuts. Stir until smooth.
Pour into wax paper lined 8 inch square pan. Chill.
Store in air-tight container.

title: jo ann's beef, beans and rice
directions: Brown beef; add onion and rice.
Brown slightly.
Add remaining ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Cover with lid or foil.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: grandma's brownies
directions: This recipe has become such a favorite amongst friends that we bake and give as birthday and valentine gifts.
We also take them on every camping, canoe and Canada trips.

title: three layer salad
directions: First Layer:
Jell-O.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water and dissolve. Add 3 1/2 cups water.
Add 1 can crushed pineapple, drained.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Chill.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown and drain hamburger and sausage.
Put in large pot and add mushroom soup and taco sauce. Stir on low heat.
Cube cheese and add to mixture.
Heat on low heat.

title: apple cheese ball
directions: Process first 4 ingredients in a food processor until smooth, stopping to scrape down sides.
Chill 30 minutes.
Shape cheese mixture into a ball and make an indentation in the top to resemble an apple.
Chill 30 minutes.
Coat ball heavily in paprika.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Insert cinnamon stick and bay leaf into indentation to resemble apple stem and leaf.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: dandy sandwich
directions: Put peanut butter in a bowl. Add applesauce. Stir and mix well. Spread mixture on bread. Put another slice of bread on top.

title: cabbage nibblers
directions: Combine butter, cheeses, salt, lemon juice, green pepper, celery, 1/4 cup nuts and cabbage.
Shape into tiny balls.
Roll balls in nuts.
Refrigerate.
Serve as cocktail nibblers.
Makes about 40.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook 4 to 6 hours on low or cook on stove top on low heat until completely heated.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Boil the oleo, sugar, cocoa and milk for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oats and vanilla.
Stir well.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool and then enjoy.

title: fruit blintzes
directions: Heat pan for pancake mix on medium-low.
Mix pancake mix rather thin, with no lumps.
Pour 1/4 cup in pan and rotate pan to spread it out thin and evenly.
Flip.
Put on plate and spread 3 tablespoons pie filling in line in center of Blintz.
Add 1 or 2 tablespoons sour cream.
Fold over as a burrito.
Pour 1 tablespoon melted butter over lengthwise.
Garnish with 1 or 2 teaspoons powdered sugar.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: 4-layer delight(lemon pie)
directions: Prepare cheese cake according to directions and spread on crust.

title: beverly's fruit salad or dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill.
Can be served 45 minutes to one hour after preparation when strawberries thaw.
Very good and pretty!

title: rainbow ribbon jello
directions: Mix Miracle Whip and Cool Whip together and set aside. Dissolve one package of gelatin in 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Add 1 teaspoon of vinegar.
Pour 3/4 cup jello into an 8-inch square pan.
Chill 25 to 30 minutes (set, but not real firm).
Blend remaining gelatin into 3 tablespoons of the blended Miracle Whip and Cool Whip.
Spoon over set jello and chill 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple walnut fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Cream together butter and sugar. Blend in eggs, one at a time, until smooth.
Blend in vanilla. Gradually blend in dry mixture and stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour in pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery with margarine.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° or until bubbly.

title: peaches and cream cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese, 6 tablespoons peach juice and sugar.
Make cake according to directions, substituting 1/2 cup peach juice for 1/2 cup water.
Pour in a prepared pan.
Slice peaches in half and cover top of cake mixture.
Drop cream cheese mixture by spoonfuls onto cake mixture in rows until gone. Sprinkle top with cinnamon/sugar and bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until cake mixture is done.
(Cream sections will be wet!)
Serve hot or cold, topped with whipped cream if desired or Cool Whip as icing.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Boil shrimp in water until pink; drain and set aside to cool. In large pot, mix cream of mushroom
soup, cream, water and curry. Peel shells off shrimp; cut into bite size pieces. Add
to
pot. Bring to slow boil for 1/2 hour.
Add
eggs
to pot.
Turn off heat; let sit until ready to eat.
Serve hot.

title: potato soup
directions: In a pot of water, boil seasonings, potatoes, carrots and onion until tender.
Add bacon, sausage and cream.
Stir and enjoy.

title: festive mullet
directions: Remove skin on fish and
cut into serving portions.
Dip fish pieces in dressing and roll in cracker crumbs.
Place fish on a well greased cookie
sheet; drizzle melted oil over pieces of fish sprinkled with paprika. Bake in hot oven at 500° for 10 to 12 minutes or until fish
flakes easily with a fork.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add unbeaten eggs with flour.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salt water until tender; drain.
Add corned beef, cheese, soup, milk and onion.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken, cheese, broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken, then remove bones.
Mix chicken with broccoli after boiled.
Mix all other ingredients together (except cheese).

title: stuffed zucchini boats
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise, leaving the ends trimmed but intact. Using a spoon (grapefruit spoon works well!), scoop out insides to form boats, keeping all zucchini "meat"; set aside.

title: layered salad
directions: In a glass bowl, layer the ingredients.
Cover bowl tightly with Saran wrap; chill overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: alexys' vegetable dip
directions: Combine all.
Separate egg.
Add chopped egg white to the rest.
Yolk is crumbled and put on top.
Serve with any raw vegetables.
It is great!

title: lois nelson's hot tortilla
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll up and cut size desired.
Refrigerate.

title: tea punch
directions: Early in Day:
Stir tea with sugar until dissolved and chill.

title: lasagna
directions: Fry and chop hamburger in skillet.
After cooked, add jar of Prego spaghetti sauce and mix well.
Cook lasagna noodles as directed on box.
When cooked, layer noodles, hamburger mixture and cheese until you fill a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake in oven at 325° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: parmesan fish fillets
directions: Wash fish.
Pat dry.
In a small bowl stir together egg white and
water.
Mix
together
crumbs, Parmesan cheese and parsley. Dip
fish
into
egg
white mixture, then into crumb mixture. Lightly
grease
large
skillet and cook fish in hot skillet for 6 to 8 minutes until fish flakes easily with fork. Turn once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Cook all ingredients in slow cooker for 4 to 5 hours on medium heat.
Stir once or twice.
When completely cooked, add 1 bag no-egg noodles or noodles of choice and 1 cup fresh, sliced mushrooms.
Heat until noodles are cooked through and tender, about 30 minutes.
Delicious.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook soup meat with salt in 2 quarts water until soft.
Remove from broth and cool enough so meat can be taken from bone and cut into small pieces.
Return meat to broth.
Add all other ingredients plus water, enough to cover.
Cook until vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes.
Add additional salt and pepper to taste.
Any vegetable in season can be used.

title: no oil bean salad
directions: Drain liquid from beans.
Combine ingredients and marinate overnight in the refrigerator.

title: tammy's refrigerator dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers thoroughly in a gallon glass jar.
Place 2 grape leaves, 4 garlic cloves and 2 sprigs fresh dill on bottom. Pack cucumbers in, standing on large end.
Fill in center.
Put in 2 grape leaves on stacked pickles.
Put 4 garlic cloves and 2 sprigs of dill.
Pack jar to top with rest of cucumbers.
Put in the rest of garlic cloves.
Cram 1 more sprig of dill on top with grape leaf.
In a large saucepan, put vinegar, salt and 3/4 gallon water.
Bring to rolling boil.
Pour boiling vinegar over cucumbers.
Run handle of wooden spoon through packed cucumbers to be sure brine touches all cucumbers.
Be sure top grape leaf is covered.
Shake jar after covering with plastic lid, no metal lid. Put top on tight.
Turn jar upside down.
Let it sit 1/2 hour. Put in fridge for 3 weeks before use.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Put
all vegetables in a bowl.	Mix salt, oil, vinegar, paprika
and
sugar.
Pour	over vegetables and toss.
Let set several hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.

title: sloppy joe(large recipe)
directions: Saute first three ingredients in hot oil.
Stir in seasoned meat.
Cook until slightly brown.
Blend in tomato paste.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve on round split bun or toasted bun.
Serves 100 (2 ounces per person.

title: deviled ham and cheese ball
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients except nuts.
Mix well.
Chill until firm.
Form the cheese mixture into a ball. Roll the cheese ball in the nuts and chill several hours or overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: gold coast pork chops
directions: In skillet, brown chops (use shortening if necessary); pour off fat and blot pork chops with paper towels.
Stir in soup, 1/4 cup water, carrots, onion and sage.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes. Add green pepper; cook 15 minutes more or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Add more water if needed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, cook bacon until crisp; remove bacon, reserving drippings.
Drain corn, reserving liquid.
To bacon drippings in pan, add liquid, onion, potatoes and salt.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add soup, milk and corn and heat through.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Crumble bacon on top.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: dump cake
directions: In greased pan, dump undrained pineapple.
Spread pie filling over pineapple.
Dump dry cake mix over pie filling.
Drizzle melted butter over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream margarine with sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add baking powder, salt and milk.
Beat well.
Gently stir in flour, then blueberries.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes.

title: evil salad *
directions: To assemble, layer about 1/3 of the mixed salad greens in a bowl; dot with teaspoons of salad dressing.
Add 1/3 of the onion rings and peas.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Add 1/3 of the cheese.
Repeat layers, seasoning each.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Do not toss.
Serve as is.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: linguica soup
directions: Soak kidney beans in water overnight; drain.
Cook, brown and slice linguica.
In a large 8-quart pot, add linguica, onions, beans, cabbage, garlic, salt, pepper, vinegar and tomatoes.
Add water to cover.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer 30 minutes. Then add tomatoes and simmer an additional 2 hours.
Add the cubed potatoes the last 1/2 hour.

title: almond pinecones
directions: Spread almonds in a single layer in a shallow pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes, stirring often, until almonds just begin to turn color.

title: dump cake or banana bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, apricot preserves, butter, vanilla and bananas until smooth, then add dry ingredients.
Mix and add the nuts, if you like.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with confectioners sugar, Cool Whip or orange, apricot preserves.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until tender.
Cool.
Meanwhile, chop onions, pickles, eggs, celery, pepper and pimento.
Mix all ingredients together with enough Miracle Whip dressing to soften. Garnish with boiled egg slices.

title: chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
