Cut up chicken in bottom of pan.
Slice eggs on top of of chicken.
Mix soup and chicken broth and pour over chicken and eggs.
Mix flour, milk, mayonnaise and butter and pour over other.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a heavy pan bring sugar,
Karo,
and
oleo to a boil and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Stir well and pour over popcorn.	Place in
pans (13 x 9 x 2-inches). Bake 1 hour at 250°, stir	often.	Remove to wax paper.
Store in airtight containers.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix mushroom soup with vegetables.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Add croutons or French fried onions to top and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: whipped cream pie
directions: Included in this section are foods that are considered "basic" cooking.
You have to start somewhere and these are foods that are easy to prepare and everyone should know how to cook.
Some good cooks are born, I suppose, but most good cooks have learned how to be one!
Nothing in this section is fancy, but all are good, especially if you want to know how to cook good Southern food!
The more you cook and the more you know which foods taste good together, the better cook you will become.
You can make up your own recipes when you are able to put ingredients together that you know will taste good.
Cooking is fun and should always be that way because most of us are going to have to cook for the rest of our lives!
You must remember that everybody makes mistakes when they are first learning how to cook; take heart, you will continue to improve each time you cook something.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Alternate flour, milk and pecans; add baking powder to flour before adding.
Add vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for one hour or until cake leaves edge of pan.
"Wonderful!"

title: stir-fried flank steak with red pepper and celery
directions: Cut the steak with the grain into 2-inch wide strips, then cut each strip across the grain into 1/4-inch thick slices.
In a medium bowl, combine the steak with the soy sauce, 1 tablespoon of the oil and 2 teaspoons of the cornstarch.
Stir to coat the steak; set aside.
Cut the bell pepper into thin slivers.
Cut the onion into 1/2-inch thick wedges.
Cut the celery on the diagonal into 1/2-inch slices.

title: lo-cal shake and bake chicken
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except chicken.
Roll chicken in mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: teriyaki
directions: Cut the steak into thin slices or strips.
Combine all other ingredients and pour the mixture over the meat.
Allow to stand 2 hours.
Thread the meat on skewers and broil quickly on both sides over barbecue or in preheated broiler.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook rice according to directions on box.
In bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, place strips of bacon.
Spread rice over the bacon strips.
Place browned chicken over rice.
Mix soup, onion, milk, salt, pepper and cinnamon together.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Bake for 45 minutes. Bring out.
Add cheese in strips.
Put back in oven; cook for 15 minutes.

title: fruit colors
directions: You will need skewers or popsicle sticks.

title: chocolate cake doughnuts
directions: Mix together sugar, shortening, salt, vanilla and cocoa.
Add remaining ingredients and more flour, if needed.
Roll out on a floured board.
Cut out and fry in deep fat.

title: grammie hammond's cherry pudding
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, milk and butter.
Mix flour and baking powder; slowly add to creamed mixture.
Add cherries last, stirring slowly.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Check with toothpick.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Cream butter thoroughly with sugar until light and fluffy; beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add mashed potatoes, vanilla and spices; blend well.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add to potato mixture, blending and mixing thoroughly.
Fold in nuts and coconut.
Turn into greased and lightly floured 10-inch tube cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve 1 cup of the juice.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add 7-Up, crushed pineapple, marshmallows and banana slices.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: sand tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Mix first 4 ingredients until smooth. Add nuts and vanilla.
Shape into rolls about the sized of little finger.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet approximately 1 hour. Roll in confectioners sugar.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Cook frozen broccoli until tender.
Drain all excess water from broccoli.
In same baking dish, mix together broccoli, soup, mayonnaise, cheese and onion.
Beat the 3 eggs and add to the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar, eggs and some of the milk.
Stir well, then add remaining milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until thick. After thickens, layer wafers, bananas and pudding. Make meringue with egg whites and put on top of pudding.

title: dutch apple bread
directions: Cream 1/2 cup butter or margarine, 1 cup sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add 2 cups flour, baking soda and salt alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in chopped or grated apples (use green apples) and chopped pecans.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Combine 1/3 cup flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon and 1/4 cup butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Test, cool before cutting.

title: stuffed frankfurter casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water until tender; drain. Mix macaroni, milk, salt, Worcestershire sauce and 3/4 cup grated cheese.
Put this into a greased, shallow casserole dish.
Combine pickle relish and onions.
Split frankfurters lengthwise; fill with relish and onion mixture.
Top with remaining cheese and place on top of the macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: beans
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Put 3 pats butter.
Bake 1/2 hour.

title: mom's snow cream
directions: Mix sugar and flour (or pudding mix) and cocoa.
Add milk and vanilla gradually until mixed.
Add snow until it is thick.
Serve immediately or store in the refrigerator.

title: potatoes solit
directions: Boil some water and put in some potatoes.
Add some green onion, Miracle Whip, chives and green and red pepper.
That's all.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onions, pepper and garlic in 1 tablespoon butter. Combine onion mixture with cooked chicken, beans and chilies.
Set aside.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bread chicken and brown both sides. Layer in baking pan the chicken, Prosciutto ham, then Mozzarella cheese.
In a medium frying pan, melt butter and saute mushrooms. Add chicken broth and Marsala and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour sauce over chicken and bake for 30 minutes.

title: grandma's old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter or margarine using electric mixer or pastry blender until particles are fine.
Add egg, cream and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly.
If desired, chill for easy handling.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed and cool in cold water.
Combine oil, lemon juice, seasoned salt and Accent together.
Add onion, green pepper, celery, pimento, olives and mayonnaise.
Blend together and store in refrigerator for 24 hours, stirring occasionally during that time.
This salad will stay fresh several days if kept refrigerated.

title: sunday brunch casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove, crumble and set aside.
In the drippings, saute onion and green pepper.
Remove.
Beat eggs and milk in large bowl.
Stir in hashbrowns, cheese, salt, pepper, dill, onion, green pepper and bacon.
Transfer to a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Yield 6 to 8 servings.

title: wash day soup
directions: In a large pot put onion, garlic and meat balls.
Cover with water and bring to boiling.
Cook meat balls so they will hold their shape.
Add celery, potatoes, carrots and add V-8 juice. Add more water if needed to cover all vegetables and meatballs. Cook until vegetables are tender, about 1 hour.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: scones
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking soda and powder and salt.
Cut in margarine or butter until mixture is crumbly.
Make well in center.
In small bowl, stir sour cream and egg yolk; add to flour.
(May seem dry.)
Turn dough on floured surface.
Knead by folding and pressing.
Pat or roll dough into a 7-inch circle.
Cut in 12 wedges.
Arrange on ungreased baking sheet.
Brush with egg whites.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes until light brown.
Cool on wire rack.
Serve warm.

title: meatballs con queso
directions: About 1 hour before serving, prepare corn bread mix as label directs.
Keep warm.
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, mix ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, milk, parsley, pepper and egg.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot salad oil, cook meatballs, a few at a time, until well browned, removing them as they brown.
Spoon off fat and wipe skillet clean.
Into same skillet, over low heat, stir cheese, green chilies with their liquid, taco seasoning mix and 3/4 cup water until cheese is melted.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and mostaccioli.
In a bowl, combine egg, cottage or Ricotta cheese and all but 1/2 cup of Mozzarella cheese.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan or two (2 to 2 1/2-quart) casseroles dishes, spread one-half of mostaccioli mixture.
Layer cheese mixture over all.
Top with remaining half of mostaccioli mixture.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 40 minutes.
Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Whisk together all ingredients or shake in a covered jar.

title: black bean topper
directions: Put mashed beans in a bowl; add tomatoes, cilantro, lime peel and lime juice. Mix well. Cover and refrigerate for several hours for flavors to blend. Spoon 1 teaspoon of mixture onto each cracker just before serving.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and food color together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix together and
spread on 1/2 English muffin and bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip bread
directions: Grease and flour pans.
Fill 5 vegetable cans 1/2 full, or 1 loaf pan.
Makes 5 small round loaves.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine flour, soda and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast mixture and buttermilk.
Mix with spoon or hands until dough is formed.
May be made into biscuits immediately.
May be kept in refrigerator as long as 2 weeks.
Pinch off as needed and make into biscuits.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: spiced cranberry orange mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce, cold water, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves.
Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours or until thickened.
Stir in orange and nuts.
Place in mold.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.
Unmold and garnish.

title: nutritious cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add
flour,
soda
and
salt.
Mix well; stir in oats and
other ingredients.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: orange slice candy cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and juice.
Sift flour with other dry ingredients, then add to egg mixture.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into 8 x 16-inch pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool and cut in squares, then roll in confectioners sugar.

title: hot tomato sauce
directions: Cook (after all ingredients are combined) until onion and celery is done, and the mixture is desired thickness.
Put in a jar.

title: cinnamon crisp
directions: Using grandma's rolling pin, roll pastry thin.
Place pastry on cookie sheet and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned.
Cool slightly.
Pour 2 glasses of milk to drink with cinnamon crisp.
Sit down with Grandma and enjoy.

title: chocolate-peanut butter-oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add milk, sugar and cocoa.
Boil for 2 minutes. Do not over or under cook this mixture.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal. Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix and heat.
Pour over cabbage and onion.

title: fried biscuits
directions: Add yeast to warm water.
Add all ingredients.
Let dough rise.
Cut into biscuits.
Drop into hot fat and fry.

title: aplets
directions: Soak gelatine in 1/2 cup cold applesauce for about 10 minutes. Add to hot applesauce and sugar.
Cook over low heat, stirring until quite thick, about 20 minutes.
Add walnuts and vanilla. Spread in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan and let stand overnight.
Cut in squares and roll in powdered sugar.

title: old fashioned chocolate gravy
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Boil until it thickens, stirring continually on medium heat.
Serve with hot biscuits.

title: microwave cocoa fudge frosting
directions: Microwave margarine in glass bowl on High until melted about 1 minute.
Stir in cocoa until smooth.
Microwave on High until mixture boils 1/2 to 1 minute.
Add milk and confectioners sugar. Beat to spreading consistency.
Blend in vanilla.
Spread while warm.
Makes approximately 2 cups.

title: white chocolate hunks
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Drop and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: aunt fannie ruth's hush puppies
directions: *If using regular cornmeal, add 2 teaspoons baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon more salt.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Beat together zucchini, sugar and egg.
Add cooking oil; mix well.
Stir together flour, cinnamon, baking soda, nutmeg, baking powder, lemon peel and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Stir into zucchini mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° until done, 60 minutes.
Cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes. Remove from pan.

title: brownie cake
directions: In large bowl, combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, and soda.
Set aside. In saucepan, add butter, cocoa, and water.
Cook over med heat until butter is completely melted.
Remove from heat and add to cocoa mixture.
Stir until well mixed.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool completely, then frost.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together Marshmallow Creme and cream cheese.
Add several drops of juice to make as thin as desired.

title: taco dip
directions: In mixing bowl, blen cream cheese and sauce.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into serving dish and chill.
Top with lettuce, cheese, tomato and onion (if desired).
Serve with Doritos.

title: old fashioned macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole well.
Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water for about 12 minutes; drain.
Lay one slice of yellow cheese in bottom of casserole.
Then layer macaroni, followed by a layer of Cheddar cheese and a few dots of oleo.
Add a very small amount of white pepper.
Repeat the layers until 1/4-inch from top.
Add warm milk to cover mixture.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and a few dots of oleo and place 1 slice of yellow cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for at least 1 hour. Watch carefully that it doesn't boil over or cook too fast.

title: christmas divinity
directions: Butter a 2-quart saucepan.
In the saucepan, combine sugar, syrup and water.
Bring to a boil.
Stir only until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to hard ball stage (260°).
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form (tips stand straight).
Gradually pour hot syrup over egg whites, beating constantly at high speed.
Add vanilla and beat until candy holds its shape, 4 to 5 minutes.
On towel dusted with powdered sugar, quickly pat or roll candy into a 16 x 16-inch rectangle and dust with additional powdered sugar.
Spread with peanut butter and roll up using towel to help roll.
Wrap in towel. Place on cookie sheet and chill until firm, about 1 hour.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.
Slice to serve.

title: pound cake
directions: Set out butter to soften for 15 minutes.
Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating 1 minute after adding each egg.
Add flour, vanilla and lemon juice.
Beat until well blended.
Bake in cold oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not open oven door while cooking.

title: shrimp noodle supreme
directions: Combine noodles and cream cheese in medium bowl.
Spread mixture in bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch glass casserole.
Cook shrimp in butter, in large skillet, over medium-high heat until pink and tender, about 5 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Spread over noodles.
Combine all ingredients, except Cheddar cheese, in medium bowl.
Spread over shrimp.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 25 minutes, until hot and cheese is melted.
Serve with rolls or warmed French bread.
Great for company.

title: shrimp-macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine in pot and add crumbled Ritz.
In casserole add cut-up broccoli, beaten egg, mayonnaise, soup and cheese.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: pound cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the butter.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat well; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flour to cream mixture.
Add milk alternately with flour beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in extracts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until tests done.
Cool for 15 minutes before removing from pan to wire rack.

title: fried chicken with gravy
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a plastic or paper bag;
shake well.
Repeat procedure with remaining chicken.
Set 2 Tablespoons seasoned flour aside.
Heat shortening in a large skillet to 350 degrees; add chicken, and fry 5 minutes, turning frequently to brown on all sides.
Reduce heat; cover and cook an additional 25 minutes or until tender and golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Drain off pan drippings, reserving
2 Tablespoons in skillet.
Add reserved flour, stirring until smooth,
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add water;
cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Serve gravy with fried chicken.

title: ham and onion quiche
directions: Carefully remove pie shell from tin and transfer to 9-inch glass pie plate.
Microwave about 1 minute at Medium setting to soften.
Press dough gently, but firmly, into sides and bottom of plate.
Prick dough all over with fork and microwave on High setting for 3 to 4 minutes, rotating every minute.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over crust, then add an even layer each of mushrooms and ham.
In a small mixing bowl, beat together eggs, whipping cream, paprika and pepper until frothy.
Pour slowly into prepared crust.
Crumble French fried onion rings over top, then sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Microwave, uncovered, at Medium setting for 10 to 13 minutes, rotating every 4 minutes, until edges are set but center is still soft.
Let stand on heat-proof surface 5 to 10 minutes before cutting into wedges and serving.

title: spinach dip
directions: Defrost frozen spinach, squeeze dry in paper towel.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill 24 hours.
Serve with black bread, crackers or be creative.

title: lemon-poppy seed fruit bowl
directions: For dressing, in small mixer bowl, beat together the honey, lemon peel, lemon juice, poppy seed, mustard and salt.
Gradually add oil, beating with electric mixer or rotary beater until mixture is thickened.
Cover and chill.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour until crumbly (crumbs should be about the size of peas).
Add salt.
Add vinegar to milk; combine immediately with flour mixture.
Roll between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in shortening, salt and sugar.
Add flour, all at the same time.
Beat until well mixed. Cover bowl airtight.
Refrigerate at least two hours or overnight.

title: hershey chocolate pound cake
directions: Melt Hershey bars and syrup in top of double boiler.
Sift flour, salt, soda; cream Crisco and sugar.
Add dry ingredients and milk slowly.
Mix well.
Add vanilla, chocolate and eggs, one at a time.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.
Start in cold oven.
Cool and spread chocolate frosting on cake.

title: wonderful roasted onions(serves 4; prep time:  2 hours.)
directions: Quarter whole onions and place in roasting pan.
Add chopped butter, kosher salt, olive oil and ground pepper to taste.
Roast at 325° for 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.
Roast at 350° for next hour or until golden brown or slightly black.
Stir frequently.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper; cook until dissolved.
Let cool.
Place beans in large casserole dish; pour sauce over beans.
Add onion and pepper slices.
Marinate overnight.
Drain before serving.
Serves 16.

title: squash casserole
directions: If squash is frozen, let thaw.
Heat squash.
Put in mixer with oleo, eggs, salt, and pepper and beat good until smooth texture.
Add rest of ingredients.
Grease casserole and pour in mixture.
Put cracker crumbs mixed with 1/2 stick melted oleo on top.
Bake 350° until lightly brown.

title: maple syrup
directions: In heavy saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Stir in sugars. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring constantly until mixture loses its cloudiness. Remove from heat and stir in maple flavoring, then butter or margarine.

title: rainbow squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash, zucchini and onions.
Mix well with all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake for 40 minutes at 300°.

title: john's strawberry muffins
directions: Stir all dry ingredients. Combine eggs, oil and milk and add to dry ingredients.
Mix gently.
Gently fold in jam and spoon in greased muffin tins or papers.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Yields approximately 18 muffins.

title: sauce amandine
directions: Cook almonds in oleo until lightly browned.
Blend in cream of mushroom soup, minced onion and water.
Heat slowly.
Pour over green beans (cooked and lightly seasoned) with some of the vegetable liquid drained off.
Yield:
1 2/3 cups sauce; enough for 1 to 6 servings of vegetables.

title: celery dressing
directions: Mix together all ingredients except oil.
Put oil in last. Beat slowly for about 5 minutes.
Makes 1 quart.

title: roast 'coon
directions: Chill coon thoroughly.
Remove all fat and scent glands.
Rub soda well into skin.
Rinse thoroughly inside and out.
Place in deep roasting pan and barely cover with warm water.
Add onions, celery and carrot.
Cover and simmer gently 1/2 hour.
Remove coon.
Place coon on back in a roasting pan with tight lid.
Add the water and roast at 350° until tender (about 2 hours).
Remove cover; add more water if needed and roast, uncovered, to a rich brown.
Serve with dressing and gravy.

title: deer stew
directions: Brown meat in pot to lock in juice.
After browning, add water half full, then add tomato sauce and okra.
Slice and cube potatoes; set aside in a bowl of water.
Drain all water off before placing in pot.
Cook until boiling and okra is soft.
Add potatoes and mixed vegetables.
Keep fire on medium just enough to a steady bubble.
Cook for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours, until sauce is thick and potatoes are soft.
You can omit deer meat for a hearty pot of stew.

title: old fashioned coconut pie
directions: Blend sugar and butter.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add vanilla, vinegar and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cousin adie's cranberries
directions: Grind and can; it will keep all winter.
If eaten right away, put in 4 apples, 4 oranges and 2 pounds cranberries with just enough sugar to sweeten.

title: lemon pork chops
directions: Sprinkle both sides of pork chops with salt.
Place pork chops in ungreased shallow baking pan or dish.
Top each pork chop with onion slice, lemon slice, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon catsup.
Cover and bake in 350° oven 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake, spooning sauce onto pork chops occasionally until done, about 30 minutes longer.
Yields 4 servings, 425 calories per serving.

title: "chicken and rice"
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add soup and water.
Add rice.
Mix well.
Then place chicken breasts on top. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: italian cream cheese fruit filled crescent cookies
directions: Mix everything, except fruit filings, in one bowl, adding first 3 cups of flour, then the fourth cup as needed.
Dough should be slightly sticky.
Separate into 6 balls, then refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Work with 1 ball at a time.
Roll out (like pizza).
Spread 1/2 can Solo filling over entire surface. Cut into 4 sections.
Cut each section in four; roll as crescent shapes (wide end to tip).
Bake for 7 to 10 minutes, or until light golden brown.
Cool.
Sprinkle on powdered sugar.

title: vegetable jamboree
directions: Pare squash, remove seeds.
Cut in small pieces.
Cook in salted water.
When tender, add mushrooms (drained).
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Peel and cook tomatoes; season with salt, pepper, sugar and butter.

title: twix bars
directions: Line 9 x 13 pan with crackers (lay flat); set aside. Mix together sugars, oleo, milk and graham crackers in a pot. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour over the crackers. Put another layer of crackers. Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter; spread on top and chill. Cut into squares or long fingers.

title: pop and fresh cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except 1 cup flour, oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Beat 1 or 2 minutes, until well blended.
By hand, stir in remaining ingredients.
Add one optional ingredient.

title: dump cake
directions: In baking dish, spread cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple.
Cover with cake mix.
Sprinkle top with nuts and cut oleo into squares.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and cornstarch. Add alternately with apple slices in pastry shell.
Cover with sour cream.
Sprinkle topping over pie and bake in a 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and pour into casserole dish. Melt margarine.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Add milk slowly and stir until smooth.
Pour mixture over casserole.
Bake in a 400° oven for 45 minutes.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Cream
shortening,
sugar,
eggs and beat until fluffy. Add mincemeat and
chopped nuts, blend.
Drop on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sour cream cranberry salad(like piccadilly serves)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Fold in pineapple, whole cranberry sauce, nuts and grated orange rind.
Chill until partially set.
Then spoon sour cream on top and stir through to marble.
Chill until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cool 1 hour before serving. Great dip for raw vegetables, chips or as a topping on baked potatoes.
Will keep in refrigerator for a couple of weeks.

title: whoopee pie
directions: Combine and beat.
Drop from tablespoon onto cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate walnut bars
directions: Melt chocolate on top of a double boiler over hot water (not boiling).
Remove from heat; when melted, stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch square cake pan.
Cool until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crust:
Combine 2 cups graham cracker crumbs and 2 sticks of margarine.
Press in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.

title: cream chicken on rice
directions: Bake chicken breasts in baking dish for approximately 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Cut breasts into bite size chunks.
Add butter, soup and salt.
Place mixture back in oven for approximately 20 minutes.
Prepare rice as usual while chicken mixture is baking.
Spoon mixture onto rice.
Serve while warm. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Heat 4 tablespoons butter or margarine and oil in heavy, large saucepan.
Add mushrooms; saute 5 minutes.
Remove mushrooms with slotted spoon; reserve.
Add flour to pan juices; stir to form roux.
Cook until bubbly.
Slowly add broth; cook until thickened. Remove from heat.
Add cream, sherry, Parmesan cheese and nutmeg; stir until cheese melts.
Add turkey and mushrooms.
Stir well. Combine with cooked spaghetti.
Turn into greased 13 x 9-inch pan or 3-quart baking dish.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter and toss with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin pie(dietetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine pumpkin, sweetener, salt and spices thoroughly.
Blend in eggs and both milks.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Serve cool.

title: mexican rice
directions: Saute rice, onion, green pepper and garlic until tender and rice is brown.
Stir in water, bouillon and salsa.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes until rice is tender.
Stir in olives, green onion and cilantro.

title: garden walk pickles
directions: Soak first 4 ingredients in brine of 1 gallon water and 1 cup salt overnight.
Drain.
Cook other vegetables 20 minutes in salted water; drain.
Boil together vinegar, sugar and spices. Add vegetables and cook 15 minutes.
Put into hot jars and seal.

title: hapa haole spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs into bite-size pieces.
Salt and pepper ribs. Brown in hot oil on range, cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Drain off fat.
Combine cornstarch and sugar, blend in liquid, vinegar and shoyu sauce.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together and freeze. Remove from freezer 20 minutes before serving.
(Nice to make in individual molds or muffin tins.)

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine beef, pork, onion, bread crumbs, milk, salt, pepper, nutmeg, allspice and egg in a large bowl.
Blend well.
Shape into balls, about 1-inch.
Brown on all sides in shortening in skillet. Remove meatballs.

title: vicki's no bake cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Heat sugar, milk and margarine just to boil.
Remove from heat.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Allow to cool.
Makes about 36 cookies, if the little cookie bakers don't lick the bowl while they work.
In that case, make a double batch!

title: grandma's fresh cream corn
directions: Cut corn from cob. In an 8-inch skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Remove bacon and reserve bacon drippings. Add corn, milk, sugar, salt and pepper to drippings. Cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir together flour and water until smooth. Add butter to corn and flour water mixture. Cook, stirring constantly, until thick. Garnish with cooked crumbled bacon, if desired.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water.
When soft, rub through a strainer (you should have about 2 to 2 1/2 cups).
Scald the milk with onion.
Remove onion and mix the milk with potatoes.

title: wassail on the wagon
directions: Heat water; add tea, cider, lemon juice, sugar, cinnamon, cloves and cinnamon stick.
Stir well and serve warm.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix well.
Put two heaping teaspoonfuls per cup.
Add boiling water.

title: southwest chicken and brown rice
directions: Sprinkle chicken with cumin, chili powder and salt.
Heat olive oil in 10-inch skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken; cook and stir until no longer pink.
Add onion and garlic; cook and stir 2 minutes.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Coarsely chop tomatoes; set aside.
Add water to reserved liquid to make 3/4 cup.
Add liquid and picante sauce to skillet; bring to a boil. Stir in rice; reduce heat.
Cover tightly and simmer 5 minutes. Stir in beans and chopped tomatoes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand, covered, about 5 minutes until liquid is absorbed.
Sprinkle with cheese (garnish with sliced avocado).

title: italian casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with chili powder, salt and pepper.
Cook tomato sauce, green pepper, onion, garlic powder and shortening for 15 minutes.
Cook egg noodles until barely tender.
Drain. Grate cheese.
Reserve some for top of casserole.
Drain corn. Mix all parts together.
Put in buttered casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chops and rice in gravy
directions: Flour pork chops and brown in own fat.
Cover and simmer until well done.
Remove chops, add 2 tablespoons flour to fat.
Add salt and pepper.
Add enough water to make thick gravy.
Mix in soup, stir until smooth.
Serve over cooked rice with pork chops.

title: sherry's quick dinner
directions: Combine all ingredients in skillet and cover.
Cook over medium heat until desired tenderness (about 30 minutes).
Delicious and easy!

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add all ingredients and simmer a couple hours.

title: easy rolls
directions: Combine sugar, shortening and salt.
Add milk.
Let mixture cool, then add egg.
Add yeast mixture and flour, 1 cup at a time, until dough is smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise 1 1/4 hours.
Shape into desired shape.
Let rise 1/2 hour.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Combine carrots and water in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 8 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Drain off liquid and return carrots to pan.
Add honey and remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring gently, until butter melts and sugar dissolves.

title: apple-baked squash(diabetic)
directions: Cut squash in half and remove seeds.
Place cut side down in pan with 1/2-inch water.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and turn squash over.
Mix apples and cinnamon.
Fill squash cavities with apple mix.
Return to oven and bake 30 to 45 minutes until apples are tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Do not brown ground beef.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot. Add just enough water to cover beef.
Cook 1 1/2 hours until thick.

title: peach velvet cream
directions: Chill evaporated milk to ice crystal stage.
Drain peaches and dice.
Soften gelatin in 3/4 cup syrup and place over low heat. Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and salt and stir.
Mix in lemon juice and rind.
Chill until mixture is consistency of egg whites.
Crumble wafers (I use a rolling pin with cookies in plastic bag).
Whip evaporated milk until stiff, and beat in gelatin mixture.
Fold in diced peaches.
Turn mixture into 2-quart mold, alternating with layers of crushed wafers. Chill. Garnish with peach half.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Place meat in a roaster.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over the meat.
Seal tightly with foil.
Bake at
350° for 2 or 3 hours.

title: hot mustard sauce
directions: Mix all until smooth. Serve
with egg rolls or meat dishes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Scrub the potatoes.
Grease well.
Place on cookie sheet. Place in oven.
Cook at 400° until done.
Take out of oven and cut apart.
You need to use oven mitts as you may get burned.
Scoop out inside of potatoes.
Save shell.
Place inside of potato in mixing bowl.
Add margarine.
Salt to taste.
Add the Cheez Whiz. Stir until all ingredients are mixed together.
Will be lumpy. Add mixture to potato shells.
Place 1/4 to 1/2 piece of American cheese on each potato half.
Press into potato.
Return to oven until cheese melts.
Makes 16 potato halves.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Pour first 4 ingredients into long dish and top with miniature marshmallows.
Add the sliced bananas to cover and let set.
In a saucepan, combine the sugar, flour and pineapple juice.
Add the beaten egg.
Cook until thickened.
Let cook and add whipped cream.

title: santa fe casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Add taco seasonings, flour and broth.
Blend well.
Stir and bring to a boil to thicken.
Stir in sour cream and chilies.
In lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer chips, meat mixture, then cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add olives and onions before serving.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook the pasta and drain, set aside.

title: fried shrimp
directions: Clean and devein shrimp.
Slit back of shrimp to butterfly it. Mix egg and milk; salt and pepper to taste.
Dip shrimp in milk mixture, then roll in flour.
Fry in hot oil until browned.
Do not overcook or shrimp will be tough.

title: hershey pie
directions: Melt candy bars, marshmallows and milk in top of double boiler.
Cool
thoroughly.	Whip
cream
and
fold	into candy mixture, when cool.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill until serving time.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown meat with the onion.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Put in casserole and bake at 350°
for about an hour or until it begins to bubble.
Bake, uncovered.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn relish
directions: Boil corn for 5 minutes.
Remove seeds from pepper and chop. Mix all ingredients with 1 cup water and simmer for 20 minutes. Bring to a boil; put in hot jars and seal.
Makes 10 pints.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt oleo in cookie pan and add the remaining ingredients in layers.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325° until done and brown.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: rugalach
directions: Mix together flour and salt. Cream together the margarine and cream cheese until light and fluffy. Blend in flour mixture. Chill several hours in wax paper (important).
Divide dough into 4 parts. Roll out each part on a floured pastry board into a 10-inch round 1/4-inch thick.
In a small mixing bowl, mix together sugar, cinnamon, nuts and raisins.
Sprinkle 1/4 of the filling on each round and cut into 10 wedges. Start at wide end and roll up each wedge to a crescent. Repeat with remaining 3 parts of dough. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 40.

title: shrimp and sausage jambalaya
directions: Using a heavy Dutch oven, saute onion and bell pepper until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except shrimp, rice and parsley.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice and return to boil.
Simmer on low heat for 30 minutes or until the rice is done.
Add shrimp and parsley.
Heat through.
Serves 6.

title: grandpa jack's chili
directions: Slice or dice onions and brown with hamburger in a Dutch oven. Add soup, beans, water and chili powder.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: mom's italian beef
directions: Saute onions and green peppers together. Combine all ingredients and simmer for 2 to 3 hours. Serve on Italian buns.

title: horseradish carrots
directions: Place carrots in buttered casserole.
Combine water, onion, horseradish, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Pour over carrots. Top with bread or cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter or margarine. Bake uncovered at 350° until hot (about 20 minutes).

title: aunt elsie's rhubarb custard
directions: Mix with beater 2 egg yolks, sugar, flour and butter until creamy.
Then add milk and mix.
Add the rhubarb and stir.
Pour this mixture into a 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 400°
for 15 minutes and then 15 more minutes at 375° until set like custard.

title: "lazy man's" cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 12-inch pan at 350°.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over oleo, then add fruit (any kind).
Sprinkle 1 cup sugar over fruit and cinnamon or other spices to your taste.
Bake one hour.
Dough will rise to the top.
Serve with cream, if desired.

title: sweet potatoes in orange cups
directions: Cut oranges in half crosswise. Clip membranes and carefully remove pulp (do not puncture bottom). Reserve orange pulp for other uses.
Combine sweet potato and next 6 ingredients; spoon mixture evenly into orange cups.
Place cups in a 9-inch square baking pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle with marshmallows; bake an additional 5 minutes or until marshmallows melt.
Yields 8 servings (110 calories with 2% from fat per serving).

title: vegetable hot dish
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: For filling:
Mix pudding with 3 cups milk; fold in Cool Whip. Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Cover with 1/2 of filling, another layer of crackers and remaining filling. Make a third layer of crackers.

title: orange slice oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream vanilla, Butter Buds, Egg Beaters, brown sugar and white sugar together.
Add flour, oats and Grape-Nuts cereal.
Cut orange slices candy into small pieces.
Fold orange slice pieces into the dough.
Chill 1 to 2 hours or longer.
Drop from teaspoons onto cookie sheet that has been sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: date and applesauce cake *
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well.
Add the eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add the spices, raisins and nut meats to flour. Stir the soda in the applesauce.
Combine the ingredients and turn into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in a slow oven for an hour.
Very moist and delicious!

title: hot home chili
directions: Brown beef sausage and ground beef in skillet.
Discard and drainage.
Saute onion, celery and green pepper.
Pour crushed tomatoes in large deep pot.
Add meat and seasonings.
Leave garlic cloves whole.
Add all ingredients and simmer 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: bethel bread
directions: Saute green onion and bell pepper in butter until tender.
Add the crumbled bacon pieces, Parmesan cheese, olives and jalapeno peppers (if desired).
Add the quartered biscuits and mix well with hands.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Glaze or dust with powdered sugar.

title: creamy cucumber sauce
directions: On wax paper, shred cucumber; pat dry.
In medium bowl, stir cucumber and remaining ingredients until blended.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Beat sugar and margarine until creamy.
Add alternately the eggs and flour, beating well until mixed.
Beat in lemon extract. Stir in whipping cream.
Do not beat after adding whipping cream. Cook in greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
